column6: Hard Candy Sheer Envy Color Correcting Primer 753
column14:
I purchased this at Walmarts for $8. I have extremely fair skin prone to flushing and redness from rosacea.

The primer goes on smoothly and feels nice on the skin. It does not have a very liquid consistency but instead feels like very soft play-dough. I use my fingers to apply and the product melts on the face easily. Let the primer set for a moment in order to best see the coverage offered. I found the coverage to be good but not great, so if you are someone with a lot of redness or flushing be aware that this primer does not offer complete color correction. A non-sheer primer may offer a more complete experience.

I find this primer works best under a color correcting foundation and without wearing blush. For the price you get a nice quality primer with a medium amount of color correcting. Those with serious redness/rosacea issues will either need to wear a color correction foundation or look for a primer with a higher level of color correcting.

column13: Stay Away LICE! Repel Lice with LiceLogic!
column14:
Just in time for school! My daughter will be in first grade and my son is going into second grade. Last year our school had a lice epidemic. Luckily my kids did not get lice...but that's because I have always used lice repelling products. This is my first time purchasing LiceLogic and I am thrilled with it's results so far.

LiceLogic Repel Conditioning Shampoo (Lavender) smells amazing! Of course I love lavender, so I may be biased. Lavender essential oil is known to deter head lice and other insects. LiceLogic is non-toxic and hypoallergenic. It's gentle to use on the entire family...so both the kids and I will be using this shampoo on a regular basis!

The bottle comes with a safety seal (which is nice because with shipping you don't want to lose your product!). Just remove the seal and replace the cap. Now you can wash your children's hair. The shampoo itself is very thin. I prefer thicker shampoo, but it did lather very easily when I massaged it into my son's hair and scalp. We followed up with the LiceLogic Repel Conditioner.

column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column14:
I received this Crest 3D White Brilliance Duo free in the mail from Bzzagent.com to try out and share my honest opinion. In the past I have used the gel whitening trays you get made at the dentist and so far after using this product for a little over two weeks I feel like the results are very comparable. I actually prefer the Crest 3D White method because it takes no extra time out of your routine to use like bleaching trays which are an extra 15-30 minutes.

Some reviews mentioned gum sensitivity and their gums turning white which did happen to me the first two or three times. The deep cleansing tooth paste is more abrasive than most normal toothpastes and people, including myself, have a tendency to brush too roughly so when doing it with this type of toothpaste it can cause gum abrasions. After realizing this I started to brush more lightly and for no longer than a minute which is plenty of enough time. I've been setting a timer on my phone for two minutes which is helpful for not over-brushing. When brushing normally I like to brush three to four minutes so it took me a few times to get used to the reduced amount of time and mentally feeling like they were getting just as clean.

I really would recommend this product especially for anyone who drinks a lot of coffee, tea or red wine. Just after a week it was such a noticeable difference that I was pleasantly surprised. Going to the dentist to get the trays and making special trips when you run out of the whitening gel can be a hassle and costly especially when there are options now like this Crest 3D White Brilliance Duo which delivers similar results.

column6: Neutrogena Wave
column14:
I got 2 little boxes of these after using the first 14 in the box with the gadget. I'm so amazed the way it gets my skin so clean! The motor seems to be going slow, so at first I didn't think it could be doing anything, the pads smell like medicine, it's all so gentle and sort of feels ineffective, but after a few weeks, my skin looks so much better, many of my deep lines are softened up, I feel really clean, some scars and even some milia are gone. Same with some blackheads. I use each pad twice (twice in one day, it doesn't irritate one bit) to save money and it hasn't caused any problems. I'd sort of like to use one of the expensive brands for a week or two to see if there is any difference to explain the difference in price.
Oh, and I think maybe some people take off the little plastic and mesh top and that's why the disposable tops stop clinging. I have no trouble with that at all, if I hold the plastic top on with my left thumb while using my right hand to pull off the pad, which does stick very well.

column6: Pacific World Corporation Sensationail Gel Polish Starter Kit
column14: I really like this gel nail polish kit.  Everything is very easy to use, and the instructions are clear and easy to follow.  The bottles included in the kit are very small, but it came with the LED light, so I'm ok with that.  I really like how the LED light works, it flashes at 15 seconds, and turns off at 1 minute.  The light automatically goes on as soon as you put your fingers under.  I'm glad there's no button to push.  The polish works just like regular polish (just be careful to avoid your cuticles or skin), but won't try until you cure it with the light.  The polish itself is only OK.  I found it very streaky and hard to get nice even coverage.  I am very happy with the clear coat though.  The primer makes the polish really stick to your nails, so if you want to avoid scraping the polish (after soaking), don't use it.  The polish does stay on for days and days, I wanted a change after a week, so not sure how long it would last if left alone.  Overall, I think this kit is well worth the money and highly recommend it.

column6: Home Health Castor Oil
column14: I finally gave in and tried this product after researching and reading so many great things about it. I have been using it frequently and in multiple ways, and so far I really love this stuff. This brand provides a very nice product for a reasonable price. I have been massaging it into my scalp and hair, mixing it into my lotions, and buffing it into my face after cleansing with a cotton ball before bed. It makes my hair softer and shiny, and my skin soft and moisturized. It almost instantly got rid of my dry spots around my nose and eyebrows on my face, and has faded my acne scars. I haven't been using it long enough to determine whether or not it is effective for hair growth, but I am very pleased with the various other results I have gotten and will continue to use this product religiously. A little goes a long way, I use it for so many things regularly and I only need about quarter sized amounts for my longer hair and full lotion bottles, and a tablespoon at a time for multiple eyelash applications (to make sure I am not wasting a lot of product). I purchased the smallest size available and predict the bottle will last me well over six months. I have found various recipes online for a range of uses for this stuff and definitely recommend at least giving this a try. I believe it is a great alternative to expensive products and treatments for lots of uses. Obviously, with anything and pretty much everything, you will have to have patience and willingness to continue routines and experiments to find out what suites your individual needs. Sometimes things that work well for someone don't work for you, and it's a bummer when you spend $60.00 on some "miracle" product and it ends up not doing what it claims. I am glad I gave this a shot, I feel like it was worth the purchase and risk due to the inexpensive cost and amount of product. I was not paid or asked to write this review, or contacted by the seller in any way except for a default email offering servicesif I was unhappy with the product. This is my honest opinion and experience. I will purchase again when I run out.

column6: Philips HP6576 Satin Perfect Deluxe Epilator, White/Champagne
column13: Discs are the way to go!
column14: Bought this as a replacement to a different manufacturer/model after reading many of the reviews.  Immediately loved the difference of these disks versus the "tweezer" style of my old one.  The "pain" level is tons lower with this-to the point I might brave trying areas other than my legs.  I have had it for a bit now, and was kind of thinking maybe it is not working as well as when I first got it, but I actually think it is because the hair is coming back thinner when it does come back.  Have never caught skin, and have not had any ingrown hairs-but I do follow exfoliating big time as it makes a difference regardless of epilator IMHO.  The only reason I know it is missing some hairs is because of the super bright light.  Can get most even now with an extra pass or a circle motion, but honestly those missed you can't see but you might feel them.  If it's buggin me that day I might drag a razor over to catch these few next shower, but if I don't bother nobody knows but me.  The fact you can use this with the cord, which is super long, is wonderful!  I also think it is way quieter than my other one.  Charges quickly.  Warning light when battery is getting low comes on before you lose any power so to speak.  I've been epilating for a while, so I went right for the direct hit without using any of the other accessories and again, would call it almost painless.  Tried the massaging attachment and could not feel it at all.  Comfortable design, clean look.  Nice storage bag holds everything including the long cord.  My previous model had come with a freezer glove so you could kind of numb the area before you epilated.  I did use it when I first started out and gradually became comfortable enough not using it.  I would say had I started with this model I don't think the glove would have even been necessary - but if you are sensitive to pain or just starting out try using covered ice packs or frozen wash cloths until you get used to things.  It's i little pricey, but you will get more than your moneys worth with this.  Highly recommend!!ey, but you will get more than your moneys worth with this.  Highly recommend!!

column14: I like that it is natural very much!  I am about 48 and have been using this for many months, twice a day under my eyes, before writing this review.  I give it 4 stars only because my very dark circles under my eyes are about half as dark as before, but still very noticeable.  I really wanted to get rid of the dark circles most of all.  If I apply it twice a day the fine lines under and at the corners of my eyes are less noticeable as long as I am not wearing make up which then fills in the lines and then you can see them more.  If I use any extra on my fingers to the rest of my face I sometimes have a blemish but not often.  It does look shiny and a little greasy at first when applied but the shine goes away very quickly.  I am not sure how well it works with make-up since I rarely wear it.  I really hope they can improve it for people like me with very dark under eye circles so they will be completely gone.  I am again very glad it is all natural and I prefer this natural product to others I have tried at the grocery store that were full of chemicals and did not help the very dark under eye circles much at all.  Please continue to improve this very nice product.

column13: This is a great addition to my anti-aging routine - I look better than I did when I was young
column14:
I try to keep my skincare routine simple. I've used multiple products in the past, and I didn't get tremendous results, only ended up spending a fortune. I've been carefully testing different products to see which ones get the most results so I can cut down on the number of products I use. This fits into that plan. I'm also looking more and more for products that rely on natural ingredients. Again, a good fit.

More plusses: The pump is excellent, makes application easy. That being said, go easy on the product. More is not more, use very little and allow it to absorb. Put too much on, and your skin is sticky and it's a waste of product.

This product has a good amount of vitamin c, which helps build collagen and helps get rid of discolorations. The hyalauronic acid is a nice bonus, plumps up your skin, but the effect is temporary. I'm looking for permanent results. Found a fabulous natural product that truly reverses aging and works like a charm with this product [[ASIN:B00IIPI6CS Bel Essence Intensive Anti Aging Treatment - All-Natural Cream for Erasing Wrinkles. Lift, Firm, Tighten Facial Skin and Fade Fine Lines - 1.5oz]] (it was actually recommended to me by Amazon). Just these two products have taken years off my skin. Not only is my skin tone even and brighter, making me look younger (thank you vitamin c), but the Bel Essence has a mix of oils that (I did some research) are known to treat scars, build collagen and erase lines and wrinkles and smooth out your skin. One of my problems in addition to lines (fine and deep) was a \\\dimpled\\\\\" effect on my forehead. Not lines so much, although I had those too, but almost as if the pores became little cavities so my forehead had an allover rough look. Using the two products together for a couple of months, my skin is smooth, smooth, smooth. Fine lines are gone, deep lines are unnoticeable and disappear completely with make up. I have never looked better, not even when I was 20. Andthis is using just TWO products.

Give it some time, it takes a month or two for your skin to turn over and start to show the benefits, but I guarantee that you will see definite results. And - only TWO products!"

column14: I was honestly nervous about buying this brush because the price was too good to be true.  I have tried various cheaper facial & body brushes in the past and it has never worked out well and they've all ended up in the trash.  THIS brush is different, it's actually very well made.  I can not open it on my own, I actually hurt myself trying, that is the bummer.  It's kind of two sided as well, in order to truly make it waterproof, I believe they had to make it this difficult, so it's a blessing and a curse...because the water does NOT get into it (like the other "waterproof" brushes I have purchased in the past).  I also think it could spin faster, it does not have much power and my face could use a little more intensity....HOWEVER, it absolutely does clean my face and exfoliate far better than anything else I could afford.  I use it every day in the shower on my body and face, I find it a little weak for my feet so I still use my non-electric foot brush.  Basically, I had adult acne on my shoulders/back, face & neck and this has helped immensely in clearing that up.  It's definitely worth the money, but if you are expecting clarisonic or a very popular quality of microdermabrasion, it may not be for you.

column6: [The Face Shop] Essential Collagen Mask Sheet x 3pcs
column14: I've done 3 treatments with the Essential Collagen Mask Sheet spaced every 3 or 4 days.  The most immediate effect was reduced puffiness (hello, cheekbones!) which lasted between applications.  My skin is smooth and faintly dewy directly after treatment, with a slight reduction in pore size.  Those benefits fade for me after about 24 hours.  So why just 4 stars?  These sheets contain a generous amount of both alcohol and fragrance which caused minor irritation for me after the first use.  Then why still 4 stars?  I was able to control the issue by shortening the sheet time to 15 minutes, then rinsing my face after about an hour and applying toner and moisturizer.  While the fragrance is inescapable, it does rinse away pretty well.  All in all The Face Shop Essential Collagen Mask Sheet is a good product at a good price for those who don't suffer from contact or fragrance allergies, or excessive sensitivity.  I will probably experiment with brands that are purer but will be comparing their performance to The Face Shop masks.

column6: Instanatural Vitamin C Toner
column13: I'm Usually A InstaNatural Product Fan But...
column14:
If you read my other reviews on InstaNatural products you will see I am a fan for the most part so when I got the opportunity to try their toner I was super excited....welll... I'm not so excited anymore.

This toner is just ok, but like many others have said it is not worth the price. It does have a strong floral scent (which is the geranium oil). I like it but I can see where it could be overwhelming to those who are sensitive to smells.

I am also not a fan of spray toners, I like to apply toner with a cotton pad. I honestly can't say I saw a reduction in my pores by using this. If it just said it was a toner with no claims to reduce pores, I would've rated it 4 stars.

The other thing I think InstaNatural needs to change immediately is the print on the bottle. The white lettering on a light yellow background is not good plus the print is super tiny. I actually had to go back to the Amazon page and look at the print with the magnifier option.

To end on a good note I will say that is is refreshing and sprays on evenly and lightly. It soaks in quickly and doesn't leave a residue.

Overall I am still a fan of InstaNatural products, just a little disappointed with this one.

InstaNatural provided this sample for testing and review with no guarantee of a favorable review.

column13: The BEST Trimmer I ever bought!!
column14:
I've had my Styliner II for months now and I can say it's a great trimmer. It gives me a close shave and doesn't get hot at all from my experience with it. I recommend this to anybody looking for a good quality trimmer, a close shave, and a trimmer that doesn't get hot after just minutes of usage like some others do.

This trimmer is a miracle for me. I have tried at least a dozen cheaper trimmers through the years and some were ok but none cut this close or were as quick to use. column6: Fractionated Coconut Oil - Pure USA Expeller Cold Pressed & Hexane Free - Best Therapeutic Grade Carrier Oil for Essential Oils Aromatherapy & Massage - Food Grade MCT - Lg 16oz - 12 Ellie's Recipes
column13: Works great, absorbs well, useful for self massage and keeping skin supple!
column14:
I use oil's for a variety of reasons. Chiefly for self massage. However I also use them for hair and body. This oil is very easy to use and goes on smoothly. It didn't leave a really oily residue or smell that was unpleasant at all afterwords. I like to use oils on my legs after a shower because I find that some of the lotions irritate with their perfume and alcohol. I have not tried this on my hair yet because it is summer and, since moving to DC, I have not done much summer deep treatments of my hair. When I was in San Diego I did them all the time because it was so dry of a climate. Now I get a ton of humidity just from the environment so the need comes more in the winter. This is a great sized bottle that should last a long time if properly stored.

In terms of self massage this oil works flawlessly. It's smooth and retains on the surface long enough to work it in, does not leave oily hands, and you don't need to use a ton of it. It's not portable - so if you want to take it somewhere else you'll have to put some in a smaller travel sized bottle. It's a little unwieldily at times due to it's size and shape. Not easy to just carry around. While that means it provides great value for your dollar it is a consideration if you expect to put this in a gym bag or such. YMMV.

column6: Green Tidings All Natural Deodorant, Extra Strength All Day Protection; 2 Sizes; Unscented or Lavender (Vegan, Certified Cruelty Free)
column14:
I have been using Green Tidings deodorant for about a year now and don't plan on switching! A couple helpful observations:
-This deodorant does not stain clothes. There may be a little noticeable rub off on dark clothing when changing (like with most deodorants) , but it washes out.
-I have noticed my underarms look much healthier after wearing this deodorant.
-I still notice a little odor after a hard workout or very stressful situation, but these are times when regular unnatural deodorant would have left an odor as well.
-I have tried the lavender and unscented varieties and definitely prefer the lavendar. It seems to have a little more solid consistancy and also smells good.
-One 1oz container lasts me a little over a month.
Overall I love this deodorant and it is great for everyday use (with no odor!) and even conditions my skin. As an added bonus, the customer service is great.

column14: Ok, so I found how this deodorant works by accident. Here's the story. I had recently got off of a parasite cleanse (another story within itself!) I did 2 rounds which was the length of 30 days.  On the first 2 days of my parasite cleanse, I noticed my body odor just disappeared! It was crazy.  I could get out the shower and not put any deodorant on for at least one hour and would not smell a thing or sweat under my arms. I thought "wow, body odor has a lot to do with the crap I'm putting in my body", which at the time I was expelling through the cleanse.  So after I did that cleanse, I moved onto a heavy metal detox, so of course, I went looking for a deodorant that was aluminum free aka CRAZINESS free or that would defeat the purpose of the metal detox, right? So I found the Hugo Naturals deodorant and applied it the next day.  A little thicker than most which makes it a little of a challenge to apply but when I tell you NOTHING all day.  No smell, no sweat, NOTHING.  So what I am saying is that it works in conjunction with a healthier lifestyle.  That's why companies came up with powerful ingredients like aluminum to fight off the bad odor we carry around instead of telling you to ditch the bad diet because it's easier, and if you are not cleansing regularly, then of course, your going to reek! Let's stop trying to cover it up with ingredients that reek havoc in our body but extract it from the source. Let's be real, you can't expect this product with ingredients like this to work for you if you are not doing your part as well.  This product delivered exactly what it says and that's to provide you with an aluminum, paraben, and alcohol free deodorant, and it does just that!  You gotta do your part too for it to work at its best.  It's like doing a cleanse and at the same time eating junk and wondering why the cleanse is not working.  Duh!!!

column6: Philips Norelco AT895/41 Shaver 4900
column14:
After my dog decided to use my last one as a chew toy, I decided to upgrade from the standard rechargeable Norelco I'd been getting to a nicer one.

The first thing I notice is how modern and sleek this Norelco looks, standing on its charger in all black. The charging dock makes charging and storage convenient, and I'm very pleased with the result.

Second, the Norelco operates quieter and shaves smoother than my previous Norelco. The hinges on the sides really help to contour the heads around your face and the end result is less irritation and a faster shave.

Everything else is the same standard of quality I've gotten from my last few Norelco shavers. I'm confident that this will last me quite a few years, hopefully even longer than my last two.

TIPS:
- Buy the replacement heads on here [[ASIN:B000068PBT Philips Norelco HQ8 Dual Precision Replacement Heads]] instead of on Norelco's website - you'll pay 10% of the price they charge on their site and you can also get them subscribe and save to pay even less.
- Oil the shaver heads just as you would a razor or electric clippers, though you can oil these every two weeks instead of after every use like clippers. I use [[ASIN:B000LNB8HK Andis 12750 Cool Care Plus, 15.5 oz]] as it's cheap, a huge can, and it has great ingredients to make your blades last twice as long (you should replace them once a year but oiling them will make them last 2 years)

column6: Best-Selling Hyaluronic Acid Serum for Skin-- 100% Pure-Highest Quality, Anti-Aging Serum-- Intense Hydration + Moisture, Non-greasy, Paraben-free, Vegan--Best Hyaluronic Acid for Your Face (Pro Formula)
column13: I Thought It Sounded Like a Good Idea. I Was Right
column14:
I have been using this Hyaluronic acid serum for a while now as a part of my skin care regimen. I am a nurse and knew that I had used hyaluronic acid to draw moisture to areas of the body that had been injured by damaging medications accidentally leaked into the tissues. So I thought the premise of the idea was sound. Would it work topically? I didn't know, but for the price it was worth a try.

I place a couple of drops on my fingers and spread it all over my face, paying attention to the dry areas and areas with those fine lines that come with the territory. I wasn't convinced that I was really seeing a lot of improvement until my coworker asked me what I was doing... that my face looked great. I was really surprised. I used this product along with Neutragena's Healthy Skin Anti Wrinkle Night Cream at night alternately with Derma E Firming Moisturizer. All that combined really left my face looking brighter, my skin softer. I have since stopped using the other products as they ran out. I am still using the acid, because you get a lot and a little goes a long way. I can still see improvement in my skin. I think it's a great product.

column6: Pacific World Corporation Mycocide Clinical NS Antifungal Liquid, 0.25 Fluid Ounce
column13: This DOES work but with a lot of patience.
column14: About a year ago when I first started using this product, both of my big toe toenails were infected with fungus both on the surface of the nail and below the surface. My wife had the same problem although her s had been infected long before mine. This product DOES work if you follow the directions on the package. It does not kill fungus UNDER the nail however if applied according to directions consistently, it WILL prevent your new nail growth, as it grows in, from becoming infected while the old infected infected nail growth grows out. I have used it myself on two toenails that were (note I said WERE) both infected. Neither nail is infected now after using consistently for about a year. My wife has met with equal success. The trick is to reapply every day by following the directions closely for about a year as your old nails grow out. I have "before" and "after" pictures as proof and will post those when I find them.

column6: Alina Skin Care VITAMIN C SERUM with Hyaluronic Acid Moisturizer and Green & White Tea Extracts, 1 ounce
column13: Best formulated and best smelling vitamin C serum yet
column14:
How do you compare the hundreds of skin care products? As a regular tester, I've arrived at a list of key considerations. I hope these are helpful to you!

~ Fragrance: Heavenly fresh grapefruit/mandarin orange scent from natural oils. One of the best smelling creams Iâ€™ve ever tested.
~ Feel during application: Smooth, like a medium weight lotion.
~ Feel after absorption: Smooth and soft, but with no film or greasy sensation.
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: Probably suitable for all. No issues with my oily and sensitive skin, it actually feels great to me.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No.
~ Packaging: 1oz frosted glass bottle with pump top. With care, pump will dispense exactly how much you want, but if youâ€™re careless youâ€™ll get a huge squirt.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* Fine lines and wrinkles are reduced and skin has a nice glow. Very slight mattifying of oily skin.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* There are not a huge number of active ingredients but they have been chosen with care. There are two forms of vitamin C, one is an ester I donâ€™t see often in skin care products that looks more stable and penetrating. Hyaluronic acid is a must, niacinimide good, PEG-23 Glyceryl Distearate looks like an excellent anti-inflammatory for red and irritated skin, vitamin B6 good. I donâ€™t get too worked up about white and green tea and aloe, but they are good ingredients in general. I think this is the most effectively formulated vitamin C serum Iâ€™ve tested so far, and should be excellent for your skin in the long term. Thumbs up on this one.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

column6: Henna Maiden Hair & Eyebrow Color: 100% Natural & Chemical Free
column14: I ordered one pack of this to dye my long hair (not quite waist length but past the bust). I must have not read the description properly but one packet would not have been enough. According to the directions I was supposed to use about 2 - 2.5 packets of henna... but I managed with just one anyway! My hair had some blonde highlights so I focused more on those areas, but all my hair was coated with product. Instructions said to completely saturate, and I know I wasn't very saturated but nevertheless, I loved the result! The areas of my hair which were blonde aren't a dark dark brown, but they are brown. Think chocolate brown. I would advise ordering enough for your needs and mixing according to other reviewers' instructions (more watery consistency, add vinegar, leave on for hours etc) to get the best results. If you don't mix essential oil to mask the plant smell, your hair will smell strongly of henna. So either add fragrance or use a highly scented shampoo and conditioner. I also find that henna can be a bit drying, so a deep conditioner is recommended after. Good luck!

column6: Remington PR1285A R8 Wet & Dry Rotary Shaver, Men's Electric Razor, Electric Shaver, Blue
column13: A good shave for the gentle person.
column14:
This is a lightweight shaver made of a not so strong plastic. It has a rubber like material down two sides of the contoured handle that helps with gripping and has the right curve to fit your hand nicely. It gives by far the closest shave I have had in a while. However when shaving it feels and sounds like the shaver head section is going to come off so that part may break on down the line. Remington suggests their â€œRemington FaceSaverâ€ preshave powder to help it glide across your face. Others may find a preshave powder helpful but I am not one to buy that sort of thing. I found I could just use the shaver in a gentler fashion and still get a good shave.
It comes with a sleek stand that you can set it upright in and place it on your bathroom counter when your are not using it. You can charge it when it is in or out of the stand. Also provided are a cover for the heads and a very small brush to clean the head section.
Sometimes, when I am in a hurry, I like knowing I can shave in the shower in order to save a few minutes. This shaver lets you shave in or or out of the shower. Of course shaving in the shower does require having some shaving gel on hand but the extra expense would be worth the time saved when you are busy.
To clean the shaver you pop open the shaver head section, use the brush to clean the debris out from the head section and rinse it with water. If you are not careful the head section could be broken off since the plastic is so thin. You are not rinsing the whole shaver, just the head section. You do have to leave the head section open to dry but you can still store it in the stand. Once a week though you need to take out the heads and clean them thoroughly.
The trimmer woks just as well as any other brand of shaver and it seems to be made of a little stronger plastic than head section so there should be no problem with it breaking off unless you are forceful.
Remington did well to use a Lithium battery in this shaver. For a 90 minute charge you can shave for 60 minutes. The shaver can only be used with out the cord so there is no shaving while you charge it. So far I have found it to last me over a week and a half. One thing I like about this shaver is the 5 minute quick charge. If the battery runs low or you forget to charge it the day before you can charge it for 5 minutes and have enough power for one shave. Another cool thing is that the shaver can be used worldwide as it automatically adapts to the voltage in an outlet ranging from 100v to 2240v.
There is a limited two-year warranty but it only covers the shaver if it has a problem due to material and workmanship. Basically if it came faulty from the manufacturer. So if the lightweight plastic breaks anywhere like where the shaver head section hinges then the user is at fault.
I do like the performance guarantee Remington offers. Like other brands, if you are not satisfied within 30 days of your purchase, you can return it for a refund.
Overall this shaver offers a nice shave at a reasonable price. I like the versatility of being able to shave in or or out of the shower and in other countries I may travel to. So I do recommend it with one reservation. You will need use caution while shaving and cleaning it so the plastic parts do not break.a 90 minute charge you can shave for 60 minutes. column13: Removes plaque, reduces gingivitis, and whitens!
column14: At first I was hesitant to try a 2-step system for a toothpaste. However, considering it takes only 2 minutes total, I quickly got over my hesitancy. The step 1 fluoride is exactly what I need - removes plaque and reduces gingivitis. The step 2 hydrogen peroxide gel is great for removing surface stains. If you are a coffee and wine-drinker like I, you will benefit from and appreciate this toothpaste combo. I tend to be sensitive to whitening toothpastes, and my teeth didn't tingle when using this step. I gave it 4 rather than 5 stars because I think the mint flavor could be a bit stronger. I did receive this toothpaste free courtesy of Crest but all opinions are my own.

column6: MY Konjac Sponge All Natural Korean Facial Sponge with Activated Bamboo Charcoa
column13: no more excuses for going to bed with a dirty face!
column14:
If you've never used a konjac sponge, you need to know that they are THE BOMB. It blows my mind that something that is basically a perfectly shaped piece of vegetable root could be the best face cleanser ever. You will be amazed at how smooth, bright and exfoliated your skin is using these and after about a week of regular use your pores will become absolutely tiny. No special sauce needed, just this sponge and some water. If you still want to use cleanser with it, you just need a drop as the sponge will make it foam up like nobody's business.

You have NO EXCUSE now not to wash your face before bed because this is about as low maintenance as it gets. Get it wet. Rub it on your face. Go to bed. Boom. Done. It even gets off makeup and it's naturally ph balanced to keep your skin gorgeous without needing toner. Plus, it doesn't dry out your skin like so many cleanser can. The charcoal in it does extra pore cleansing and tightening and is ideal for blemish prone skin.

On top of everything, I LOVE the size of this one- I've gotten these in so many sizes and shapes, but this is easily the largest sized one I've gotten, making it easy to hold. I'm impressed that they have so many varieties available as well, I've only ever tried the white ones and the charcoal ones- I'd be interested to see the difference.

I may have gotten this for review purposes, but trust me, this is a REAL TWO THUMBS UP!

column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column14:
Crest products are my favorite for tooth brushing, and mouth washing. That being said, I was disappointed with the claims of this product. I expected at least a minimal change in the color of my teeth, alas, there was no visible change.
This product has 2 steps, the first is for prepping your teeth by cleaning them, like a regular toothpaste. The second step is for polishing and whitening. While the first step does its job and I feel my mouth is very fresh and clean, the second step has been a waste is my time over the last 4 weeks that I've used the product.
I did not change my daily habits such as drink or food intake as I feel that would falsify any claims for whitening if I suddenly stopped drinking coffee, tea, soda, juice. I wanted an unbiased opinion.
Now, I am grateful for BuzzAgent and Crest for providing this product free of charge as I would be extremely disappointed to pay $24.95 for basic toothpaste.

column6: Burt's Bees Body Wash, 12 Fluid Ounces
column13: Heavily watered down...may want to reconsider if you expect the quality of yesteryear (the 90's tee hee)...
column14:
You know, I remember when Burt's Bees products first came on the market in the 90's and everyone loved it, everyone had tried at least 1 of their items... such good good quality. My fave was the cuticle cream & toothpaste, always pricey but you just needed a teeny tiny bit to be effective. Th Body was is fragrant & did the job, of cleansing really well, the scent does not last on your skin, I wish it did. When I was searching for a more antibacterial body wash, I thought I would be getting a quality product that will surely last me a long time. Not so, I needed to transfer some product out of the bottle into a pump dispenser and when it easily poured into the second container I knew this was a heavily watered down product and I sighed...then I did a little research and saw that Clorox now owns this company AND Burt really got the short end of the stick on his business dealings!! RIP.
So I will NOT be buying this again as it is heavily watered down. There is a competitive brand that is pure product so I will switch to that.

column6: Sudocrem Antiseptic Cream 125g
column14: It's taken me quite a while to write a review but when I purchased another jar today, decided that it was about time, since my first purchase was back in 2011! This cream has helped me to deal with angular cheilitis. Five years ago I was having terrible trouble with trying to get rid of sores at the sides of my mouth that were not only painful but very unpleasant to look at. Tried many different 'cures' and nothing helped. Finally I stumbled across a forum where someone recommended Sudocrem and I figured since I'd tried so many other treatments, might as well try another. Even though I didn't think it would do any good, I was desperate. Within a few days the sores were gone and within a week I couldn't believe that it was completely gone! For a few months I was very diligent about continuing to apply during the day and before bed but eventually I found there was no need. Every once in a while I can feel the tell tale symptoms and I immediately grab the Sudocrem and it prevents the cheilitis from getting out of control. Since I only need to use small amounts, the 125g jar expired before I was able to use all of it, so getting four years usage out of one jar is an amazing bargain. :D FYI, be sure to order the 'Prime Member' jar if you're getting the 125g, even if you're not a Prime member because otherwise you'll have to wait a few weeks to a month for delivery!

column13: A Reasonable Toothpaste for Reasonable People
column14:
I'm a engineer with a Spock brain, so frankly I never really paid any attention to fragile little flowers with hyperbolic claims that they need to avoid SLS and fluoride like the plague. (Because c'mon....let's hear it for natural selection.) That being said, I grudgingly admit that I have fewer perioral dermatitis issues when I use fluoride-free toothpaste. Correlation != Causation....but hey, I'll take any advantage I can get on this.

I hadn't tried the Kiss My Face brand before, so wasn't sure what to expect. As it turns out, this gel worked fine. It's a nice plastic tube: easy to squeeze. I have no idea in what universe the flavor could possibly be considered "Orange Mint," but whatever....there isn't a ton of flavor, but its completely inoffensive. It's better than getting stuck with a strong flavor that you hate, right? Just think--now that I don't waste so much time standing around marveling over an abundance of flavor, I can shave literally seconds off my toothbrushing process, and get back out in the real world that much quicker to solve significant engineering problems.

column6: Tigi Bed Head Colour Combat Dumb Blonde Shampoo 8.45 oz.
column13: If you're a Smart Blonde you should use Dumb Blonde!
column14:
I am a natural blonde who stared to go gray at a young age (thanks, Dad!) So in my 20s I decided I wanted to live life as a redhead for a while. 10+ years later, I started with blonde highlights, then decided to try dying it my natural color again. I had shampoo specifically for red dyed hair and needed some for blonde so it wouldn't fade or look ashy before I was ready to dye it again.

So far I am really enjoying this shampoo! It smells clean and fresh, and lathers really well - my hair is a few inches past my shoulder, and normally I need to use about a 50 cent piece-sized amount of shampoo to feel clean. With this one, I use about a quarter-sized amount and it lathers all of my hair and I don't feel like I need to repeat it.

I've only used it for about two weeks on freshly dyed hair and so far the color is still really good. It also seems to keep my hair clean longer - I can go 2-3 days with my hair looking and smelling freshly washed and clean. My hair color tends to fade around the 4-6 week mark, so I will post an update there. But I love this shampoo, and my mom is even using it now for her blonde hair.

One point I should make - the description of the product does not include what's on the front of the label. You can see it by zooming in on the photo (which I didn't do), so I didn't realize that it specifies it's for "highlighted or bleached blonde". Though I do have light blonde highlights, my base color is a darker, honey blonde, so I might have thought twice before buying this particular brand. However, I am hopeful that it will keep both shades of blonde bright and vibrant! I purchased this product at a discount in exchange for an honest, unbiased review.

column13: Works great on oily lids, but not fingernail friendly
column14: I have long fingernails so that makes it difficult to apply with fingertips the way I have with other eye shadow primers that come in tube form, especially since the compact this product comes in is very tiny.  However, good things do come in small packages!  Using a small lipstick application brush, a little tiny bit of this stuff goes a long way.  You'll want to apply a very thin layer and let it try a few minutes to set while you do your foundation, blush, etc.  If you don't put in on too thick and give it a few minutes to set, you are guaranteed to have bright shadow that lasts all day without creasing.  I have VERY oily skin and eyelids and this really works... much better than L'Oreal's Magic Decrease primer, which is the last one I tried (hated it) and just as well as some more expensive ones I've tried in the past.  I'd have given this 5 stars if I didn't have to use a small brush to apply it, but despite the slightly less convenient application process, I would buy this again because it does work well.

column6: Dove Men+Care Dry Spray Antiperspirant
column14:
First, I want to note that I sweat a lot and I don't really have any skin sensitivities. About a year and a half ago I noticed that the antiperspirants I was using started giving me severe irritation. I was scratching my armpits non stop and when you're on a date, it's definitely not something that'll help you get a second one.

The last 6 months i've tried a lot of different brands spending at least 6 bucks on each one. I'm not going to name all of them but they all failed for me. I was about to give up when my friend had mentioned he was having the same problem and mentioned Dove Men+Care. I looked on amazon and saw that it was under 5 bucks so I figured why not? I've been using the spray for a week and half now and NO irritation AT ALL! In fact, I skipped the weekend and not much sweat either.

All in all, i'm enjoying it for now. I'll see how it goes in a month.

Side note - this uses Aluminum Chlorohydrate which is different from the other brands I've used. I think the others use Aluminum Zirconium Tetrachlorohydrex. I don't know if that's what caused the irritation I had but it seems to be the only ingredient that's changed. Hope this helps!

column7: I signed on to review the Genuine Crystal Nail File by Malva Belle in exchange for an honest and unbiased review. While every woman likes new Nail Swag, I knew the best, most critical customer would be My Mother ;). I handed her this Nail File, asked her to do her Nail Filing Business a few times and to report back to me on her Likes and Dislikes. A few days later My Mother called me with her assignment fulfilled. I cannot do this product justice any other way than to offer this direct quote from My Mother- "I threw away every other Nail File in my house (Daughter) and I want a half dozen more of THESE." I wish I could convey what receiving such a well regarded opinion from *My Mother* really means and how hard it is to get her approval :). She reports that the Genuine Crystal Nail File by Malva Belle is, First Of All, beautifully crafted, solid, durable and "pretty." She appreciates that it comes with a case for storage. She also reports that this file did not break, chip, or crack her nails, nor did it cause injury at the cuticle line. If you are in need of a Nail File and want one of the best available, Mandy's Mother gives this Genuine Crystal Nail File by Malva Belle her Seal of Approval. Now if *I* could just get her Seal of Approval... ;).

column6: Carapex After Bath Lotion with Aloe and Shea Butter
column13: If you have dry skin you need to try this lotion
column14:
I have very dry skin and I often go from one lotion to another because either its not helping my skin, or its too oily. The Carapex After Bath Lotion. This lotion is not the heavy or greasy like the other lotion's I've used. This lotion has a very creamy and has a non-greasy texture. The ingredients are a blend of shea butter, aloe vera, soybean oil, vitamin E and Japanese green tea extract.
The first time I used it I noticed how easy the lotion came out and thought that it would not work as well as the description stated. However, I was extremely surprised at how easy it spread on my skin, the lotion absorbed very quickly, and left my skin feeling moisturized without the greasiness some of the lotion has. There are no artificial fragrance or harsh chemicals, so there is no overpowering smell, so what you're getting is just that, a moisturizer for your skin. This product has left my skin feeling better than ever and I use this lotion every day. I am definitely a very satisfied customer!!
*I received this product free in exchange for an honest and unbiased review

column6: Dove Men+Care Hair Styling, Sculpting Paste 1.75 oz
column13: Solid hair styling product that keeps hair looking great but doesn't look like grease
column14:
What we have here is a pretty solid product, and I don't just mean how well it holds my hair.

What you'll find inside the lovely grey container is a white paste that has the consistency of creamy putty. It's not like a typical gel product that feels gooey and sticky - it's a paste that when rubbed in your hands will make it look like you've just dipped them into white paint. But don't fear, it goes on without leaving any trace of colour in your hair or on your hands.

Emulsification of the product is nice - it does NOT clump like a gel product does, which means once you start working it through your hair you aren't going to walk away with bits of clumped together hair that are obviously adhered with gel. This isn't Something About Mary.

The hold is effect all day long - I use this right out of the shower on damp hair which I've found gives the best results. If your hair is too dry, just moisten your hands before applying the paste and you'll get the same result. It holds without looking greasy. No one wants that slick back look these days (well, if you do, try a different product) and this one doesn't disappoint. I also found that it doesn't leave my hair "crunchy" like many maximum hold gels do. It's just a nice quality firm hold.

This product is one that I'm planning to keep in my bathroom cabinet and use regularly. A solid 5 stars for product consistency and texture, quality, and ease of use.

column6: Nerd Skincare Miraculous Brightening Facial Mask
column14:
I really like this mask. I don't do spa's, mani's and pedi's, I prefer to do my own thing at home, much more relaxing to me. I couldn't tell the ingredients before I received this so I was taking a chance, but it was all good. The ingredients are exactly as follows.

Water, Glycerin, 1,3-Propanediol, 1,2-Pentylene Glycol, Macadamia Nut Seed oil, Squalane, Behenyl Alcohol, Shea Butter, ( Butyrospernum Parkii)Fruit, Palmitoyl Tripeptide-5 and Glycerin, Ceramide 3, L-Arginie, Hyaluronic Acid, Vitamin E, Allatoin, Xanthan Gum, Dipotassium Glycyrrhznate, (Licorice Root Extract), Cholesteryl Hydroxysterate, Glycosphingolipids and Phospholipids and Cholesterol (Lecithin), Ferulic Acid Ester and Cycloartenol and 24-Methyl Cycloartenol Phytosterol and beta-Sitosterol (Rice barn Oil Extract(< Algae Extract and Pullulan and Water and Phenoxyethanol and Sodium Benzoate and Potassium Sorbate (Nannochloropsis Oculata Extract) I know things not spelled right in there, but hey I tried. Anyway you can see all ingredients and their are some really good ones.

I used this on a girly night, had a hot tub soak, came out, threw this on for probably 45 minutes and just relaxed. Removed the mask, rubbed the last of what was left on skin on and it absorbed really well. It took a few minutes, maybe 5 or so for it to all absorb in, but it is a treatment you don't do that often also. I didn't want to waste anything left on the mask since it is a one time use product so I wiped it all over neck, chest, and anywhere I hit before I threw the mask away.

It left my skin very very moisturized, smooth, very light refreshing smell is all, nothing strong. No irritation just soothing relaxation. It did seem to tighten and firm a bit and just made skin glow. I couldn't justify using them very often due to price for a one time use product, but for a splurge now and then, yes you do need to try one of these, my skin felt fabulous afterwards.

column14: I used this to restore an old FEG Browning pistol.I took off all the bluing and completely dismantled every piece I polished and degreased it as best I could. Then I began applying the Oxpho creme after heating up the metal with a heat gun. It took me around  four hours and several coats to complete the whole pistol.I let all the parts sit in oil overnight and most of the next day. Then I assembled the pistol and the results were nothing short of amazing. It looks like a new gun almost and the creep and crunchiness is almost non existent on the trigger pull. I was able to seal out most of the pitting and marks with the Oxpho.I have since shot a few hundred rounds through the gun and the bluing is holding up nicely through several cleanings.Lots of prep work and application but the results are well worth it. Highly recommend this.

It is concentrated and effective while remaining light and non-sticky.  You can also use it as a neutral "carrier" oil for your strong essential oils.  The price was affordable and the product arrived packaged well, wrapped in plastic and inside a box to keep from breaking.  I am very happy with my purchase and will be buying this again on a regular basis.

column6: DIGIWAVES ** NEW RELEASE HOLSTER For 5.5\ (PERFECT FIT FOR iPHONE 6 PLUS) ** High Quality PU Leather (Black) iPhone 6 Plus 5.5\" Vertical Executive PU Leather Pouch Cover Case Holster Swivel Belt Clips With Magnetic Closure For Apple iPhone 6 Plus 5.5\" inch"
column13: Perfect for iPhone 6 and Speck Grip case
column14: UPDATE SEP 2015: After about 5 months, the clip broke at the hinge pins and holster is unusable.  Unfortunately, this is the only VERTICAL holster I can find that has my requirement for the J hook for the belt clip, and that can fit the iPhone 6 with the Speck Grip Case, which is necessary for my butter fingers... I would order another, but needed to go on travel, so I was forced to buy a Mophie Hip Holster for iPhone 6 Plus and Juice pack at Best Buy out of necessity. I probably will buy another of these after the Mophie breaks.  The Mophie is heavier and bigger all around, and fits the Grip Case covered iPhone easily.  ORIGINAL REVIEW APR 2015: Fits the bill for me and my iPhone 6 Plus with Speck CandyShell Grip Case.  Fit was tight for a few days, now it is just perfect. FWIW, this case will be loose with just a bare phone.  Someone else makes a real leather version of this case, with a smaller flap, allowing headphone connections.  That leather case is too tight for a Speck Grip Case, and seems to be made for the bare phone only, or a really, really slim case, maybe like the Incipio.  So go in with your eyes open on fit.  The rotating clip with the J shape hook is the set up for belt use.  This was the key feature for me.  Other clips just don't do it.  The J shaped hook is critical for security and this big phone.  I have used this on dress pants every day with a belt, as well as jeans and shorts, also with a belt.  Very secure.  The only issue with this case, since it is Polyurethane (PU) is that it does not wear as well as leather.  I think I will need to get a new one in a year because the corners get dinged up.  There is no functional degradation, just cosmetic, the underlying gray color starts to show when the the black surface color gets dinged/cracked.  Again the material is fine, it is just the color layer.  Quick solution is Sharpie permanent ink pen to touch it up

column6: Volumizing Powder
column13: I really like this product.  Five stars!
column14: This powder works great!  I sprinkle just a little on my roots in 1 inch partings down to my ears and rub it in well.  It provides nice volume and works better for me than powdery dry shampoo.  For the back of my head, I shake some on my fingers and then rub it in well, right into the roots.  The volume lasts most of the day but it's easy to revive with my fingertips and a few upside down shakes of my head.  I bought this product at Sally's when there was a buy 1 get 1 sale because I was curious about it and with the sale, I figured I had nothing to lose. The regular price is about $6.  It works much better than I'd hoped.  Once on the scalp, the powder turns clear so there's no white residue.  I'm sure it works as well as more expensive products that are triple the price (after all, how different can they be?) like Bumble and Bumble Pret a Powder. It also doesn't make my hair oily or dry it out.  I was using Living Proof Amp, which is a cream, but this works much better for me.  It also isn't sticky or stiff like a root spray.  I've found it works best on second day hair, however.  All and all, I really like this product.  It's nice to be pleasantly surprised by something new.  And although the container is small, you really need very little to do the job, so it will last quite a while.  I'm a fan of other BTZ products, namely Smooth Criminal Primer, the matte clay putty and the dry shampoo, so I'm glad the brand lived up to my standards with yet another excellent product.  I definitely recommend this volumizing powder.  It works like a charm for me.

column14: I really love this product. My problem with that brand was that it seemed to run out super quickly, & it was hard to get the proper amount on the cushion after the first few uses. column13: Decent frizz prevention, but I have to mix it with other products for it to work best
column14:
I have to mix this with a mousse, glossing cream or styling lotion, a few drops of this in with the other product, for it to work well without weighing down my hair. It does work, and it works well. I just visited Washington DC in the middle of the worst heat and humidity they've seen there in a long time, and I did not have frizz, too much volume, or fly-aways even once during my stay. But, I don't like having to mix it with something else to avoid the greasy, matted down look I get when using too much of it alone or for two days in a row. It should work alone, all by itself.

As long as I mix it into the other product well before applying to my dry hair, it is a great product. It's not a bad price, nor does it smell funny or dry out my hair. But, if you have very thin or fine hair, I can see where it would weigh it down, make it look greasy or dry it out, or all three, over time.

column6: Fractionated Coconut Oil - Pure USA Expeller Cold Pressed & Hexane Free - Best Therapeutic Grade Carrier Oil for Essential Oils Aromatherapy & Massage - Food Grade MCT - Lg 16oz - 12 Ellie's Recipes
column13: Great for Hair and Skin, But a Tad Greasy After Use
column14:
Dry, cracked skin not only looks horrible, it can hurt, too. The bodyâ€™s largest organ needs TLC from time-to-time, especially as it combats the daily onslaught of soaps, perfumes, laundry detergents and softeners, the atmosphere, and anything else that is within its daily environment. Whether due to sunburn, the dry heat from a furnace, chemical dry-out, or the myriad other reasons why skin can become rough, flaky, and torn, the main issue is applying a moisturizer that will rejuvenate the flesh. That is where Ellieâ€™s Fractionated Coconut Oil joins the fray, as a combatant against the dry skin battle.

Packaging/Texture

Ellieâ€™s Fractionated Coconut Oil comes in a plastic bottle with a lever cap; the packaging includes a separate pump if you wish to swap it out with the standard cap. The oil itself is clear with a thin viscosity, almost watery in texture. I opted to use the pump, which dispensed a fairly good amount of oil on each push. In fact, one pump was usually enough to handle both legs and arms without needing a refill. Finally, there is no odor for this product, which is almost disappointing in a way, as coconut has such a pleasant smell. On the upside, however, you will not have to worry about insects attracted to you because of the scent (which can happen with perfumed soaps and beauty products). It is rather nice not having to shoo bees away due to my choice of moisturizer.

But, Does It Work?

Over the course of two weeks, I utilized Ellieâ€™s Fractionated Coconut Oil for two things, 1) moisturizing my skin, and 2) adding moisture to my hair before washing it in the shower. After two weeks, I can comment as follows:

1) The oil does work very well in restoring my dried skin. I recently had a sunburn, and the oil went a long way toward soothing my baked flesh. That being said, there is a slight greasy feel that tends to remain on your hands after use, and I had to wash with soap to remove it if I accidentally used too much product.

2) My hair absolutely loves the Fractionated Coconut Oil, which also acted as a conditioner and helped prevent tangles. My hair is down past my shoulder blades, which means lots of tangles from going about my day. This is exacerbated when it is hot outside due to frizziness and sweat. During each shower I would massage the oil into my hair and then comb it through; I found that tangles separated easier and I had a lot less breakage as opposed to just using water. In addition, my hair had a lovely sheen to it.

All of this being said, the other claims by the manufacturer are accurate, thus far. I cannot really comment upon the ability of this product to not go rancid, as I have only had it in my possession for a little over three weeks. That being said, Ellieâ€™s Fractionated Coconut Oil is odorless, clear, and does moisturize both your skin and hair. As to the greasiness claim, I found it to be otherwise. There is definitely a thin sheen that can be left behind, especially if you use a lot of product. Fortunately, it did not leave grease spots on my clothing.

Final Say

If you would like an economical product that does moisturize your skin, is economical, has no smell, and works as well as or even better than big-name, commercial oils, then Ellieâ€™s Fractionated Coconut Oil is a great option. It is very utilitarian in terms of use on both the skin and in your hair, and because it doesnâ€™t have an odor, you will not have to worry about it clashing with your soaps, perfumes, or other beauty products. At the end of the day, Ellieâ€™s will moisturize your skin and keep your hair shiny and soft. That being said, the slight greasiness is just irritating enough for me to remove one star from this product. It wonâ€™t get onto your clothing, but it is annoying when you need to put your contacts in or do anything else that needs dry hands. Final say: 4 stars of 5!

column6: Aztec Secret Indian Healing Clay 1 LB (Pack of 2)
column13: but it really does leave your skin feeling amazing. I suggest mixing the clay with apple cider ...
column14:
Wow. You can really feel this stuff getting the blood moving in your face. Almost to the point to when it dries, it hurts, but it really does leave your skin feeling amazing.

I suggest mixing the clay with apple cider vinegar in a plastic sandwich baggie to eliminate crazy mess. Apply an nice past-like consistancy to your face and let it dry. LET IT DRY. It's going to itch. It's going to be uncomfortable. It's going to pulsate. Just suck it up, and let it dry.

Then, use WARM WATER to remove the mask. Don't try and peel anything off (unless you want to actually lose layers and layers of skin).

Also, be careful of sensitive drains. This stuff can clog easily!!

Overall, I really love the way this makes my skin look/feel.

column6: Christian Dior Voluptuous Care Lipcolor, # 651 Tourbillion Pink, 0.12 Ounce
column13: There's a reason this lipstick is being sold for less than retail price
column14: There's a reason this lipstick is being sold for less than retail price. The lipstick itself is unscathed and looks brand new. It's easy to apply and glides weightlessly on your lips. It also has the dior signature rose scent that I love. The packaging of the lipstick, however, leaves much to be desired. I assumed based on previous purchases with this seller that the lipstick wouldn't come in a box and that was true. I expected the lipstick container to be fine though and that isn't the case. There are numerous scratches all over it and it seems that there are food crumbs stuck between the lines of the Dior logo and the lines along the side of the packaging. The packaging simply makes it look like a used lipstick.  The lipstick is amazing, but I was expecting for the packaging to be fine as well, since that's why I spent so much on the lipstick. I did get it at a slight discount in exchange for a review, so I won't be returning it, but for future buyers be aware that there really is a reason this lipstick is being sold at less than retail. If you want it just for the color, which is a nice pinky coral nude that looks good on my medium skin tone, than I would say go for it. If you want it for the appeal of having a Dior lipstick though, I'd advise spending a bit more and knowing you'll get an unscathed product.

It came in a maroon velour pouch along with an extremely soft DermaCloth that is actually a vary powerful exfoliator that i use on my face. I have included pictures for reference.

In the short time I've been using the Striafade I have not noticed a single new stretch mark and none are any worse, but I haven't noticed any fading yet, which might be because my belly is still growing and that I have not been using it for long. What I have noticed is immediate relief from the pain, tingling and itching as soon as I apply the cream.Â  It's soothing and feels absolutely amazing!! I'm sensitive to strong smells, but the scent of Striafade is light, pleasant, non-medicinal and not overwhelming. I use it twice a day on problematic areas. Disclaimer: I received this product at a discounted rate in exchange for my unbiased review. Regardless, I'm very happy with my purchase and would happily purchase again. column6: Acne Treatment Supplement: Top Rated Acne Pills for Women, Men and Teens
column14:
All I can say is that I've had acne all my life, from a teenager to an adult. There are times that it would take a break, due to topical prescriptions. However it would last for a short while, and to make matters worse, I would have to stay out of the sun. I get blackheads, white heads and cystic acne. The whole nine yards. At least 2 weeks in each month it would get worse and for whatever reason since this year, not a day would pass and I wouldn't have at least 2 bumps, not pimples, as they were red and ugly, on my face. I had someone ask me once if I had chicken pox, as the acne left blemishes on my skin. I just want you to get an idea as to what I had to deal with. I was sick and tired of it.

Anyhow, I have been using this for less than a mth and I am pleased. It has improved 90% and I'll take that any day. I hope that it continues to work...fingers crossed tightly.

This is a life saver for someone who hates shaving! I apologize for the long review beforehand, but I promise you, the details will help you make an informed purchase!

------------------------------------------ BACKGROUND------------------------------------------------------
I'm used to getting my legs, arms, arm pits etc. waxed professionally once a month, back when I was in India. When I moved to the US, I realized how super expensive it is to get it done here, especially on a student budget! I tried waxing at home but there were always difficult patches which would turn sore and red because I couldn't hold the skin taut. Hence, like every one else, I started shaving!

The problem was that I had never shaved before. Maybe once or twice in high school but that too when my mother was supervising me. I hated it. I hated spending extra time in the shower. I hated that it had to be done more often. I hated the cuts and razor burns. I tried shaving my arms once and it was a disaster. That's when I thought that I should probably look up electric shavers, and I found this one!

------------------------------------------ REVIEW------------------------------------------------------
Close shave:
I think the main issue most people face with electric shavers is getting a close shave. If done right, this can give a close shave. hold the shaver perpendicular to the surface, so that the foil and both side of the trimmer are touching your skin. The trick is to go back and forth several times over the same area. There is a little bit of a spring action, so that you can, very gently, press it down on your skin, giving a closer shave. If you have longer hair, apply some talcum powder/baby powder and run a dry towel across the area in the direction opposite to the hair growth to lift the hair up. If you have really long thick hair (or if you are a guy shaving his legs), use the pop up trimmer to trim first.

Battery life: Even though it said that it needs to be charged for 12 hours before the first use and between every use, I used it right out of the box to test it out on a small patch. It shaved well. I decided to wait 24 hours just to make sure I'm not getting any reaction, and charged it in the mean time. The blades did spin faster. So I believe it's a good idea to charge it between shaves. The manual says that 12 hours of charging gives about 20 minutes of shave, which sounds ridiculous at first. However, it took me, the amateur shaving person, 10 to 12 minutes to shave both legs, both arms and underarms. I think 20 minutes is more than enough.

Wet shaving: Since I hated shaving, I don't think this is a feature I want to try. The manual says I can use this with some shaving cream, and I lot of reviews say that your skin needs to be soaking wet to shave. If I ever do try it, I will update this. I think it's unnecessary to wet shave when I'm getting very good results shaving it dry, however, I feel it's a good feature to have in case that's your only option, for example, if your sharing a hotel room with friends and don't have the privacy.

Regrowth: Surprisingly, the regrowth was not as blunt as normal shaving, which is what gave me the confidence to shave my arms! You do have to let it grow a little longer than usual to shave well.

Cleaning: It is extremely easy to clean. It comes with a dual ended brush to brush of hair during the shave. After I am done shaving, I pop the head off and rinse both, the head and the blades inside in water. It's a good idea to press your finger onto the faucet so that it gives out a sharp forceful stream. I first rinse the head, then put a some hand soap in some water in a cup, and leave the head in that to soak while I clean the blades inside. I first rinse the blades in the sharp stream, then I dunk the blade only in the cup full of soap water and swish it around, and then rinse both the head and the blades. I use a q tipto get into the corners of the plastic inside. To dry off, I sort of shake both the parts vigorously so that the water falls out, put the top back on to protect the blade, and leave it to air dry for a few hours. Once I know it's fully dry, I put it for charging.

Ergonomics: For dry shaving and washing, it's very easy to hold. It fits well in my small hands and doesn't slip out of my grip. I don't know if the surface will become slippery if you're shaving wet with shaving cream. The placement of the buttons is good so that you can start and stop the shaver or open and close the pop trimmer with the thumb of the hand you're holding it with. I believe the design is good for both, right handed and left handed people. The side of the the blade is big enough for quick shaves, and small enough to get around difficult areas.

Portability: If you have the right case to carry it in, it's easily portable. The case that comes with it is too small to fit both the shaver and the charger. This is my only complaint. Other than that, it's not too bulky and heavy to travel with.

Longevity: Only time will tell. I have had it only for a few weeks and used it 3-4 times, and so far it's great. The blade and the foil are replaceable, so that's a good think. Other than that, if you read the manual, follow the instructions, keep it clean and charge it timely, you're doing everything on your side to maintain the product. If anything goes wrong or I face any issues, I will come back and update this.

Overall, I think it's a good product, very affordable (I bought it for 14.99, the original price is 29.99, which is still great if it lasts for more than a year), it does the job well without nicks and cuts, and it is FAST!

If you found this review helpful, give it a thumbs up! If you have any questions, please comment below and I will try to answer them to the best of my knowledge. column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Value Pack - Brilliance Toothpaste 4.1 oz & Polishing Treatment 3 oz Mesmerizing Mint
column13: I love the fresh from the dentist feel!
column14:
Let me start off by saying that I was given this product to use/try, from Crest, in exchange for an honest review. I have always been super self-conscious about my teeth. My dentist says that they have good color, but I'm a soda drinker, and I know that they could be whiter. I don't usually try home whitening products, but I had heard nothing but good stuff about this set, so I had to try it. When my box got here, I was nervous to try it, but also anxious at the same time. The first time I used it, I brushed my teeth with my regular toothpaste just before trying it, so I could have a more accurate before to compare with my after result. The first paste is gritty, like the kind they use to clean your teeth at the dentist's office. The taste leaves something to be desired, but this paste goes to work quickly. The grittiness is awesome at removing the stains on the teeth's surfaces. I used that one for a bit longer than a minute. The downside is that I have sensitive teeth, and this toothpaste kind of made them flare up, but it was not unbearable by any means. After that, I brushed with the second paste, without rinsing out my mouth in between the two pastes, as per the directions on the tubes. The second paste is clear, and tastes worse than the first one. The directions stated to brush with the this paste for 1 minute as well, and again, do not rinse after brushing. I'm sure it is because this paste is not only to polish the teeth, but that it also contains a leave on whitener. I then waited about 30 minutes before eating or drinking, like I would with a professional cleaning. I was shocked that I was able to see a visible difference the very first time I used it... even my kids noticed it on the second day. After just a week of using it (2a day), I am smiling a lot more, and I am not as self-conscious of my teeth. My teeth are whiter than they have been in quite some time, and that is a great feeling. I am going to continue to use this paste to see just how white they can get! I would have rated it 5 stars if it tasted better, and if it didn't irritate my sensitive teeth. So, if they could make a sensitive version, with a better taste, I would be all over it. If you are in the market for a teeth whitening system, or you have always wanted to try something, but you're skeptical.... this is just the one for you! Not only so you get to skip a trip to the dentist's office, but you will be saving quite a bit of money. Results are just about immediate, and you won't be disappointed... I know I'm not!!!
*Update* After using fro 10-15 days, my sensitive teeth are no longer flaring up at all. In addition to that, the taste has grown on me somewhat. Most of all, I still love the way that my teeth feel after using this!ey can get! I would have rated it 5 stars if it tasted better, and if it didn't irritate my sensitive teeth. column6: Thymes Kimono Rose Cologne Rollerball
column14:
UPDATE (8/11/15): The customer service was outstanding. The gentleman I was communicating with through e-mail was polite, helpful and quick. He resolved this issue in no time. I'm upgrading this review to four stars as promised.

Last thing: I just wanted to say this is a wonderful perfume (the smell is incredible!); the product is also made in the U.S.A. (I think)... I smelled it a few times at Central Market and was impressed each time - if you're a Thymes fan, definitely give it a shot, you won't regret it. I would give it five stars if not for the issue I had (dried out perfume). However, I'd say this is always a risk when buying online. It isn't anyone's fault. It's just something that happens. Perfumes are being stored at warehouses in warm/cold temperatures all the time, so it will happen once in a while. A customer service representative I talked to mentioned that they would conduct a quality inspection as a result of this incident to ensure this won't happen again.

---ORIGINAL REVIEW---
My perfume arrived empty. There wasn't a single drop of perfume in the bottle. I wrote to the customer service and asked for a refund (even though this item is not eligible for a refund but in this case I think it's well deserved). I will upgrade this review to 4 stars when/if I get a refund, but at this point I'm giving one star to this product.

I feel like the lavender does help, but if you don't like the smell of lavender it can be overwhelming. You can both heat and cool it. I've only tried putting it in the freezer so far. column6: Braun 3 Series 340S Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor, Wet & Dry
column14:
I got this as I wanted a shaver for touch ups and daily upkeep. I had tried the ones with the round blades and found them to be lacking. So I figured for the price I would try this one with the foils esp since I read some great reviews on it.

First, the best pro is it's price. For a good daily shaver, this is great price. The head comes off easily and can be cleaned with ease. It is also water resistant so it can be used in the shower or with a shaving gel. I found it to give a fairly close shave and not irritate the skin. It comes with a nice charging stand, sample size oil for the blades, a cover for the blades, and a brush for cleaning.

I've had some of the expensive self cleaning models in the past and tbh this does all they did for me. The one exception is I have to clean it, which is rather easily done imo. So if you don't mind the extra min spent on upkeep of it, then def go this route and save your money for much more fun things :)

column6: KINeSYS SPF30 Performance Sunscreen Spray, Mango Scent, 4oz
column14:
I have used this brand for years and absolutely love it. I started using it when triathlete friends of mine swore by it - it really stays on in the water and through rain or sweat. I've even not reapplied as often as I should and I rarely get sunburned. It smells good, there is no alcohol (to my knowledge) and it doesn't have that "hurt your lungs" alcohol smell that some sunscreen sprays. Heck, this even kept us from burning (or even looking tan, this coming from a redhead who burns easily) during Spring Training in Scottsdale.

As a travel spray, we purchased the 2 ounce size and just refill it from the 4 oz bottles. Plus I can take the smaller size out with me on long runs.

While it doesn't go on dry and takes a bit to dry, it doesn't take long. It doesn't stain, I really can't think of any downsides to it.

column6: Conair French Twist Perfect Up do Clip Set
column13: New directions on an old Twist!
column14:
Am 71 yrs old. Am growing hair out now. Want to do Fr. Twist again like I did when young woman. Intend to purchase a shaper like this soon, because I had one in past and used it with great results! It's very hard to find one nowadays so I am glad it's sold here.

Not sure if attached clip is good idea. Will try it but remove it if not easy or successful.

I think it would be very hard to follow directions as presented on website.

Here is what I used to do, will do in future, and which may be helpful to other customers: 1. Brush hair toward one side of head. 2. Affix shaper to scalp with long bobby pins inserted vertically, one at top and one up from bottom. 3. Brush hair toward other side. 4. Wrap hair around shaper, starting at bottom, in sections, securing as you go with large hairpins along the fold line. 5. At finish, at top of head, loop remaining hair around to form curl[s] and tuck ends into and under top of twist. Use whatever size hairpins works for your type hair to secure this section.

Easy and Beautiful!
