column6: Best Molding Creme for Strong Hold Matte Finish - No Shine Hair Product For Textured Modern Hairstyles - Lamel Styling Clay for All Hair Types 2.7 Ounce
column13: Great Matte Finish Look with a Strong Hold
column14:
This is a great hair clay similar to pomade texture. You use it in a similar fashion, only a small amount is needed, and it gives your hair a strong hold all-day. Dab a bit into the palm of your hand and work through hair using your fingers to shape and separate into pieces. I particularly like clay over pomade because of the matte finish look. This is a great product that Iâ€™ve received at a discount in exchange for an honest review, and one that I would highly recommend and would continue to buy.

Difference between Pomade and Clay:

Pomade
The Look: Classic and polished. Think Joseph Gordon Levitt or Leonardo DiCaprio. It's a timeless style that's great for the office.

What It Does: Gives hair a slick, high shine finish with a lot of hold. Pomades stay moldable all day so you can retouch periodically.

Clay
The Look: Sexy, undone hair that begs to be played with. Think James Franco or Robert Pattinson. Perfect for the weekend.

What It Does: Gives hair more volume and texture so it'll look thicker and give it separation. Putties and clays both have a matte finish.

column13: The Brush Lasts About A Year....

The bristles have been shedding ever since I bought the set. Sometimes there is a sizable clump of bristles that become detached from the handle when I shave.

I came online here at Amazon to find a good quality brush. As another reviewer suggested, buy a good quality brush separate from the bowl and soap. Unfortunately, for those of you who have not already purchased the set in order to get the bowl and soap you must buy the complete set. I have yet to find the soap and bowl sold separately. I have found just the soap for sale.

- The price it goes for is quite high (thankfully I received mine at a discounted price in exchange for my review)

column13: Purple Rain - Prince Would Be Proud Of You - He Might Even Use This, He Loves Purple So Much
column14:
I fell for it, the new advertising and the new color for Axe. I figured this would be something different. A lighter brighter less teenage boy trying to pick up chicks smell.

Nope. It is the same old Axe, still dedicated to the thought that women like strong smells. And that dudes will like strong smells and funky colors in the shower.

Yeah, this soap is purple. Not lavender purple - Prince purple, Royal Purple Oil purple. I have no idea why this is purple and not green or yellow. I get it why they wouldn't make it red. Yeah, that would be gross.

It still smells strong. Way strong. After a shower, well I'll admit, it does kind of smell fresh. But a guy shouldn't need that much fresh smell.

You're not a no GMO, organic, fragrance free guy. You don't mind using chemicals. This is your body wash, man.

By the way, that's a huge bottle. Go ahead and squeeze out a lot for the shower.

And the cap - you press the little Vee to open it up snap cap top style. And the bottle is tapered in the middle with grippers, so you won't drop your soap in the shower. You know, it isn't a good idea to drop your soap in the shower.

column13: I have to say that I love mud masks
column14:
I have to say that I love mud masks! Who doesnâ€™t? I now have several mud masks in my collection, some of them come from the Dead Sea.

In this post I am reviewing Treâ€™Yours Dead Sea mud mask. The beauty of any mud mask is that you can feel like you are having a spa day at home, for a sliver of the price. I also always lack the time to go to a proper spa as I take care of kids at home, and with a baby on my arms most of the day it is really hard to find time to go to a salon. So, I find ways to relax at home with mud masks consumer products!

I prefer Dead Sea masks to some other brands because I have heard so much about the healing properties of the Dead Sea, and Dead Sea salts and mud are some of the main attractions of tourists going to the Dead Sea region resorts to heal, use some preventative solutions to feel better. Preventative care is often overlooked in our busy life, but this is exactly what will bring relaxation and soothe you in your daily pursuits.

I am enjoying having access to Dead Sea products without having to take an expensive trip abroad. Castle Baths is the company that came up with this product of Dead Sea mud masks.

This mud mask container can last you a while. All you need to apply is a thin layer of mud on your skin. This mud is great as it has so many applications. You can use it on your face and body, as well as hair. I can write on and on about the health benefits of this product but the fact that this mud comes from the Dead Sea region speaks for itself â€“ you donâ€™t need to explain a whole lot more â€“ the health benefits are quite well-known as the mud from that area is full of essential minerals, and salts. This is a natural product and all you get is pure Dead Sea mud in a jar! There are no additives, purifiers, or chemicals!

Here is my grain of salt â€“ I find while the container is nicely sealed for freshness, is a very cute tin overall, the label for this mud is hard to read a bit. It is printed on light grey label paper, and the words that describe the product and application instructions on the container are printed in white ink, so it is really hard to read for me, as I have some eyesight problems. I wish the writing were a bit easier to read.

Overall, I am very happy with this product, and will be looking forward to using it in the next few weeks!

column6: [USA] SAPO Organic Bamboo Charcoal Soap Bar - Natural US Handmade - Helps with Acne, Psoriasis, Eczema - Has Coconut Oil, Oatmeal, Shea Butter - Leaving Your Face and Body Fresh and Clean
column14:
This Bamboo Charcoal soap is simply a great product to use for your face and skin! The soap came in simple packaging, which was nice and easy to open and use. This product is made in the USA and has been certified organic.
I wanted to try this product out because I heard that African Black Soap caused many people to break out or have irritated skin and I didn't want to risk that. This soap has no smell, so for people with sensitive skin - this should not irritate it! The complete ingredients of the soap are listed on the box and they are: Activated bamboo charcoal, olive oil, coconut oil, palm oil, sunflower oil, safflower oil, shea butter, sea salt, oatmeal powder, and grapefruit essential oil. This soap is really gentle and I know that ingredients like oatmeal help to soothe and smooth irritated skin.
I am using this as a face wash since it is the most sensitive part of my skin and it is working really well! There is no harsh smell and my skin is soft after washing, unlike how it is with other harsh soaps.
This product was provided to me at no to low cost. All thoughts are unbiased and of my own opinion.

column14: It's a very interesting cologne.I won't say it's as good as the dark green,soapy,and sharp nature of Quorum.But I will say that Krizia Uomo had no justifiable reason to be kept out of the limelight compared to the rest of the pine genre as this is a classy scent.At first spray it will remind you of Pino Silvestre in some contexts.Lemon,pine,carnation,a little sweetness in the mix...then it changes.This turns into a pleasant tobacco scent on dry down that's smoothly sweet with a little hint of floral.You don't really get pine at this point it has a light note that's patchouli and musk.A part of me says four stars because it's not what I call faithful to being a pine based cologne in it's lifespan.But it's outdoorsy,kind of spicy,and turns into a well characterized tobacco cologne.Krizia isn't as strong as Quorum but it's certainly colorful and not linear.I'm glad Krizia Uomo is still made I can't find it in local stores.

Using this product ruined the first part of our vacation due to his pain and having to find places in Colorado to stay inside to avoid the sun to let him heal. Despite my long held belief in using organic products and following the EWG recommendations I will never use this product again and would not recommend it to anyone.

column6: Van Der Hagen Premium Shave Set (2.5 oz. Soap, Bowl, Brush)
column13: Cheap and gets the job done.
column14:
Soap didn't last long at all, VDH makes a decent unscented soap that I found at my local grocery store, and that one is faring much better.

Bowl doesn't have a handle, so that is disappointing, but it works and sits flat. Size is fine and doesn't look stupid in the bathroom.

Brush is just fine. Doesn't come with a holder, so mine has been drying bristles-up, which is bad, but I shake as much water out as I can, and it has been holding up for a couple of months just fine.

For the price, in a pinch, or for someone new to wet shaving, I would recommend this set. Once the soap runs out, you find good soap to put in the bowl. Once the brush is destroyed from drying upside down, you replace with another cheap brush with a stand. Once the second soap runs out, get a decent mug if you want a handle, or if you've gotten used to this, then whatever, it's a ceramic bowl, not much to complain about.

Not great as a gift, not much luxury here, but as a necessary hygiene product, it is just fine.

column6: Shea Moisture Shea Butter Leave in Conditioner 8oz
column13: Smells terrific and could be great for someone with non-henna'd hair....
column14:
I bought this to "save" my hair. After years of using henna (because I'm a hair donor and cannot use chemical dyes), my hair has become rough, gnarly, "like piano wire" (according to a friend), and basically untouchable. I stopped using henna and started using another chemical-free dye; so far so good as far as that goes... but I needed something to LEAVE IN to help my hair to soften, look and feel touchable, and above all... HELP ME WITH FRIZZ and help my beautiful spiral curls have the "oomph" they used to have. Right now, they only have "uggggh", no "oomph"...

So I used this after my bi-weekly washing. I can't just wash and go (no curly-girl can), so I put my hair into my usual braided updo. Next day, unfurled the hair, combed out... was HOPING that this stuff would do something with my curls and also, feel SOFT. Well, it didn't. Felt kinda sticky and rough and left a weird film on my hands. I tried it again w/ the next wash, used LESS product - because "a little goes a long way" as so many on here have said! It worked a LITTLE better; my curls looked more natural and my hair felt softer. But that feeling didn't last long. It weighed my hair down and my hair still felt rough (that weird film).

I will continue to use it because it SMELLS MARVELOUS (hubby was freebasing my hair all night on this stuff; he adores the smell, and so do I). And because I adore Shea Moisture's products - I use their shampoo and conditioner, which is why I turned to them for a leave-in conditioner. I'm hoping it's just my hair being a turd due to overuse of henna (maybe my cuticle is too rough and I need a super exotic $5,000 conditioner before THIS conditioner will work? Who knows?)... because I adore Shea Moisture so much! If my hair stops being a turd and this indeed turns out to be a 5-star, and my piano wire rough weird hair becomes soft and beautiful and touchable again... I'll be back...

column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column13: Perfect for a Noticeable Brightness Boost!
column14:
When it comes to toothpaste, I am a dedicated Crest user and have been for years. My standard Crest toothpaste has a whitening component, and while Iâ€™m sure it helps prevent stains, over time certain habits (I drink coffee and red wine often) lead to less than super bright teeth. Enter Crest 3D White Brilliance Daily Cleansing and Whitening system. The â€œsystemâ€ involves a 2 step process, where first you brush for one minute with a Deep Cleaning Toothpaste, followed by brushing for one minute with a Whitening Finisher gel (with no rinsing in between steps). As a Crest fan, I have used Crestâ€™s other 2-step whitening system before (Crest ProHealth HD), and I liked the results as well as the squeaky clean feeling it gave my teeth. But that system was a bit too harsh on my sensitive gums, so I had to use it for one brushing every other day instead of twice a day. Having to use my regular toothpaste routine in between slowed down my results a bit. So when I was offered a free trial system of Crest 3D White Brilliance as part of a promotion from Crest, I was happy to try it out and see if I could use it more frequently to get a faster whitened smile.

After using the product for about 3 weeks, I am happy with my positive results, with no gum sensitivity problems! My teeth are noticeably brighter, shinier, and overall they feel very clean, similar to the way they feel right after a cleaning at the dentistâ€™s office. I would be likely to use this system maybe twice a year to renew my smile and re-whiten my teeth. The two step process is not a big difference from my regular one step brushing routine, and doesnâ€™t really require any extra brushing time (2 mins total? I can live with that!). The Deep Cleaning toothpaste in the step one tube is a good consistency - it has a bit of texture to scrub the teeth nice and clean without being overly coarse or gritty. Without water, it does not foam a lot, but it doesn't feel that much different than regular toothpaste. The step 2 tube contains the whitening agent, and it doesn't have an unpleasant taste. The other 2 step system by Crest I've tried had a very bleach-y tasting whitening gel, and it actually tasted a lot like Crest white strips. The Whitening Finisher gel that comes with the Crest 3D White Brilliance system is a much more pleasant experience. One other thing I did notice with this system is that when I used it the very first time, I had white spots develop on my gums in a few areas. The instructions with the system indicated that this is not abnormal and temporary. In fact, the spots did go away in a few hours and they never came back with any later usages.

Overall the pros of the product:
1. It left my teeth and mouth feeling especially clean, like it feels right after a cleaning at the dentist
2. It made my teeth noticeably whiter and shinier
3. My sensitive gums were not irritated by the product

The only con:
1. It did leave some white spots on my gums after the first usage. The box says this is normal and the spots went away, but it did make me wonder a bit about what caused that and if it was good for me.

For the most part, this product did exactly what it claimed to do, and I am enjoying my newly brighter and whiter teeth! I would definitely use this again, not as my standard toothpaste, but every so month for maintenance to keep my smile looking bright and sparkly.

column13: Very nice cream with an unfortunate lack of transparency in ingredients
column14:
How do you compare the hundreds of skin care products? As a regular tester, I've arrived at a list of key considerations. I hope these are helpful to you!

~ Fragrance: Lotiony.
~ Feel during application: Smooth and slippery. This is a light to medium weight lotion.
~ Feel after absorption: Soft, moist
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: Should be okay for all. Feels lovely on my oily, sensitive skin. Shea butter is a great moisturizer for dry skin.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No indication.
~ Packaging: 1oz heavy frosted glass wide-mouth jar with screw-top lid.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* Skin looks perkier, moister, very slight reduction in appearance of fine wrinkles.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* This has a number of good active ingredients that should help prevent skin aging. Iâ€™m disturbed by the lack of a full ingredient list anywhere on the box or online. The ingredients listed by the manufacturer are only the active ingredients; if they were combined alone this would simply be a pool of oil. The fact that itâ€™s a lotion means that there are emulsifiers and some type of water-soluble ingredient(s) in it. This lack of full and honest disclosure is why Iâ€™m rating what could otherwise be an excellent product at four stars rather than 5. I donâ€™t even think itâ€™s legal to sell this without making the full ingredient list available with purchase.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

column14:
Anyone who has ready my reviews knows that I am Majestic Pure fan all the way. I have been using their oils for a few months now and love them. They go in all of my DIY beauty recipes and are part of my daily health and hygiene.

I got the Jojoba oil after a friend of mine who is a make-up artist told me that the oil was great for filling in lines, wrinkles, and for creases in concealer and eyeshadow. I had to give it a try.

Basically, if you are using it for that purpose you simply take a small drop on your ring finger and lightly tap it under the eye or on the eyelid. Make sure you don't get too close to the waterline. It worked like a charm. Within seconds the fine lines and creases were gone!

If you are looking for a pure oil that is good for fine lines, wrinkles, and make-up creasing I highly suggest Jojoba and specifically Majestic Pure.

column6: CRYSTAL BODY DEODORANT Stick Unscented (4.25 fl oz)
column13: Amazing Product & Best Application Advice I Have Found
column14: Best advice I found for success with this product: Run a bit of water over the top of the rock and apply continuously under your arm until the moisture dries (about 30 seconds), and then do the same to your other side. Some people use the liquid rock as a light back up layer after using the rock, or use a natural scented deodorant as back up - any of these options works extremely well for me.  I read a lot of reviews & tips before purchasing this and I must say I'm so impressed by this product. I was finding that regular deodorants (even the clinical strength) tend to give out half way through the day, but this one didn't. After reading numerous reviews I followed some advice and used the crystal rock first and then put the liquid roll-on lightly over top as a back-up layer. I cannot believe how well this works. I haven't yet tried it during something like a work out, but for day-to-day purposes its amazing. I don't have to feel self-conscious at work anymore (in fear that my deodorant will stop working). I honestly don't mind sweating as long as I don't smell. The added bonus of no white residue, or yellow stains just makes it that much better. Highly recommend.

column6: The Honest Company - Sunscreen Lotion SPF 30, 3 Fl Oz
column13: My toddler was burnt wearing this sunscreen
column14:
I'm really confused about this sunscreen and how I feel about it. I was pleased when I saw the 2 pack at Costco and that it didn't contain all the chemicals that I'm trying to avoid. Today my son and I were in the sun for an 1.5 - 2 hours (which included at least half of that time spent in the shade) and we both got burnt using this sunscreen.

It's not too thick and spreads a little easier than other comparable sunscreen, but it's a sunscreen and what good is it if it doesn't protect us?

I felt so awful that I let my toddler get burnt, because at first I thought I must have just forgotten to put on his arms, but his arms were greasy with white sunscreen in the crease of his arm, so I'm wondering if this sunscreen is actually effective.

For now, I'm going back to Badger sunscreens which Amazon always has in stock!

column6: Innisfree No Sebum Mineral Powder 5g
column14:
It's a loose powder, so be prepared to buy/use a powder brush along with it because the puff is literally useless and will pack on WAY too much powder. If you want something that you can bring on the go for touch ups, pay the extra money and go for the compact, which is what I wish I did. There's a slight mineral-y scent to it that's a little disconcerting at first, but not unpleasant.

Despite the inconveniences, it's a pretty good powder and I like the way it applies. It's translucent and leaves your skin feeling soft and distinctly un-oily, which is a must for my sweat-proof summer routine. Recently I've been combining this powder with the "baking" technique, so it doesn't matter if I accidentally put a little too much powder on, and I'm pretty pleased with the results. But like I said, it's a huge hassle to bring a loose powder around for touch ups and blotting, especially since the effects won't last you the entire day, so you might want to go for the compact instead if that's what you're looking for.

I have said this many times in my reviews, I love diffusers. They are the safest way to make a room smell nice.

I was sent a sample of this to test and review. The thing about this one is that, while it is one of the largest diffusers out there, with only 2 modes (high mist or low mist), it can still only last up to 12 hours and needs a lot of essential oil drops due to the amount of water it can contain, for it to efficient. But the biggest complaint is the price. This is a very high priced item with only 2 mist mode settings and only 1 led setting. Blue light on or off.

Other ones I have tried, have several light settings and best f all have a setting for intermittent mist to make the water last longer with a smaller container.

So all in all, this is a good product, but for the price, it is very limited in features. If you do not care about the extra features and just want a large diffuser to decorate a large table, while making the room smell nicer, this can work for you. But in comparison, it doesnt really work for me.

column6: Urban Decay Naked Skin Weightless Ultra Definition Liquid Makeup - #0.5 30ml/1oz
column14: As a pale girl I am always on the lookout for the perfect foundation. I decided to try the lightest shade of this new foundation by Urban Decay. It comes in a 1 fl. oz. bottle with a pump dispenser. You must shake it well before each use to get it mixed thoroughly. Application is fairly easy. In my case I just pump out a little on my brush and kind of stipple it all over my face concentrating on the areas that need it the most then I buff it into my skin. I have a lot of discoloration so I always have to go back and add more to problem areas. There is no SPF in this foundation and it has a somewhat thin consistency. I have combination skin and it does not cause me to break out. I did go through a period where my skin was super dry and this foundation did seem to accentuate the dry patches. The coverage is just okay in my opinion but it is buildable. I am including a before and after using this foundation on my cheek. You can see all the discoloration that I have to cover. Overall I would say this is a good foundation but it has its flaws.

column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column13: Loved it at first...but then the staining happened
column14: I received a kit for free from BzzAgent and Crest for testing purposes.  At first, I loved this kit and couldn't say enough good things about the simplicity, convenience, price, and pain-free, instantaneous results.  All you have to do is brush with the paste and the gel for one minute each, twice a day, as you normally would.  In that regard, this is one of the easiest whitening systems I've ever used.  However, BE CAREFUL.  This product contains stannous fluoride which can cause staining.  There is a disclaimer on the product which I hadn't noticed until I got a slight brownish color (almost like a coffee stain) on my teeth.  Supposedly, this can be due to improper brushing, but I had been very careful with following the directions and even using a timer when brushing my teeth.  At this point, I'm disappointed because of how much I loved this product.  Now I'm stuck with this staining and I don't know how to make it go away.  It isn't terrible, but I definitely notice it.

column13: This frankincense has very astringent qualities, juniper was one of the main notes, very striking smoky notes, as well.
column14:
Boswellia serrata is a plant that produces Indian frankincense, Salai, referred to in Sanskrit as shallaki and in Latin as Olibanum Indicum.The plant is native to much of India and the Punjab region that extends into Pakistan. Frankincense is tapped from the scraggy but hardy trees by slashing the bark, which is called striping, and allowing the exuded resin to bleed out and harden. These hardened resins are called tears. There are several species and varieties of frankincense trees, each producing a slightly different type of resin. Differences in soil and climate create even more diversity of the resin, even within the same species.

Frankincense serrata essential oil is made from resin of Boswellia serrata and hydro-distilled by an old traditional technique from distillers in India.

What You Get: (1) 10 ml Boswellia Serrata Essential Oil in a Dark Amber Bottle, with Black Plastic Cap. Origin: India , Steam Distilled from tree resin.

PROs:

âž”' Aroma. This frankincense has very astringent qualities, juniper was one of the main notes, I found there to be some very striking smoky overtones as well. Such a contrast from Boswellia Carteri (African Frankincense) - which has a more well rounded, spicy with ginger-like profile.

âž” '100% USDA Certified. Pesticide free. As with all organic products, none of it is grown or handled using genetically modified organisms, which the organic standards expressly prohibit. Products bearing this label are made with 100% organic ingredients and may display the USDA Organic seal.

âž”' To promote a good sleep add 2-3 drops on a tissue, fold and place inside your pillowcase. If you prefer vapor diffusion add a couple drops along with Lavender and Clary Sage in your candle oil diffuser or electric diffuser.

'âž” Blends well with: Carrot seed, Cedarwood Atlas, Clove, Basil, Bergamot, Buddha Wood, Cedarwood Himalayan, Chamomile Roman, Cinnamon Leaf or Bark,Clary Sage, Coriander, Myrrh, Nutmeg, Pine, Sandalwood, Vetiver, Geranium, Ginger Fresh, Grapefruit Pink, Kaffir Lime, Spruce, Lavender Bulgarian, Lemon, Lime, Neroli,Orange Sweet, Sandalwood, Siam Wood, Tangerine, and Vanilla Bourbon essential oils.

Benefits of this oil:

âž”' An Ayurvedic herb also classified as a phytopharmaceutical (H15; Europe) which appears to be quite anti-inflammatory, may help cerebral edema. Boswellia serrata appears to have preliminary evidence for anti-inflammatory joint disorders.

âž”' The anti-inflammatory properties of Frankincense serrata make it ideal for joint pain and for menstrual pain.

âž”' Positive effects of Boswellia in some chronic inflammatory diseases including rheumatoid arthritis, bronchial asthma, osteoarthritis, ulcerative colitis and Crohn's disease have been reported. [source: Ammon HP."Modulation of the immune system by Boswellia serrata extracts and boswellic acids. [Review]" Phytomedicine. 17(11):862-7, 2010 Sep.]

'âž” Diffusing Frankincense serrata during meditation creates a meditative environment.

CONs:

'âž” At least one case study has noted the possibility of an allergy to Boswellia Serrata when topically applied as a cream. [source: Acebo E, et al Allergic contact dermatitis from Boswellia serrata extract in a naturopathic cream . Contact Dermatitis. (2004)]

CONCLUSION:

A great addition to your sleep regimen. Astringent smelling oil, a contrast from the spicier African frankincense.

column6: L'Oreal Paris Voluminous Butterfly Mascara, Midnight Black [872] 0.39 oz
column13: A Wand and Formula that Really Works
column14:
I like Lâ€™Orealâ€™s Voluminous Butterfly Mascara in Midnight Black (washable). I have very short, sparse, and light colored eyelashes that are hidden behind somewhat thick glasses all day. My eye makeup is usually a dramatic daywear with a lot of emphasis on the eyes (so you can see them behind my thick, black, plastic frames and thicker lenses).
I am a drugstore make up user as such any comparisons are between this and other drugstore brands.
Pros:
â€¢ Great, intense dark black color. I think its color is a lot like Lâ€™Orealâ€™s Carbon Black mascaras.
â€¢ I have less flaking with this and other Lâ€™Oreal mascaras than I do with CoverGirl and Maybelline (which I used to be a big fan of).
â€¢ Can hold a curl from my Revlon curler pretty much all day.
â€¢ Gives me great length.
â€¢ Doesnâ€™t give me raccoon eyes even during summertime use.
â€¢ Wand works really well for me.
â€¢ Formula is consistent throughout three months of use. Doesnâ€™t dry out quickly and isnâ€™t too wet of a mascara to begin with.
â€¢ Easy to remove with just water and Cetaphil soap. (Make up removers and my skin donâ€™t mix well)
Cons:
â€¢ Biggest con: The terrible, chemically floral scent. This scent lingers all day when you wear this product. Itâ€™s like a bad perfume scent, but close to your eyes. I can get used to it, but it weird and makes you wonder what Lâ€™Oreal is putting it in.
â€¢ Not much volumizing. (A little weird that itâ€™s called â€œVoluminousâ€). However, I wasnâ€™t really looking for volumizing so it didnâ€™t bother me.
â€¢ Cannot use more than three coats or it clumps. (All drugstore mascaras do this to me though).
â€¢ Wand had a bit of a learning curve.
â€¢ During allergy season, I find this irritates my already irritated eyes. (Generally, I just go make up less on really bad allergy days anyways).
To use. I use the Lâ€™Oreal Voluminous Butterfly Mascara I first curl my lashes. Then I use the non-flared side of the mascara wand to coat my lashes on both eyes. Then, I go back (this prevents clumps) and use the flared side to comb through my lashes, wiggling it slightly. This separating them for a fanned look while also lengthening them. Sometimes, I use the point of the brush to help get in the corners. For my bottom lashes, I first use the non-flared side and then use the point to define them (mine tend to lay flat and this seems to curl them). This works really well for me.
I would say there is a good chance I will probably buy Lâ€™Oreal Voluminous Butterfly Mascara again. The color is great and this works well to make my lashes look like them exist and holds a curl. I would not recommend this mascara to those looking for a volumizing mascara or are sensitive to perfumes. I downgraded this mascara a star because the smell.

column6: Remington Silk Ceramic Professional Hair Dryer
column13: Works for my diy and craft projects
column14:
I do not dry my hair with a hair dryer, but I will use it to set a style on occasion. My main use for a hair dryer is crafts, diy projects, and science experiments, so my review is based upon the usefulness for those purposes.

My old hair dryer, which I've had for many years, is finally on its last legs, so it was time for a new hair dryer. I didn't need something that cost an arm and a leg as I don't need all the dings and whistles for my purposes. I just needed something that had different heat settings and air flow settings. I wanted something that was light weight and comfortable to hold.

This hair dryer fits the bill with its 3 heat settings and 2 speed settings. For more delicate items, I use the low heat and low speed. For shrink wrapping baskets, I use either the medium or high heat setting and high speed. The high heat is hot and this hair dryer can really kick out the air which makes the shrink wrapping go a lot faster than it did with my old hair dryer.

It's comfortable in my hand thanks to the shape, and since it's light weight, it doesn't tire my arm out when a project takes a while to dry/set.

column14: I use this for easy clean up when painting my nails and doing nail art by just brushing some around the cuticles letting it dry down, then painting my nails and  peeling off after. I was a little worried that this might take a while to dry down but it seemed to dry down fairly quickly with in 2-3 mins at the most and peels off fairly easy with out much struggle or too much effort. I actually decided to take this product and transfer it to an empty nail polish bottle to make application easier as the container is some what large for what I need to use this for and can get messy easily or spill.  If you are going to transfer this product the best way I recommend to do it is thru an oral syringe  (the kind used to give infants medicine), usually you can find one for cheap at your local pharmacy. Transferring this product was also very easily and practically mess free and clean up was a breeze since all you have to do is just wait for it to dry and then peel it off! I would definitely recommend this product to anyone looking for easy clean up for nail art but doesn't want to pay the crazy prices these polish makers/companies want for one tiny bottle. column6: Batiste Dry Shampoo
column13: Game changer!  Replaces Mousse, can wash hair less often,  fills out the roots :)
column14: Wow!  I have tried a lot of dry shampoos from high end to all the drug store brands and this is by far the best.  Only one that comes close to this is the Bumble and Bumble one for blonds but it is way more expensive and I do like this one better.  The Batiste for blondes make my fine blond hair look more voluminous and flowing on days when I wash it and I spray it on day two for oil absorption so I only have to wash my hair every other day.  I have pretty oily roots in the morning and with this and washing every other day my oil production has really slowed down.  The tint to this spray powder is key here.  I have naturally light blond hair and for day two unwashed hair the crown of my hair looks darker even when it doesn't look oily because the hair gets darker when its wet/oil.  This makes my color continuous adding and the powder itself gives it fullness which is why this makes your hair look phenomenal.  I have stopped using mousse altogether because I realized this lifts where mousse weighs it down.  It also smells amazing, not overpowering just a nice neutral sent so my hair doesn't smell like hair! on day two.  It is powdery to the touch for the first few hours but doesn't get everywhere by any means.  Lift your roots section by section and spray it in.  Finish your makeup or put your clothes on then massage it a bit and you won't see any residue at all.  I keep from tossing my hair or running my fingers through it for the first few hours so the powder really stays to the roots of the hair.  After a while you can't tell it is in three at all as your natural oils have mixed with it.  If you have problems with it coming off on clothes and such I would say you are either using way to much or are spraying the surface of your hair which won't give good results anyway. Lift your hair up with one hand and spray the under side of your roots. You want the powder to absorb from the bottom not all over the top.  Hope this is helpful.  I buy this product in bulk now.  Amazing!mazing!

column13: Good replacement for the extinct Bullfrog Surfer Formula
column14:
I was a long-time user of Bullfrog's Surfer Formula. Bullfrog discontinued it, and the replacement didn't come close in ease of use and effectiveness. I did a search, hoping to find a hidden BSF supply. None to be found, but I saw a reference to Doc Martin's Nextgen. Hmm.

I decided to buy it. The product arrived. My first reaction was a little skeptical: 2 ounces isn't much!

I gave it a try the next day on a hot, sunny day. A little bit goes a LONG way, so 2 ounces should last a while. It is very easy to apply, and even has a pleasant scent. I was out in the sun 5 hours with one application, and didn't have any burn. It didn't run until I got a surprise face bath, and then I had some run-off in my eyes. But I haven't had any eye run-off otherwise, even on long, hot, sweaty, muggy days.

Doc Martin's Nextgen is a good substitute for the late Bullfrog Surfer Formula: it's easy to apply, it works for hours and hours, it stays put, but it's easy to remove when you want to remove it. I expect to be a repeat customer.

A pleasant surprise was receiving a personal e-mail from the seller checking on my satisfaction. Old-school customer service, which I appreciated.

column6: Blistex Moisture Melt, .35oz
column14: After having more than one tube of wax-based lip balm (Chapstick for one) melt into an unusable goo in the South Florida heat, I did a little research.  The wax-based balms offer more protection than healing.  I wanted a combination of both.  My lips aren't necessarily "chapped" all the time but they could use a boost here and there.  I've tried a few other "ointment-based" lip balms but seemed to keep coming back to the Blistex Moisture Melt.  It offers shea butter, aloe AND sunscreen all in one.  It has a slightly sweet taste which is important since you tend to ingest part of it anyway.  I don't necessarily believe in the hyped "softbeads" but hey, whatever floats Blistex' boat.  It seems to last just as long as wax-based lips on your lips.  I like the four pack.  It's a good value, especially with Amazon Prime shipping.  The per-pack price is less than here locally at a brick-and-mortar store (when you can find it).  Soooo, I am able to keep one at the bedside to use just before retiring, one in the car, one hanging around home and one for work.  Does it separate a little in the heat of the car, yes.  But it is still quite usable.  I give this two thumbs up!

column6: Italia Deluxe Ultra Fine Lip Liner set (Pack Of 12)
column14:
I like the variety of colors provided in this set. I generally wear one of the red shades under red lipstick, but I've also worn the other colors alone with just a bit of gloss. If you're trying to figure out what shades of lipsticks look best on you, or just want to play around with colors you wouldn't normally wear, I think this is an excellent purchase. There are a couple of very dark burgandy or purplish shades that I would never buy in a tube, but I actually liked the way they looked for a more extreme look.

They have a nice fine tip, and are easy to apply. Each liner is a full size (approximately the size of a regular pencil), so you can get a lot of use out of them.

They last pretty long, depending on your eating and drinking habits. If I wear the liner alone over lip balm, it generally lasts through coffee, a snack, and a bottle of water, but is generally gone by lunch. With the liner and lipstick (Besame brand), I usually still have color on my lips after lunch, though it's faded a little.

I think this set is a good buy if you're looking to experiment with a lot of different lipstick colors.

column13: Good face wash - smells nice and fresh.
column14: I'm 24 with mild acne and really sensitive skin which can be either oily or dry depending on the day. I like this face wash well enough. I put it in my own pump bottle and use a wash cloth to wash my face with it since it's runny but I don't mind that. I think the smell is pleasant. To me it smell nice a fresh, it reminds me the smell of tea tree oil. I've only used a couple of day but it's gentile enough that I can use it morning and evening without over drying my skin. I will update when I see how well it works for my blemishes and such.  UPDATE: After using this for a week or two I haven't seen any difference in my acne and it did begin to dry me out a little bit after using it all the time so I've cut back to only using once a day or maybe every other day. It doesn't seem to clear my face up at all but then again neither has anything else I've tried so that's probably just me. Don't let it discourage you because if your skin isn't ultra sensitive like mine it may work you. I still love the smell and think it's a decent cleanser but I'll probably try something else soon since I'm still trying to get my face cleared up.

column6: Encre Noire Cologne by Lalique for men Colognes
column13: For A Strong, Masculine Man THIS is Your Cologne
column14:
This stuff is amazing. If you love Vetiver this scent might be for you. I say might because don't think this is some fresh, soapy Vetiver like most that are on the market. This is dark, hard, woody, strong, and masculine. Encre Noire translates into Black Ink and that name is spot on. On the initial spray the Vetiver is so strong the cologne has an inky scent to it. This initial blast of ink only lasts about 5-10 minutes however, as the scent dries down the Vetiver becomes more earthy and you start to pick up this slightly burnt wood scent. The dry down on this is hands down one of the best I've ever smelt. It does take a certain kind of man to be able to wear this cologne however. You have to be able to match its intense, strong, masculine scent. This instantly became one of my wife's favorite scents. She loves Vetiver and her favorite cologne on me ever was Creed's Original Vetiver. When she smelled this one on me she said she would put it tied with Original Vetiver. Not because they smell the same (they don't) but because this Cologne is just awesome.

The projection is out of this world. After spraying it (2-3 sprays) on my wife can be over 10 ft away in a different room and still smell it. It fills the air. Her immediate response when she smelled it in the room, not knowing what I had put on, was "Something smells REALLY good." After I told her what it was she said, "You bought this one right? It smells amazing."

Longevity is also a beast. I can wear in the evening, go to bed, and still smell it the next day. We timed it on my skin and could still pick it up over 18 hours later. This is a cologne where you do not want to over spray. 2-3 max will give you everything you could possibly need.

Everything about this cologne just screams "niche". This isn't a department store fragrance made to appeal to the masses. The bottle, the quality of the ingredients, the smell. If I handed you this cologne you would assume it's some ultra high end brand. The fact that you can get it for around $30 is insane. This cologne isn't for everyone, it isn't for the office, it isn't for a summer day out. This is an evening out or suit & tie fragrance. This is a fall/winter fragrance. This could be someone's signature scent. For all the things this cologne isn't, what it does do, it does to perfection. I will always own a bottle of this cologne from now on.

column6: Men's Rogaine Foam One Month Supply
column14: I started using the liquid 5% Rogaine when I was 18 years ago when I began to experience thinning in my crown area and slight recession in vertex areas. I've also used Propecia/finasteride for the past 17 years. My crown filled in within four months of starting Rogaine liquid, my vertex mostly filled in within 6 months, my hair regained nearly all of it's pre-thinning thickness around 1 year after starting the Propecia and today I still have most of my hair (I'm between a Norwood I and Norwood II). I have slight recession in my temples and have been able to maintain most of my widow's peak. I prefer the foam to the liquid. It is MUCH less irritating to my scalp (although I understand experiences will vary among users), and right now I prefer the brand name Rogaine because it seems to retain more of it's foam consistency when applied, compared to generic minoxidil (store brand) foam. The brand name Rogaine foam seems to also be even less irritating to my scalp than the generic minoxidil foam.

Took my family to the waterpark for the day and applied this non-harmful, non-chemical, completely non-functional paste pretending to be sunscreen.  Now the entire family is sunburned - even though over a 5 or 6 hour window, we applied the sunscreen liberally 3-4 times.  This natural ingredient sunscreen allowed the natural sun to naturally burn our skin - so natural!  We would have been better off going with no sunscreen than this garbage - at least we would not have had the false sense of being safe from the sun's harmful rays, and would have worn protective clothing and found more frequent shade.  Give me traditional sunscreens any day over The Honest Company "Sunscreen".

column14: I purchased the New Pro-Nu Soft & Comfortable Sleep Mask with Ear Plugs & Carry Pouch, because who can't sleep better when it is totally dark?  I know I can!  We listen to the radio at night and between the glowing lights from the radio and the red number's on the alarm clock, sometimes, I cannot get to sleep.  These solve that problem!  The New Pro-Nu Soft & Comfortable Sleep Mask with Ear Plugs & Carry Pouch comes with, well a carrying pouch, ear plugs (great for when the husband starts snoring too loudly), and an adjustable sleep mask.  But wait, there's more!  This particular sleep mask has 2 nice little slots on the back to store your ear plugs!  I have never seen this before, but I have to say it is a great concept!  I used to sleep with ear plugs and sleep masks quite often when I was younger, and the one thing I always did was lose the ear plugs.  It never failed. I had them for a few days and then they were gone.  Well, now, I can just take them out of my ears and place them in the elastic band of the sleep make and I don't have to worry about finding them later!  The mask itself is very soft on the inside and has adjustable Velcro straps in the back to help ensure a prefect fit.  I would recommend this sleep mask to anyone that travels or just needs the room dark to fall asleep.  I purchased this New Pro-Nu Soft & Comfortable Sleep Mask with Ear Plugs & Carry Pouch at a DISCOUNTED price in exchange for my HONEST & UNBIASED opinion.

column14: I was reminded this morning of the beauty of YSLâ€™s Lâ€™Hommeâ€¦ A fragrance nearly 10 years old and still going strong.  This blend of citrus, spicy, and tonka bean notes remains a staple go-to fragrance in my collection.  I have found that Lâ€™Homme will work during any season and for most events â€“ from formal to more casual outings.  Additionally, I would offer Lâ€™Homme works across many age groups, and while many masculine notes are present, it is â€œsoftâ€ enough for those who enjoy fragrances that are closer to unisex.  Regarding longevity and projection/sillage, I am certain Lâ€™Homme has gone through the reformulation process, and the product of today is a faint memory of historical versions.  Be that as it may, the memories remain fond..!!  Todayâ€™s Lâ€™Homme manages average longevity and projection/sillage, lasting 4 to 6 hours on me, longer on clothing, all at armâ€™s length distance.  YSL is well known to create Rock-Star fragrances and Lâ€™Homme is the â€œbig brother in the bandâ€ in this lineup.  All said, my final tally for Lâ€™Homme is 4.2 stars out of 5 stars.  If performance were better in the current formulation, this fragrance would be near perfection.  Regardless, I remain committed to a solid recommendation adding Lâ€™Homme to any collection and a â€œLoveâ€ for the Fragrantica following. You will not be disappointed.. column6: MerieWare Electrical Callus Remover and Foot File
column13: No Super Power. Like Other Battery-Operated.
column14:
This device is advertised as being super powerful vs. its competition. The others all warn you not to press too hard or the device will stop. Not clear what that is all about, but have had no problems with this unit. Despite the warning about its possibly removing live skin due to its power, it is a pussy cat. How much damage can be done with 2 disposable batteries? This thing is not operating on AC power.

Found no issues when I deliberately veered of onto live skin.

Actually found no difference between this unit and all its competitors.

Bottom Line: probably no difference between all these callus removers based on the review comments. All are equally effective at removing dead skin and, if powered by batteries, very unlikely to do you any harm. So my advice, buy the least expensive.

Chose this one because it had no compensated reviewers. All the others were dominated by paid reviewers who gave them 5-star reviews. Are you surprised? (Some gave only 4 stars.)

column13: best value for the money. If you want a electric toothbrush and water flosser. Dont think. just buy
column14:
Fantastic value. It does what it says. It cleans your teeth. And it comes with many different attachments (which all have a dedicated storage area next to the water tank)

Only problem I have seen is that it uses water fast so you might have to refill the cup often. And the water flosser , when turned up to "maximum power" becomes obnoxiously loud. But that is to be expected of water pumps.

I do wish the toothbrush heads were made of a more "rubbery" plastic because if you are using the higher powered mode and your teeth touch the hard plastic it can be quite uncomfortable or even painful.

Definately a great buy. 1 point deducted because the brush heads could be softer.

column6: Glow Perfume by J. Lo for women Personal Fragrances
column13: Great first perfume for young women.
column14:
Glow is the first "grown up" perfume I ever owned when I was about 15. When this thing launched it was a BIG DEAL and I was excited to jump on it.

As far as fragrances go, it's definitely not going to wow you. Honestly if you're an adult who has already tried a number of fragrances you're probably going to want to skip it. It's a very generic "clean" smelling fragrance with some slight floral notes. However, as a first perfume for a teenager I think it's a great choice. It's very safe, it smells pretty good on nearly everyone and I don't think it's offensive smelling at all. It also lasts quite a while. I'm kind of a perfume nut so I've tried everything, and this honestly is one of the longest lasting scents I've ever used. It's also very subtle and almost impossible to go overboard with, so you don't need to worry about putting on way too much and clearing a room.

column6: Crest Pro-Health HD Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Healthier Mouth via Daily Two-Step System - 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column13: I've noticed my teeth are whiter
column14:
So full disclosure, I received Crest Pro HealthÂ® HDâ„¢ toothpaste for free to try as part of a promotion with Crest and BzzAgent. With that out of the way, I will explain to those unfamiliar with this product that the two-step process involves one minute of brushing with the cleaning toothpaste and then one minute of brushing with the polishing/whitening gel. The cleaning toothpaste seems to be comparable to other Crest products. The whitening gel also seems similar to home whiteners. The fact that it is a two-step process is an extremely minor inconvenience, though when you have an electric toothbrush (as I do) it simplifies things. I know that after it buzzes twice it's time to move onto step 2.
I find the taste to be inoffensive. It's not great, but I don't really expect toothpaste or teeth whiteners to have a pleasant taste. The step 1 toothpaste is a little on the gritty side, if that's something that bothers you.
In any case, I will say that I was really glad I got this opportunity because my teeth definitely look whiter. It's not as stunning of a difference as I saw with some other people's reviews, but I definitely noticed whiter teeth after using the Crest Pro HealthÂ® HDâ„¢ for 30 days. I think my teeth weren't that yellow to begin with, so maybe a less dramatic change is to be expected. I guess that's the only reason I'm giving 4 stars rather than 5.

column14: Vanicream Lite Lotion has saved me from the debacle caused by Nutraderm Original Lotion having been taken off the market. I have been using it now for over a month. On the great big plus side, it does not irritate my face, it does not clog the pores, it goes on smoothly. It does seem to sink into the skin and not leave a sheen. For me, sinking into the skin typically translates as dryness. My preference is for somewhat of a sheen, but in the case of this product, sinking into the skin does not equal dryness - it leaves more of a natural effect and I have to assume that the moisture actually protects the inner layer of the skin, and results in continued comfort. I have also used the Vanicream Moisturizing Skin Cream, which provides a thicker feel. I find it very useful in the areas that can become exceedingly dry - such as around the sides of the nose which, at least on me, needs the extra protection. In the absence of Nutraderm Lotion, I will stick with this product line which I can at least live with comfortably.

column14: I don't usually write reviews for anything but felt inclined to for this product. I made the switch to natural deodorant 8 months ago and have tried almost every brand. Before switching to a natural deodorant and leaving behind my toxic antiperspirants I did a recommended week armpit detox using bentonite clay. I will say that this deodorant has been the best for keeping smell away the longest than any other brand I have used. Although there are many things I dislike, for example it is chunky when applied. I discovered that you have to rub it into your skin after applying. It has left unwanted yellowish marks on all of my shirts no matter what I do. I have sensitive skin and I know I react to magnesium oil which is one of the ingredients. I wish I didn't as it is helpful in eliminating body odor. I did have a skin reaction and grew skin tabs (red bumps) after using this product for a week. I am pretty sure it was due to the magnesium oil ingredient. So unfortunately, I am back to trying to find the ideal healthy all natural deodorant.

column6: Naturalico Anti Aging Organic 20% Vitamin C Serum for Face with Hyaluronic Acid 1 Oz
column14:
I have been using this Vitamin C serum for about four months now and am amazed at how effective it is!

My skin is extraordinarily fair, heavily freckled, and (unfortunately!) fairly "lined" for my age (despite wearing sunscreen daily, wearing a hat when in the sun, and avoiding the sun as much as possible). I have, since the age of 25-30, had deep lines between my eyes, across my brow, and around my lips (due to using straws, I believe). Around age 35, I began getting lines near my eyes and very deep laugh lines, as well.

Trying to make myself accept my lines, I called them my "lines of wisdom," but still (vainly, I suppose) wanted them to go away. Hence the reason for buying this vitamin C serum!

~~EFFECTS ON WRINKLES AND LINES~~
Within about two weeks of daily use, I noticed the lines between my eyes were beginning to fade.
Within about four weeks of daily use, I noticed the lines between my eyes were less than half as deep as they had been, the lines near my eyes were completely gone, and my laugh lines were beginning to fade.
Within about eight weeks of daily use, I had a SIGNIFICANT reduction in the lines between my eyes, the lines near my eyes, and my laugh lines. The lines around my mouth and my forehead lines haven't been significantly affected, but I can deal with those if the others are so significantly reduced.

~~USE ON SENSITIVE SKIN~~
I have very sensitive skin that turns fire-engine-red when most skin products come in contact with it, but my skin handles this serum quite well. I have ZERO redness, don't break out, and have no other ill effects.

If you are expecting PERFECTION and to have the skin of a young child, you'll be disappointed. This serum is excellent, but it isn't able to erase the signs of aging completely.

If you are expecting to look just a few years younger, though, you'll love this serum!

I really like the way they look when they're layered up an arm or wrist. The designs and colors used are awesome. My son and I have several of them on right now. They don't irritate our skin or itch. They are very easy to apply and will stay on for a few days if you don't really mess with them. Mine have stayed on for about 3 days so far and only a couple are starting to come off. It really just depends on where you put them. The ones on my outer arm will probably last a week. The ones on my wrist and hand are starting to come off but it's because I wash my hands a lot. These would be great for when going to the beach, a party, or some other fun event.  I received these tattoos for reviewing purposes. All opinions expressed are solely my own.

column6: NeuCeutica Retinol Hyaluronic Acid Moisturizer Cream: Collagen, Vitamin C, 4 Ounce
column13: Good Alternative for those not wanting prescription strength.
column14:
I wanted a cream that I could pamper myself with that would have the ingredient Retinol in it because I didn't want to get a prescription for Retinol. I knew that would mean that I would have slower, less potent results but I'd avoid a doctors visit and it wouldn't be another thing perscribed to me. Because its not prescription strength though it also wouldn't be as irritating to my skin. So with that in mind I wanted something with a combination of focused skin care ingredients that I could use in combination with another product.

Looking into the other ingredients Asana Beauty uses in combination with Retinol I knew I wanted those ingrediants to all have proven clinical results. Fortunately early research suggests that applying hyaluronic acid to the skin might be helpful for treating burns and skin wounds, Jojo oil is nearly identical in chemical structure to the natural oils in your skin and Shea butter's skin care and healing properties were first harnessed thousands of years ago. So this is a irrefutable moisturize with reported skin softening and strengthening as well as wrinkle reduction. Of course results vary depending on what youre using it for and the person but 4-6 weeks with expected results on something like wrinkles, and instant results with itching or dry skin made the "Best Anti Aging and Anti Wrinkle Cream" provided to me for evaluation and review preferable just based off of researching the key ingredients. And with a larger than average contents (4 ounces) this will last the month or two of dailey applications.

column13: Highly Recommend for Healing and Hydrating Your Skin
column14:
I've used a couple of serums with Vitamin C but had been reluctant to purchase due to price and fragility of product due to natural ingredients -- it's hard to travel and ship items within Texas when we're hitting triple digits.
With that said, I really needed something to help hydrate my skin this summer. I purchased this serum on Prime Day for a ridiculously low price. I saw results the morning after the first application, which I attribute to the Organic Sea Buckthorn oil plumping up by skin. After the fourth day of use, a friend commented on how radiant and youthful I looked! Not too bad since a week earlier my pores were quite obvious.
If you are concerned that you may be allergic to one of the ingredients, do a patch test. Also keep in mind that breakouts can still occur in first week of using any product to detox your skin -- drinking plenty of water, diet with fruit and vegetables, and exercise will speed up your body's natural process to heal skin as well.
My only complaint is that I wish Valentia had more products, including a cleanser and moisturizer. I use in combination with Avene products instead.

column6: Ultrax Labs Hair Surge | Caffeine Hair Loss Hair Growth Stimulating Shampoo
column14:
I got this shampoo along with the Ultrax Hair Rush supplements about a month ago, on the recommendation of a friend. Not sure if it's the shampoo or the supplement, or the combination of the two, but I have definitely noticed a substantial decrease in the amount of hair clogging up my shower drain.

I have been dealing with an abnormal amount of hair loss after having a major surgery a year ago. I'm not sure what caused it, but I suspect the shock my body experienced combined with stress and a lack of nutrients needed to replenish my hair. I had reached a point where I was ready to try anything to stop the shedding. This shampoo is doing the trick! It doesn't really lather like a regular shampoo, so I treat it as a serum - start at my scalp and work it through the rest of my hair.

I've still got the bottle my friend gave me, but will definitely order more once I run out.

The initial scent is lovely, but it's got a half-life of maybe an hour. By midday my BO has made a return, and the lovely scent that once graced my pits is gone. column6: Foxbrim Argan Oil Hair Repair Serum - 100% Natural - Hair Treatment Oil Blend - Argan Oil with Jojoba Oil, Coconut Oil & Shea Butter - Foxbrim 4OZ
column13: Brought my hair back to life
column14:
This product has saved my hair. I dyed my hair a month ago to put a crazy hair color in it and it became very damaged. It felt the consistency of straw and it was a horrible hassle to brush. I will say I like this product. I read the directions wrong but it did so much. I was not supposed to use so much but my hair was so absorbent from the loss of protein. I probably used half a bottle the first time but I don't regret it. I let it sit in my hair and soak it up for a day and a half. (I'm a stay at home mom so I have the time). I have to say it made such a difference. By the time I washed the oil from my hair it was completely different. I won't lie I was pretty sure I'd have to do it a few times to get the result I wanted but it was a pleasant surprise what a difference it made. My hair was softer and not as hard to brush. The straw feeling is mostly gone. I'm pretty sure a couple more treatments should help it get back to normal. I went to cosmetology school so I'm used to cholesterol treatments, but this is better than that.

** This product was given to me free for my unbiased product review. These comments are my own.

column6: One 'n Only Color Fix with Argan Oil
column13: I was pleasantly surprised and decided to not even dye over the stripped hair because I liked it so much
column14: I'm reviewing this for the product not the seller. My hair has been numerous different colors this past year including blonde, orange, and a dark black/burgundy color (most recent). Before I used this, it was a dark brown at the ends, burgundy in my roots, and had blonde highlights to try to lighten the dark brown. I wanted to go back to my natural color (a light auburn) and I purchased two boxes of ColorFix and two boxes of boxed dye. I only used approximately 1/2 of one box of Colorfix and it completely saturated my hair. I used an applicator brush and did it very evenly and thoroughly. Then I put a processing cap on and let it sit for exactly 20 minutes and then went to wash it out for 5 minutes, following the directions. To my surprise, all of the dark brown/burgundy had lifted. Leaving behind a medium blonde with a slight orange tint and it still had the blonde highlights throughout. I was pleasantly surprised and decided to not even dye over the stripped hair because I liked it so much. I rewashed it and deep conditioned it and it feels no worse than it did before (my hair was already over-processed). I am incredibly impressed by the effectiveness of this product and I highly recommend it. It does smell strongly of rotten eggs though and the stench lingers in your hair and around your home (but its just a small price to pay for how great this product works). I also decided not to use the 3rd step bottle because I didn't want it to get any darker. Good luck!

column6: Crest Pro-Health HD Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Healthier Mouth via Daily Two-Step System - 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column13: Crest Pro-Health HD toothpaste changed the way I brush
column14: I received this kit free to test as a BzzAgent.  It's a 2 part system.  The first part of the Crest Pro-Health HD Toothpaste kit is a cleanser.  It contains the Stannous Fluoride that dentists recommend.  It cleans teeth and removes stubborn plaque.  The 2nd step is the polisher, and it whitens teeth.  Not with harsh chemicals, but with hydrogen peroxide.  I used the kit for over a month.  I know my teeth are cleaner in general.  Most of this is due to the 2 minutes required to brush for the Crest Pro-Health HD Toothpaste kit to work.  One full minute for each toothpaste.  My breath doesn't  feel as horrible in the morning, either, which meant that germs were being killed, as it is the plaque which causes bad breath. I'm not sure how much whiter my teeth look to other people.  but I think that they are slightly whiter. The reason I didn't give it a full 5 stars is that if I brushed for 2 minutes using ANY toothpaste, my teeth would be cleaner, my breath fresher.  Another aspect that I liked about this kit in particular is that the whitener was not harsh in any way.  I did not feel any tooth sensitivity, which is what I feared.  But that never happened with this.  A downside was that it is time consuming to use, if you follow the directions and brush for the full 2 minutes.

column6: Neutrogena Ageless Intensives Deep Wrinkle
column13: Best wrinkle cream I've ever tried.
column14: I was looking for a solution to my nearing middle age eye wrinkles. I have droopy upper lids, crows feet, slight bagging on my lower lids and dark circles under my eyes. I'm also getting those annoying lines around my upper lips (sounds attractive doesn't it?) I have tried many store bought creams including Oil of Olay Regenerist, Strivectin, and more expensive products with no results. I have to say that this product reduced the crepiness of my upper eyelids, smoothed out my crows feet, and reduced the puffiness under my eyes (though it did nothing for the dark circles under my eyes). So I tried it on my forehead, and it smoothed out those lines (not entirely, but noticeably different).Then I tried in on the wrinkles around my lips. Okay, it didn't work there, but I was happy enough with my results to buy another tube of it. It's smooth going on and you don't need to use a lot, but the size of this tube was too small (though you may want to get it if you just want to try if for a month). I will be purchasing again. Best result I've gotten from any over the counter product so far. I give it 4 stars because it didn't work on my lip lines (though it DOES say it's an eye cream!)and it didn't do anything for my dark circles. Though if that product existed, I'm sure we all would've found it by now.

The conditioner is more critical to me  I use Ouidad Essential Daily Balancing Rinse. for my conditioner and I do it very particularly. I gently comb in into sections with  wide tooth comb, scrunch it up and leave it in for at least 3 minutes. I only wash and condition about once a week so it is a long process. My hair is long and curly like corkscrews about 3//4 inch diameter but that varies actually. Some are looser, some are straighter. I just don't think the shampoo is so critical, but if I use a different conditioner my hair is ruined without hope. Also, my hair is very dry and always has been. I just don't make oil or grease anywhere so someone out there with oily hair will probably not find this helpful. The shampoo works and it smells great. I have heard daily shampoos are harsh but I don't use them daily so that shouldn't count

column6: Hustle Butter Deluxe - Tattoo Butter
column13: Highly recommend for tattoos and other skin irritations!
column14:
I absolutely love this stuff! After using another brand that is much thicker that is the usual ointment recommended by tattooers, I was given a sample of this and I will never go back. Hustle Butter is by far the best smelling, easiest to spread, and quickest healing ointment I've used on my tattoos. I have about 30 hours alone into my leg and I've been using this from the start, every session healed wonderfully, not one scab or oozing, ect. Heal time was about 1.5-2 weeks, with one session being closer to 3 weeks.

I HIGHLY recommend Hustle Butter for tattoos and other things, dry skin, small scratches, rashes, ect. Hustle Butter's Facebook has a lot of great stories of people having positive results on things other than tattoos.

After being tattooed, I wash the area with soap 2-3 times a day, after 2-3 days (when the tattoo starts feeling dry) I will apply the Hustle Butter, twice a day after washing with soap. Keep doing this until your tattoo is healed! Remember to use lightly, which should not be a problem with hustle butter, unlike other ointments.

column6: BS-MALL(TM) Makeup Brushes Premium Makeup Brush Set Synthetic Kabuki Cosmetics Foundation Blending Blush Eyeliner Face Powder Brush Makeup Brush Kit (10pcs, Golden Black)
column13: Perform as GOOD  as my VERY  expensive ( Mac, Sigma) and you can't beat the price!! Only 1 quick fix needed!!!!
column14:
Great price for these brushes. I got a silver set for my Daughter & a gold set for myself. We did have some handles come loose & fall off of 3 on one set & 4 on the other. There's a great review on top of here that will explain how you can easily fix this issue! A hot glue gun, & a bit inside and the handle will be tight on them forever! I knew this when I purchased them, so it wasn't a problem . For the price of these, the quality is great and you get a lot of different sizes, shapes. It's well worth it. But don't expect to pay $10-$12 for a bunch of decent quality brushes & get upset that the handles come loose. It's an easy cheap fix & you'll have great brushes for a few dollars!
Like she said, when you get them, wiggle the handles until they come off & fix it permanently with the hot glue gun. That way your not in the middle of getting ready to go out, putting on your foundation, concealer and it comes off and your pissed! Lol -
They are really soft, I've had NO shedding with either set. Or so minimal that I didn't take notice. They wash well, and dry nice and soft. Any loose hairs should come out when you wash them which should be done as soon as you get them & before you use them. I will be buying more sets to have, & in case the price goes up or they aren't around after. They are really great brushes and you can't , can't beat the price! I've bought expensive brushes where 1 eye brush was about $40, and I will never spend that money on brushes again! These are just as good ( after you fix the handles) and SO much cheaper! I will put my money towards great makeup that I use to spend stupidly on a few brushes because they say * MAC or * Sigma on them. Your paying them for the name & for the company to promote their products. These are Good, quality brushes where it really matters- the hairs that touch your face & put your makeup on. They don't soak up the foundation, it applies it to your skin & doesn't streak or micro exfoliate your skin as your rubbing and make it flake so your makeup isn't smooth. These are soft, but will stand up to any technique of applying foundation, powders, concealer, shadows etc.
Spend your money on great makeup and save a lot on these gems.
Love these. I've used liquid, all sorts of powders ( Ben nye loose, bare minerals, benefit) , pro cream foundation and concealer a ( Kett, Graftobian, Mehron) , also cream, powder blushes & highlighters and these brushes performed great with ALL of them.
I recommend these highly, even with the small easy fix issue with the handles!

column6: Simply Elegant Serenity Now Luxury Soft Bath Pillow - Ivory
column13: Fantastic product, highly recommended and enjoyed.
column14:
This is the fourth bath pillow I have tried. Thus far, this is by far the BEST one I have tried. The first two I tried were plasticy, cheap, blow-up air ones that weren't comfortable, practical, or long lasting. The third one, the most expensive of the 4 (purchased from Bed, Bath & Beyond for $25) and the one I've been using for quite some time, while passing the longevity test, had countless other issues that lead me to begin the search for a 4th. Needless to say, when the opportunity to fortunately receive this product at a discounted rate for the purposes of testing it and posting a completely honest and unbiased review, I was beyond excited.

This product appears to be made of a quality foam material with a smooth and supple sort of vinyl coating. It is completely sealed (not filled with holes) so that water cannot seep into the foam inside. The pillow I was using prior to this one (see picture, from Bed, Bath, & Beyond) has holes that soak up water, making it heavy and susceptible to mold (as can be seen in the picture), no matter how many ways I tried and products I used to attempt to clean it.

In addition to the material, I love the shape of this pillow. The seam is folded flat and make for an exceptionally comfortable bath-lying position. Unlike my previous pillow, which had no foldable seams, made my neck have to arch in an unnatural and uncomfortable way.

I also really love the suction cups of this pillow. They easily attached to my tub very securely and effortlessly. Compared to the more expensive Bed, Bath & Beyond version, that requires much finagling to ensure a decent suction. This pillow attached so well, I was almost concerned that it would be difficult remove, but the suction cups have these handy little tabs to pull and make removal a breeze (lacking in my expensive BB&B one).

Furthermore, no stinky smell or manual blowing up required! With a first impression such as this, AND a significantly lower price than the BB&B product, I LOVE this fantastic product and highly recommend it.

P.S.- While I have not yet used the eye mask or downloaded the music content, I'm am pretty impressed with their inclusion as bonuses and will update this review once I have had the opportunity to do so.

P.P.S- My BB&B pillow was tossed straight to the trash after my first bath session with this pillow.

Pros:
- Quality Material
- Perfect Shape
- Very Comfortable
- Perfect Tub Fit
- Quality Suction Cups
- Bonus Products Included
- No Stinky Smell
- No Blowing Up Required
- Very Fair Price

Cons:
-NONE to report at this time

column6: Curel Itch Defense Skin Balancing Moisture Lotion 20 oz
column13: Relieved my skin from dryness and itchiness.
column14:
I noticed as I gotten older my skin has gotten drier and itchier. Noticed that the lotions I was using was not helping me at all. My parents used this Curel Itch Defense lotion, so I tried it one day. I was amazed how I didn't have to use much of it and it did relieve the itchiness on my skin. My skin looked so much better and didn't feel all greasy or gross. None of us have eczema, but we have dry or itchy skin.

This Curel lotion last a long time. I am still on the same bottle since February of this year, still got about 2 to 3 months left of this lotion. I don't have to use much, enough to cover my body after I get out of the shower. Last all day. Sometimes I will reapply to my hands and arms. This lotion really makes my skin soft and moisturized. Start with a small amount like a pea size and work up with little more at a time. If you use too much at one time you will feel greasy. This lotion is not like regular lotion where one gets a tablespoon or more and use it on one arm. Very little of this goes a long ways. It's best to apply after bathing.

One of the few body lotions that can be applied to the face. I use this on my neck and face. At the bottom of my neck around my shoulders, that area gets that itchy tight feeling, hard to relieve at times. Curel really helped. When I use on my face I use it more on the outer of the face and less in the center. I don't use it all the time on my face but every so often, when I need some extra relief in that area.

Sometimes I get mosquito or bug bites, this lotion helps take the itch away, not fully but it does help to relieve that itchy feeling to where you can forget about it and not touch it.

This lotion does not have a bad scent or smell, it's fragrance free. Some lotions that have no scent or no fragrance, will have a smell to it, kinda gross like. This lotion has no smell at all or it is so light that it's hard to notice it.

I was never a Curel fan before I tried it years ago, but this lotion has changed my mind about Curel. I used other kinds of lotions for sensitive skin that has been out for years. Did not help me one bit. Curel Itch Defense lotion worked when I first used it. I hope the makers of Curel lotion keeps this lotion on the shelves and does not change the formula. This stuff works amazingly.

column14: I love this candle!!!! The packaging and label are simple and descriptive, but not too overwhelming as to take away from the simple aesthetics and therapeutic qualities of the candle. It's so therapeutic! The scent filled the room and it helped to make for a much more relaxing night after the baby went to bed. The wax melts into this thick, oily substance and was great for giving the perfect massage! My boyfriend asked me again the next night to light the candle and give him a massage! column6: MHD Professional 1.25 Inch Salon Grade Professional Tourmaline Ceramic Plate Hair Flat Iron for Hair Treatment Black Color
column14:
I absolutely LOVE this flat iron! I have had a couple of the really expensive ones and while they may work, they do not compare to this one! I have pretty thick wavy/frizzy or what I like to call a mess of hair! Most other straighteners will straighten my hair but by the end of the day my hair will start to frizz back up or will start to make itself wavy and forget about sleeping on it! When I got this flat iron free in exchange to review I got so excited to try it that I did my hair later than I should have and decided to go to bed. The next morning my hair was still extremely straight and I had no frizz! I could not believe it!

Another thing that really surprised me about this flat iron is how fast it got hot! Sure, most flat iron companies will tell you it gets hot in seconds, but you can't really tell when it is done. Even with digital displays it wont tell you when it is done heating up. This one not only tells you when it is at the right temperature, but it also shows you how fast it is heating up. Within about 30 seconds it is above 400 degrees! It also stays hot while in use which is great and the buttons are in the perfect place so that you don't accidentally turn it off in the middle of a strand.

My favorite part about this flat iron that I HATE about my other ones is that it has little guides (look in picture) on the outsides of the plates. Nothing is worse than trying to straighten your hair than having some of your hair get stuck in-between the plates and the handle and it snagging your hair, or when you have to re-do a strand because half of it fell out of the plates. The guides keep your hair in place and keeps them from getting stuck. I am completely in awe of this flat iron and have been talking about it non-stop to my friends. It really is a great product for a great price and if you are looking for a great flat iron you should really check this one out!
