column13: My go-to moisturizer all throughout my pregnancy
column14:
Almond oil was my saving grace throughout my pregnancy! I wanted to use a safe moisturizer that I knew didn't have any harmful chemicals and since you can eat almond oil, I was totally comfortable using it as a moisturizer. I started using this a few weeks after I found out I was pregnant and was super-generous when using it on my belly. I also didn't get a single stretch mark! I know they say that is totally genetic, but I have stretch marks on my hips from a growth spurt as a teenager, so I'm a believer that the sweet almond oil helped!

FYI, since I was so generous when applying throughout my pregnancy (at least 2 times a day), I made sure to wear a tank underneath my clothes for the day, just to be sure my outer clothes didn't get stained, since there was a little oil that soaked through during the day.

Fast shipping and would totally purchase again!

column6: Crest Pro-Health Clean Mint Toothpaste
column13: like my taste buds were gone
column14: I used Crest Pro Health for several years with out a problem.  Then, I got a weird spot on my tongue several months ago.  The spot was smooth, like my taste buds were gone.  It didn't hurt, so I ignored it.  I went to the dentist last week and he diagnosed me with a condition called Geographic Tongue.  He also asked what type of toothpaste I used.  When I told him, he wasn't surprised.  He recommended that I stop using Prohealth immediately, and said my tongue condition would probably improve.  He was right!  After 3 days of using a different toothpaste, my tongue condition is gone!  The dentist said he used to give it out in the office, but about 20% of patients experienced problems after using it.

column6: Braun Silk-Ã©pil 7 Wet and Dry Epilator, White
column14:
I think experiences with this product are going to vary wildly depending on the type of hair and skin each person has, so I'll start by saying that I have extremely sensitive skin, prone to razor-burn and ingrown hairs, plus my hair tends to grow back at an very fast rate, so I am probably not an ideal candidate for epilation. Also used this for my legs, I haven't yet tried it on my armpits or bikini line.

First, yes, it's painful; but I'm a big baby about pain, and I was able to stick it out, so I think most people can handle it.

Second, this is not a use-once-a-month-and-forget-it tool. Hair grows back fast enough that I have to do touch-ups with it every single day. However the regrowth is sporadic, so it's not really bad doing the daily maintenance.

Third, my legs are not nearly as smooth as after a close shave. Most hairs are plucked, but some will be clipped instead, plus there are always some that are too short for the tool to grab. No matter how much time I take, I always still have a bit of stubbly texture left behind. Not nearly as prickly as shaving stubble, but definitely not silky smooth. I also have to use the tool at night before bed rather than in the morning, as my legs will be covered with little red welts from the plucking for a few hours after using it.

Overall, I have been using this for almost a year, and I think I prefer it to shaving, but only because my razor burn was painful and unsightly. This is no great solution, but it's better than razors for someone with skin as bad as mine. At least until I can afford laser treatments.

column6: Hydrating Argan Oil Hair Mask and Deep Conditioner By Arvazallia for Dry or Damaged Hair - 8.45 Oz
column14:
I have to say this is the best conditioning product I have ever used.

I have thick, naturally wavy hair that has been a nightmare my entire life. It does what it wants, it gets extremely frizzy in both humid and dry conditions and it tangles easily. In the summer it's even worse because I'm in the pool every day and the chlorine really takes it's toll.

I've tried so many different conditioners I've lost count. Some work ok, some don't work at all and same made things worse. I've tried other products with Argan oil in them too and, while better than most, they still weren't amazing. I found this product here last year during the summer when my ends were fried crispy from chlorine. I didn't think anything would make that much of a difference but after reading all the reviews I decided to give it a shot. I am so happy I did.

I use just a little once or twice a week as a quick conditioner and then when my hair starts really frizzing and look dull and damaged - in the summer from the chlorine and in the winter from the dry air - I slather it on and leave it in for several hours. When I rinse and dry after that it's like I have different hair. No frizz, no crispiness - it's soft, silky and smells great! I also get far fewer tangles than I used to and the ones I do get are much easier to comb out, which is a big plus for me.

I've seen a couple of reviews here saying the product left their hair greasy or it was too heavy. I have to guess they are not rinsing it out well enough after using. I could see that happening if you don't rinse properly. But I've been using it for over a year now, I always make sure to rinse it out completely and I have never experienced that problem, even after leaving it in for hours. No greasiness, no heaviness, just soft, silky, awesome feeling hair.

If you're like me - and have tried everything and almost given up on finding something that works - give this a shot. I almost guarantee you'll be glad you did. I know I am!be glad you did. I know I am!

column6: NuJu Revitalizing Eye Gel For Dark Circles Under Eyes, Puffiness, Crows Feet and Wrinkles 15g Contains C4-Peptide-3
column14:
As someone who suffers from chronic insomnia (and the lovely, inescapable dark raccoon circle eyes that come with it), I was pretty excited to try this. Iâ€™ve only used it for one day, and the gel is pleasant enough to use, but what I want to bring up is the disparity between the ingredients that are advertised for Nuju Revitalizing Eye Gel, and the actual ingredients. Iâ€™ll break this down the best I can.

Right off the bat I noticed that this product claims to be paraben free, but has a number of contradicting Ingredients: Ethylparaben, Butylparaben, Propylparaben, Isobutylparaben. This could be a major problem for anyone with allergies or sensitivities. This product also claims to have time released retinol, which is notably missing from the ingredient list. Iâ€™ve listed almost every ingredient in this eye cream, and its function, below. Personally I think this will be useful for moisturizing, and perhaps a temporary rejuvenated look, but it doesnâ€™t seem to pack enough punch to tackle my under eye circles. Because of the disparity between advertised ingredients and the actual, Iâ€™m giving this two stars. Keep in mind I donâ€™t claim to be a scientist. Just going off of easily available information.

Generally only high concentrations have substantial effects on skin, but thought to help reduce swelling and inflammation among other things)

column14:
I suffer from constant spasms on my right trapezium so I'm always looking for all sorts of things that may help, aside from actual medication. This concept is a bit new for me though. It is small and more like a liquid type of Bengay. The smell is very mentholated like all other muscle rubs. The size is more like something you would carry in your purse. It's not a big roll on. It's more like a perfume or pulse point oil kind of thing. At first I was a bit disappointed because of the size of the product but then I realize I have a better use for it if I keep it in my purse. I actually like the smell so I might even use it as a pulse point rollerball. When it comes to effectivity, I received today and I've already applied it twice. I have to say I was pleasantly surprised that this little thing actually provided relief. Honestly, I didn't expect it to work too well but the liquid consistency and the rollerball work quite well. In my case, I did have to use the small rollerball over a large area but its still nice for traveling and for keeping in my purse.

column13: THIS URBANXY BEARD OIL WORKS WELL ON SENSITIVE SKIN
column14:
My oldest son has very sensitive skin so we have to be careful what he uses. This UrbanXY beard oil is made with 100% natural products, so he thought it would be ok to try. He keeps a beard because shaving cream irritates his face and he hates to have rashes on his skin. We opened the bottle to smell it but we really could not smell anything. He used the pump to get just a little of the oil out and rubbed it all over his beard and even on his skin under his beard. His beard looked smooth and actually a little longer where the oil smoothed it out so much. He liked that it looked longer and felt so soft. I kept waiting for him to say it was bothering him but he didn't mention anything. After a few hours I asked him If his face felt ok and he responded it felt fine and he liked how soft his skin felt under the beard. The next day he still did not have any irritation so he is still using the beard oil. I looked at the ingredients and it includes argan oil, jojoba oil, and coconut oil. I actually put a little bit in my hair just to see what it would do and left it in there for several hours then washed it. My hair seemed to lay better because there was less frizz. So my son and I are sharing this beard oil. I am very pleased, my son likes it and it is not irritating him. Plus, I can condition my hair with it also.
I received this product at no cost in return for an honest and unbiased review.

column6: Nexxus Conditioner, Keraphix 13.5 oz
column14: I have fine, straight, color treated hair that I have to wash and dry daily. With a straight hairstyle I only need a flat iron to tame the ends, which causes dryness, breakage and color fading. I have tried a number of products with OK results and found this one to be no different than any other keratin conditioner containing hydrolyzed keratin.  Hydrolyzed means that the keratin has been broken down to theoretically result in better absorption by the hair. Unfortunately, there is no longer enough "true" keratin to make a real difference in repairing damage and/or split ends.  For what this stuff costs, you can get the same results from any conditioner with hydrolyzed Keratin. If you want keratin you need it oxidized (read the label), which is not widely available in the US. I have found it only in Paul Mitchell Wild Ginger which is a wonderful product (no more flat iron) costing about the same as Nexxus.

column13: I wanted to not like it, but I do
column14:
I've always liked Axe products. Despite being a good product, great packaging, and smelling good, they didn't let success get to their head and blow up the price. That said, I haven't been a big fan of multi-function bath cleansers. It's the coating they leave that just makes it feel like you still need a shower.

However, I think they have corrected that with this product. In spite of my expectations, I actually felt very clean after using it from head to toe. My hair wasn't oily and my skin didn't feel waxy as I honestly expected. Being a little older my skin tends to be a bit dryer, so the moisturizing aspects of the product left my skin feeling pretty normal instead of dried out. And while I still retain a good head of hair, I am cognizant of plugging hair roots with detergent residues and stopping hair growth. Axe 3 in 1 leaves no such residue.

I'll be back for more

column6: Goldwell Dualsenses Extra Rich Color Duo (25.4 oz each)
column13: Keeps my Goldwell Topchic color fresh
column14:
I've been using the Joico Color Endure line for a few years. I LOVE the way Joico makes my hair feel; however, the color dulls a bit with my (almost) daily cleansing. Because I use Goldwell Topchic color, I figured I'd give the Goldwell shampoo/conditioner set a try.

I have mixed feelings about the Extra Rich Color Duo. The shampoo definitely cleans my hair, and the conditioner really helps to keep the color in and makes my hair super shiny. Thing is, I am accustomed to conditioners making hair feel soft and smooth--this conditioner does not do that. It doesn't have that smooth, moisturizing feel that most other conditioners have. So I am conflicted because the results are there, but I don't have the satisfaction of running my fingers through my wet, slick, slippery locks while in the shower. In fact, I can't detangle my hair in the shower with this conditioner, which seems odd, but there you go.

5 (five) stars for results: shiny, color-saturated, healthy hair.
-1 star for "sticky" and tangled hair... weird

column13: overall a nice shaver for the price
column14: Norelco Shaver review  I gave this the full 30-day test to make sure my skin had time to adjust to the shaver. Overall, it does a good job, at a fair price. What I liked best:  Quiet operation - it's really quiet, compared to shavers I've tried from other brands, and also compared to other (lower-priced) Norelco shavers. Simple cleaning - all you have to do is place it on the cleaning unit and let it do its thing. Decent shave - it gives a good, close shave for a shaver of this kind  Things I don't like so much: Noisy cleaning - while the shaver is quiet, the cleaning device is not. It's quite loud, and runs for some minutes by itself. This can be annoying, depending on when you decide to place the shaver on the cleaning device. (Don't do it if anyone is sleeping.)  Trimmer comb is awkward - something about the way this attaches feels counter-intuitive; definitely took some getting used to to get the angles right when trimming a beard.

I don't think I would personally buy this product again if it weren't basically the same price as Gold Bond spray. So in conclusion, I would say try Gold Bond as it is readily available everywhere and if bothers you or you are sensitive to it give this a shot. Or just give this a shot. It was the number one pick in the article I read and Gold Bond was #2 but I think that also had to do with sensitivity with the spray. Just make sure it's the recommended 9" or so away when you spray and you should be fine. But with this product there is no need for any fear. column6: Bed Head Curling/styling Iron, Purple, BH327
column14: I would like to start by stating: I have never ever curled my hair with any type of iron before. So that says something about the learning curve for this product. I watched a 7 minute tutorial on YouTube to get an idea of how it worked before trying it out. I used this iron on clean un-blow-dried hair, with no product. I used the lowest heat setting and held each curl wrapped between the beads for 40 seconds. Curling my entire head took no more than 30 minutes. Overall I would say the results are not too shabby for someone with zero experience. I didn't use the glove because it made it a bit awkward to section and grab locks of hair, but I didn't get burned all the same. The kickstand is easy to operate with one hand. The resting mat is the perfect size for my small counter space. And I love the super long cord with the swivel end connected to the iron. This is definitely something I will use regularly to give my hair some quick texture.

column6: Magnetic Eye Mask Plus Ear Plugs for Great Sleeping Offers Relief from Migraines; Ideal for children; Relax and Fall Asleep Quickly; Get A Good Night's Sleep and Wake up Refreshed Now!
column13: I was looking for a sleep mask to block out light since my husband likes to leave the tv on at night and I like a pitch black ro
column14: I should but I never write reviews but have to on this one!  I was looking for a sleep mask to block out light since my husband likes to leave the tv on at night and I like a pitch black room.  I tried a couple others but they were either too hot or the last one the strap was too tight (not adjustable) and caused a headache.  So when I came across this one I thought I'd give it a try.  I'm 33 years old with a few fine lines around my eyes so I thought I would try it.  Also, i have what a nurse told me once, longer than normal eye bags.  The length from my eye socket to the top of my cheek bone is longer than the normal so there was nothing medically I could really do about my puffy bags except surgery. Any injectable fillers would actually make them worse.  So, first night I slept with this mask, I woke up this morning without the normal headache and neck pain.  I usually take Tylenol as soon as I wake and crack my neck all day to release the tension.  Didn't have to do that this morning.  I read the Pamphlet that came with the mask to my husband and bragged about no headache, etc.  When I said removed the puffiness around the eyes, he said "your eyes aren't puffy".  He is usually a smart ass by nature so I looked at him and said whatever he said "no they really aren't!  You aren't scaring me this morning."  I looked in the mirror and I am amazed! I really thought my only option was going to be BOTOX injections in my armpits. THIS STUFF WORKED. I have not put the claim of it lasting a week to the test, however I have gone easily 4 days with one application and it has held up. At most, even on extremely warm days I get only a very small spot of sweat in the armpit. NOTHING like the sweat stains I used to get that leave me walking around like I have T-Rex arms because I don't dare move them. column13: This is the CC cream you have been looking for!
column14:
If you've tried other CC creams without much success: then this is the one for you. This is a CC cream that is CC!!!

Absolutely the best CC cream, in my opinion. Well worth the price, as a little goes a long way. No apparent fragrance. Not drying at all. This is a matte-finish but with a fresh, dewy look. Absolutely a MUST have for the 40+ women.

Pro's:
Great texture, not too thin, not too goopy, smooth and easy to go on. I like that it has sunscreen in it. I wear it alone or with some cheek blusher and contour. Surprisingly, no re-application throughout the day.

Con: (Just one) This is the only reason for the 4-star rating.
The shade is quite a bit lighter than expected. After reading the reviews, I did order a shade UP. I am blonde with a fair complexion. Normally a "Light" shade in any product line works well for me, but this product's "Medium" is more of a "Light" If you were to wear a foundation over the CC+ cream, then perhaps the shades are correct.

column14:
I was excited to receive the Crest Pro-Health Daily Two-Step Toothpaste from Bzz Agent to try and review. I have tried several whitening toothpastes prior to this one and never noticed any difference.
Crest Pro Health comes in two tubes and requires brushing twice which seemed slightly inconvenient at first but I quickly got used to it once my mouth and teeth started to feel cleaner and look whiter. I also noticed that my morning breath seemed better and I didn't have a sour taste in my mouth. My husband also used the toothpaste and was very happy with how his teeth looked and how clean his mouth fell.
I do have to warn everybody about one thing - the taste wasn't the greatest and brushing second time without rinsing first didn't help either.
Otherwise I would recommend Crest Pro Health HD Daily Two Step toothpaste to everybody that cares about the health of their teeth.

column14: For me, the biggest difference between soaps marketed to men as opposed to the fairer sex is the scent.  Most "men's" soaps I have tried have been subtle and nondescript.  So I found it odd that this soap has a strong floral scent that filled the bathroom (and some of the hallway) upon opening it.  Once in use, the smell does not linger on the skin so that is a good thing from my point of view.  If have sensitivities to smells, you probably will not want to try this scent un-smelled off the internet.  But as a soap, it does its job well.  It leaves my skin soft and refreshed after each use.  One other thing I have noticed in other men's soap is most of them now have those smell microbeads things, but this Dove Soap does not have those, so if you hate those things, you will like this soap (though I feel cleaner with those little exfoliates included in the soap).  Overall, this is just a run of the mill average bar of soap.

column6: Eye Circles Less Apparent, Mimi Fontaine Eye Cream Reduces Look of Dark Circles for Men & Women 100% Guaranteed - Best Under Eye Cream - Anti Aging Under Eye Moisturizer for Reducing the Appearance of
column13: Impressive ingredients: Hydrolyzed collagen, Hydrolyzed elastin, Licorice root extract, Vit E, Retinyl palmitate.
column14:
This is the first time trying this product. It's a bit expensive, but I received a discount for an honest review. It does work....slowly. I have seen improvement. It's been about 3 weeks from when I started using the product. I use it twice a day. The application dispenser is excellent that avoids wastefulness of tubes. It doesn't have an unusual scent that was noticeable. I don't like creams with odors especially when applying to my face so I really appreciate a clean scent. It absorbs quickly and my own concealer applies evenly afterwards. It felt gentle to my skin without any stinging or other untoward reactions. This is a paraben free product without any animal testing.
The ingredients are impressive and this description is found on their Mimi Fontaine homepage:
Hydrolyzed collagen - Hydrolyzed collagen plumps up the skin and reduces the look of fine lines, wrinkles, and bags under the eyes.
Hydrolyzed elastin - Elastin lets the skin resume its shape after stretching/contracting, as is it does when you smile. The small molecules of hydrolyzed elastin penetrate the skin's surface and improve its elasticity. so you can keep your naturally beautiful smile without worrying about "crowsfeet" forming at the corners of your eyes.Contains licorice root extract - Licorice root extract is a natural ingredient traditionally used to treat overpigmentation caused by inflammation, eczema, and other skin disorders. It produces a significant improvement on dark circles under the eyes.Contains vitamin E - Vitamin E supplements the skin's natural antioxidant defenses and provides protection against ultraviolet radiation and other free radicals. This makes the skin around the eyes less likely to age prematurely and wrinkle. Also contains retinyl palmitate. Retinyl palmitate is a form of vitamin A. Studies have shown it safe when used with ordinary care to avoid overexposure to ultraviolet light. When absorbed into the skin, it promotes collagen production and cell rejuvenation, and decreases pore size, so the skin around your eyes looks younger.

A little bit of it goes a long way and I think this will last a few months which helps in justifying the expense of reordering it in the future. I look forward to seeing how this continues to work with consistent use.

column6: Shea Butter
column14: I LOVE THIS PRODUCT!!!  I am having some hormonal issues with my skin, so I decided to try this instead of spending a ton of money on a dermatologist.  I am SO glad I did!  I purchased this about a month ago, along with some pure tea tree oil and some pure coconut oil.  The shea butter came exactly as it was advertised, and all 3 products were packed very well in an Amazon cardboard box, so I had no issues with melting, damage, or anything else.  The mixture I created with these ingredients is AWESOME!!  The tea tree oil has a very strong smell, but the shea butter and the coconut oil offset it somewhat. This product works great as an everyday moisturizer (I use it every night and every morning, but you may want to let it sit for a while before putting on makeup if you have naturally oily skin like I do), and I love the way it makes my skin look and feel.  My husband also uses it for his trouble spots, so it works for the men folk as well.  This product gets a definite recommendation from me!

column14: I ran out of my last retinol product and after searching all the retinol moisturizer reviews here, I chose this one. I have been using it for several weeks now and I love the result. I am 48 years old and while I have always had great skin, thanks to good genes, I was noticing some changes and inconsistencies related to age. :( It happens. This product did not burn my skin. The last type I used did, but I think it was because I had never put retinol on my skin before that. So if this is the first time you have used it, maybe it will sting a bit for the first few applications. This moisturizer goes on smooth and is not greasy at all. It absorbs nicely into the skin. I experienced no redness, rashes or blemishes after using. After a few weeks of using this moisturizer, my skin is softer, with a more even tone. The aroma is nice, barely there. The pump action on the dispenser is great. The bottle size is good for gripping. I can, without hesitation, recommend this product.

DISCLAIMER: I used this product exclusively as a face wash.

PROS

+ Pleasant licorice scent that lasts for a while. I've often been complimented on it.

+ I've never had serious problems with acne/pimples, but get them on occasion. Having used this twice a day, it has aided in clearing up my face.
+ It doesn't have a laundry list of ingredients that I can't pronounce.

CONS

- It's pretty expensive so I use it exclusively as a face wash.

SIDE NOTES:

Be sure to properly rinse and ensure that the soap does not remain on your body when you dry off because it will stain your towel and leave it with grey blotches.

column6: ORGANIC Rosehip Oil - 100% Pure Certified Organic Cold Pressed Virgin Rose Hip Seed Oil for Face, Skin, Nails & Hair - BEST NATURAL MOISTURIZER to heal Dry Skin, Scars and Fine Lines - 4 fl. oz
column13: may be diluted, does not share characteristics of true 100% rosehip seed oil
column14:
I'm torn on how to review the Skinology Rosehip Seed Oil. It came nicely packaged, and absorbs quickly into my skin without feeling greasy. If it is indeed 100% pure and cold-pressed, great.

BUT.

100% pure cold-pressed rosehip seed oil should have the following qualities among others:
-deep orange/amber color
-thick oil
-fragrant scent (that some describe as rosy)

However, the Skinology oil I received is:
-nearly clear, with a very slight yellow tint (it's clearer than vegetable oil!) I can't post an external link on Amazon for what color it should be, but if you search Google Images it's easy to find examples.
-runny (same consistency as vegetable oil)
-no discernable scent.

I am concerned that this oil is diluted with something else. If just one of the above were lacking, I would write it off as difference in processing technique or something. But even if it were 100% rosehip seed oil but heavily processed, it should still retain at least a little color, thickness, and scent.

Without having confidence in what this oil may be adulterated with, I'm not comfortable risking it on my skin or scalp.

(I am including a photo with this review of the color of the rosehip oil I received. As you can see from comparing it to photos of quality pure oil, this does not look right!)

I received a free sample of this product in exchange for testing, inspecting and reviewing it. I received no other compensation for my review and always give my honest and unbiased opinion of each product. I welcome your questions & comments on my experience.

column14: This product absolutely does not remove skin tags.  I wanted to remove ONE, TINY skin tag on my chest, and this stuff didn't do it.  I applied it diligently 2 to 3 times a day for a week and a half.  Judging from similar reports online, the tag should have disappeared.  For its small size, it should have just shriveled up and fallen off (or have been easy enough to pluck off).  Nope...nothing....still have it on my chest.  And the best part was that the area surrounding the tag turned very rough and red...clearly a sign of skin irritation.  My next strategy will be to use Dawn dishwashing liquid.  Allegedly, that's how my grandmother removed her skin tags.  Long story short:  avoid this product at all costs if you're only using it for skin tag removal.

column14:

I love all of their scents. A note is that they smell very good in the perfumey way of companies who use ton of artificial scents as opposed to the earthier scent of companies who use pure essential oils. This may be a drawback or may not be a drawback, depending on what your personal preferences are. It is also *very* moisturizing and leaves a silky feel to the skin, a definite bonus if you have very dry skin like me.
So why not 5 stars? The pricing is completely out of control. You can go to a drugstore and get these products for $4 each, or $12 for 3. The incentive in buying in bulk is to save money, but you actually waste money at this price. I bought it knowing this, because I have free same day delivery and no time to run out to buy this, but I did feel duped

column14: I received this brush a couple days ago in good condition. This is not my first boar bristle brush, but my first brush from this company. The bristle were soft grade like I had hoped. So, not salon quality which I wasn't expecting anyway.) the brush is nice to look at, but I'm not positive this is real wood...I think it's wood but it seems to have some sort wood-look "sticker" on it to enhance the grain with a clear coat on top of that. The size is perfect. Not huge paddle type, but not pocket size. Just right. The logo on the handle is smaller than pictured and may wear off after some use because it's not indented in the wood. All these things are minor, and I didn't expect Mason Pearson status. I just wanted a nice brush with genuine soft boar and no nylon that I can afford and that's what I got. :) Overall decent quality brush. column6: Crest Pro-Health HD Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Healthier Mouth via Daily Two-Step System - 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column13: It whitened my teeth in the same amount of time I normally would brush.
column14: When I got a free box of the Crest Pro-Health HD Daily Two Step Toothpaste from Crest through bzzagent, I was skeptical.  I had used whitening toothpastes before without much difference and I had tried the strips and I never seemed to be able to follow through on those to get them to work well.  I had a box of strips that had been sitting, unused, next to my sink for a few months, so I decided to give the Crest Pro-Health HD Toothpaste a try. I read the directions, which I am glad I did, because you use the step 1 for a minute (the fluoride toothpaste to protect against cavities & gingivitis) and then you spit it out, but you do not rinse (It took a few rounds of this before it because second nature not to rinse with water). Then you use the Step 2 for a minute (a whitening gel that contains hydrogen peroxide).  You rinse after this step is complete.  Within a few days, I thought my teeth looked whiter.  I drink a lot of tea and some soda and my teeth tend to lose their shine and get a bit of a dingy look to them.  After I had been using the Crest Pro Health HD for a couple weeks, my mom came into town and one of the first things she said to me was to ask if I had had my teeth whitened.  The product is very simple to use and it produced results for me.  You brush your teeth as long as you normally would (two minutes total each brushing), so there's no added time or inconvenienced like you can have with strips or other whitening methods. I am also not a fan of my toothpaste flavors, but this has a light minty taste that did not bother me at all. My first box may have been free, but I have continued using it on my own.

column6: PURA D'OR Anti-Hair Loss Shampoo (Gold Label), Effective Solution for Hair Thinning & Breakage, NEW & IMPROVED PUMPS, 16 Fluid Ounce (Packaging May Vary)
column13: I thought this was maybe more like snake oil
column14: Okay, I'm not really one to buy into hype.  To be honest, I thought this was maybe more like snake oil.  It's hard for me to believe something that's organic would have anything in it that would actually work, but I figured the reviews were good, and it wasn't a ton of money.  I'm a natural skeptic, so I expected there had to be some tiny result after a couple weeks.  I'm 44 and still have about 75% of my hair. No obvious bald spot, just a bit of receeding and thinning.  It's gotten worse this last year.  My dad has a thin bit up top, but my brother is completely bald and has been for many years.  Anyway, it works.  I cannot conceivably think there is any coincidence.  By growth length of the new short hairs, it had to have started working day 1. Seriously.  So, my hair is coarse and straight.  Used to be super thick.  I have a part on the side, and noticed I could see a couple inches back on my scalp as it thinned out.  Now, it's getting harder to see after a couple weeks.  There is a ton of new hairs now half an inch long.  They are a little bit finer than my normal hair, but they're in there, and hundreds of em and seems  like they're getting thicker.  Now, one thing that is a little disappointing is that they're not growing in the sides of my forehead where the hair stopped growing entirely.  Seems like they're only growing in places where my scalp didn't totally give up.  So, I'm disappointed I didn't start this shampoo a long time ago, but I am thrilled it's a product that actually works!  I wash my face, then shampoo up, then wash everything else and shave in the shower. By that time it's been about 2 minutes and I rinse out the shampoo.  Great product.  Now if they had a pill I could swallow that would help me lose weight....

column13: For those who have a child with sensory issues, this is a GREAT brush! Knots out in 10-minutes and no fusses.
column14:
AMAZING BRUSH!!!
Our daughter has Aspergers and is EXTREMELY sensitive when I am brushing her hair. The slightest, "tug" and she is 'outta there! I had to do something to assist me and found this brush, liked the reviews and ordered it. It was here in 2-days!

First, the brush is very ergonomic for the person who is using the brush. I didn't drop the brush nor did it slip.
Second, there were only a few "tugs" as I brushed her out following the morning in the pool.
Third, it took a TOTAL of 10-minutes to comb/brush her out using this brush alone. Incredible. I attached pictures so viewers can see the before and after. No tricks...in 10-minutes, that knotted mess became a smooth body of hair and without the slightest pulls/tugs. Further, our daughter said as I was brushing, "This feels good!". Wow. WOW! She despises having her hair brushed- I must do it while she is watching a nature program to hold her attention.
Finally, when checking the brush when we finished, there were no hairs that had pulled out during the brushing.
OH, and finally, finally, all knots were removed- even the stubborn knots and all within 10 minutes. Yesterday, it took a full hour to get through her hair. I had contemplated cutting it to her shoulders but she refuses...and now, I don't think this will be necessary at all.

Thank you, Crave Naturals for this product...coming from a mom with a child that has sensory issues, this brush is fantastic! I will definitely buy this again!

column6: Sebamed Liquid Face and Body Wash, for Sensitive Skin 33.8-Fluid Ounces Bottle
column13: Great body wash for those with dry, itchy, sensitive skin
column14:
I have sensitive skin. Well, actually, seborrheic dermatitis, which means my skin is not only sensitive but gets pretty dry and flaky. I also try to use products that don't test on animals. And for bathroom products, that's not very easy to find. Well, maybe it is at Whole Foods but not at a regular grocery store. So, I was surprised when I was at Costco and came across this body wash and that it had the cruelty free icon on it.

Initially, I was put off by the label and the name. It just seemed very clinical and medicinal. But I figured I'd give it a shot, and I'm glad I did. Though I've been committed to trying cruelty free products, I've unfortunately found that some of those products aggravated my skin (and yes, I realize it's possibly because they don't have the same testing standards as the products that do test on animals). So, maybe a more clinical kind of product is what I needed.

Some have commented on the smell. I think the closest comparison I could come up with when trying to describe the smell is that it's kind of like baby powder, but not quite as good. But certainly not unpleasant, at least to me. But my focus is on the results. When I used this, my skin felt great. Not itchy, not flaky. Just moist and clean.

Having gone through all the products I've tried with the conditions that I have with my skin, and to have such positive results, I can't speak highly enough of this product. Maybe if I didn't have issues with my skin, I'd be somewhat indifferent about it. But it has made such a difference for me, that I am solidly in the Sebamed camp.

I live in Las Vegas and have visited the distributions I myself personally have bought products directly from them in fact and this was never mentioned. In my own particular case I applied the manly guy darkest brown. Be careful of this color in particular because it is not really a dark brown at all it is literally a jet black it is the blackest of black and is considered a level "one" on the scale of current coloring. It made my hair literally eight Gothic black color that I have had to live with now for close to eight months as I grow my hair long unfortunately I'm going to have to live with these results longer than the average person because I'm unwilling to cut off the five or so inches of hair the remains of this color. If you're going to use this get at least two shades lighter and I'll repeat that two shades lighter than you "think" you're going to need. Don't listen to the packaging or the people at Hannah King. Once this stuff gets deposited in your hair it is impossible to remove. I went to literally 10 salons and smoke to very high level color experts and the indicated that there is no product on the market anywhere including home remedies such as olive oil baking soda lemon and a dozen other "home remedies" that will work. In fact the color removers on the market such as eliminate which are used in the very high-end salons are not powerful to remove this product. Another way to put it that the permanent hair colors that are used by stylists that have peroxide and ammonia are much easier to remove then hand it is Hannah is virtually permanent and believe me I mean permanent because I spent months and months trying to get this out. Even a heavy bleaching would not remove the product though I opted not to do this because it would be too destructive on the hair. Some stylists mentioned to me that Henna chemical composition is such that any "color remover" that would be sufficient enough to at least make some difference would have to have so much bleach and ammonia and peroxide in it that my hair would personally fallout. If I can save someone from the trouble of putting this stuff in their hair hopefully this will help you. So if you have very dark hair let's say you're a dark brown start with a light brown if you really feel compelled to use Hannah but at this point I would never recommend it to anyone including myself but at least that way if it's a little darker than you expect you of a chance to recover from it. Again my advice would be at least two shades possibly three shades lighter. So if you're dark hair go with a light brown not a medium brown a light brown if you're a medium brown I would be very careful even ordering the light brown product as it made dye your hair to dark. I started with a very dark brown hair so I went with the darkest brown which one would presume would end up making my hair "dark brown" obviously. But instead it made it check ebony black so be careful.

column13: My Blotches Are Already Dissapearing since applying this Kriri Honey Cream!!
column14:
I have had an issue with blotches appearing on my upper arms and chest area for a while now. The doctors were unable to define what was causing them, so when offered the opportunity to receive this Kiri Honey Cream at a reduced cost in exchange for testing and review, I figured it couldn't hurt to try it.
It arrived within 2 days of placing my order, and upon first inspection I was very impressed with the thick creamy appearance of the Honey Cream inside the nice looking jar.
I rubbed a little on the areas where my blotches are the worst and was pleased to see it was well absorbed and didn't leave my skin feeling or looking at all greasy.
The very light fragrance is pleasant and not at all overpowering. It dissipated within minutes of application.
I repeated the applications 3 times a day for the next 3 days and I am extremely impressed to see that the blotches are diminishing!
I have not used anything else on my skin so I have to contribute the improvement to this fabulous Kiri Honey Cream and it's ingredients.
I will continue to apply it 3 times a day and update my review in a week or so.
Hoping that what I have experienced already is an indication that this product is going to be the answer to my prayers of having soft, smooth, blotch free skin and giving it a 5 Star recommendation!

column6: [USA] SAPO Organic Bamboo Charcoal Soap Bar - Natural US Handmade - Helps with Acne, Psoriasis, Eczema - Has Coconut Oil, Oatmeal, Shea Butter - Leaving Your Face and Body Fresh and Clean
column13: I Love it, Great Scent, Fresh Clean Feeling After Shower
column14:
From what Iâ€™ve read bamboo charcoal has been used for a long time for getting clean, hundreds of years in fact, I didnâ€™t know this, but itâ€™s supposedly very beneficial to you and your skin. The bamboo charcoal is an all natural acne cure as itâ€™s more absorbent and thus gives your skin a better deep cleaning than traditional soaps. The soap also eliminates bacteria and it can absorb toxins and impurities from you skin and itâ€™s a natural exfoliator. Iâ€™ve been using it daily and I love it, itâ€™s got a great scent and you really do feel cleaner after your shower.

The package for the Sapo bamboo charcoal soap is a just a small brown box with a nice looking label on the front with the ingredients listed there for you which are all natural.

When you take it out of the box the first thing that strikes you is the look of it, itâ€™s rough, itâ€™s course and itâ€™s black in color. It does have an scent of grapefruit that is immediately noticeable. The soap is made from only a few ingredients: activate bamboo charcoal, olive oil, coconut oil, palm oil, sunflower oil, safflower oil, shea butter, sea salt, oatmeal powder and grapefruit essential oil. No hard to pronounce chemicals in that list of ingredients at all.

Sapo soap is artisanal or handmade so itâ€™s not smooth like commercial soaps. The soap has lots of bumps and bubbles in it, itâ€™s not a perfectly formed block. Yes itâ€™s a block but what I mean is that it doesnâ€™t look like soap you would buy in the store, you can tell itâ€™s handmade.

The soap is about 3.5x2x1 inches in dimensions and itâ€™s about 4 ounces in weight.

We have five people in our household, me, my wife and three kids and we all tried it.

My wife didnâ€™t like it, she said she didnâ€™t like the smell, my wife is picky though, she only like what she likes and itâ€™s hard to get her to try new things at all.

My three kids loved it, they thought it was neat to use black soap to get clean with.

I personally love this soap, I love the scent and I really did feel cleaner after my shower.

The soap does seem to produce more lather than other bar soaps. I normally use Irish Spring soap, and the Sapo soap has much more lather than that does.

It is kind of odd at first when you lather up your rag to see a black tinge to the rag and lather. I was half expecting to see the black charcoal color on my skin honestly.

I was also expecting the soap to be gritty but itâ€™s not, the lather is smooth and almost soft really. The lather has a different and softer texture and feel to it than my normal commercially made soap, itâ€™s lighter and more fluffy really.

The Sapo Bamboo Charcoal Bar Soap is a great soap in my opinion, I love the scent and I really did feel cleaner after my shower.

The only complaint I might have is that the bar is rather small, it only lasted week, but then again five of use were using it everyday.

All natural and organic is a good thing I think, it had to be better for you than all the chemicals we expose ourselves to.

I can highly recommend the Sapo soap, once you try it youâ€™ll love it. I think I need to order some more.

Pros:
+Lots of lather
+Great scent
+Organic

Cons:
-None really

column6: Waterpik Ultra Cordless Plus Water Flosser WP450 1 ea
column13: Several years after I bought it, the product is ...
column14:
Several years after I bought it, the product is still usable. I've had the often reported charger contacts corrosion problem just over a year after I bought the item. Repaired it myself. Two years later, the stock battery became weak, wouldn't hold a charge for a while. The charging circuit in this device is way too primitive. There is a schottky diode between the battery and the charging contacts, which drops voltage from the charger (3V) down to 2.45V, that's all. This prevents overcharging the battery, however the battery is never charged to full capacity. I've replaced the ni-mh battery in mine with a cheap new ni-mh battery from China, removed the diode from the circuit, and replaced the charger with a cheap universal ni-mh charger from China. Used an automotive miniature waterproof connector (AMP SuperSeal 2-position) as a connector, to prevent corrosion of the charger terminals. By the way, every time I had to service the electrics in this device, I had to disassemble everything, since the electrics are the deepest hidden part in the case.

column6: Clean & Clear Essentials
column13: perfect for oily skin in summer
column14:
This review is for the deep cleaning toner.

This is so like something I would have used in high school (I'm now 37). But it is summer in Georgia and it is hot. My skin is getting oily. So I really wanted an alcohol-based toner to use. This one was inexpensive. And it is effective.

I, personally, do not find this drying. Perhaps it is because I moisturize well, or because my skin is oily. If you have skin that's extremely sensitive, especially to alcohol, you'd best avoid this. But if you want a way to make your skin feel refreshed and get rid of some oil, this is definitely worth a look.

I use this after cleansing and before serum (I follow the serum with moisturizer and, if it's daytime, SPF and primer, not necessarily in that order). It really helps get all the grime off that cleansing missed (including traces of liquid foundation).

Here are the ingredients since I didn't see them on the product page:

Active Ingredients: Salicylic Acid (0.5%)

Inactive Ingredients: Water, Alcohol, Glycerin, Isoceteth 20, PEG 32, Sodium Citrate, Fragrance, Propylene Glycol, Dimethicone Propyl PG Betaine, Benzophenone 4, Algae Extract, Aloe Barbadensis Leaf Extract, Denatonium Benzoate, Blue 1

Not thrilled with the fragrance or dye, although they have not irritated my skin. I note this does not contain witch hazel, so if you are sensitive to that, this may be a product you want to look into. Overall, though, I've been very happy with this and would buy it again.

column6: Schick Hydro 5 Disposable Razors for Men Our Best Disposable Shaving Razor - 3 Count
column13: Very effective and perfect for senstive skin
column14:
I came across my first Hydro 5 when I purchased a pack of [[ASIN:B0056GOHN4 Schick Quattro Titanium Disposable Razors for Men]] that included one of these as a sample. I can make a direct comparison to the Quattro, as well as to wet shaving with a safety razor.

First, the hydrating gel reservoir does not act as a shaving cream or gel - you still need one or the other. It is a feature that is designed to keep your face protected when you go over the same place a few times after the initial stroke that removes the cream or gel.

This razor, like the Quattro, needs a few strokes to break in when you first use it. Mine pulled a little on the first few strokes with the grain, but quickly smoothed out. I think this is a quirk with Schick blades in general because I have never experienced it with a Mach 3 or even a safety razor.

If you generally use shaving cream note that this (and the Quattro) work a lot better with a gel type cream than foam. If you are a wet shaver who occasionally uses disposables for convenience I need to point out that these do not work well at all with shaving soap and a brush.

These take a strong stream of water to clean, which is the only complaint I have. Otherwise this model has proven to be the best disposable, multi-blade razor that I have tried because it is absolutely smooth (after a fast break in) and leaves my sensitive face closely shaved with no rash or other issues.

column6: ACF Sleep Mask & Ear Plug Set â€“ Premium Quality Eye Mask w/ Memory Foam
column13: The perfect sleep mask for me, with some ear plugs tossed in.
column14:
I've been looking for something like this locally for quite awhile. Since I work nights and my master bedroom is almost entirely windowed the sun shining through in the morning has been a huge problem. All the sleep masks I've seen at local retailers have been very cheap looking and often more expensive than this one. When I was given a chance to get this product at a discount in exchange for an honest review I had to order it.

Now that I've had it a few nights I can't find a bad thing to day about it. The mask is padded with a soft foam, almost like memory foam, and has molded spots for your eyes and nose which make it extremely comfortable to wear at night. I was worried that it might slide around on my face as I toss and turn but it seems to stay perfectly in place thanks to the adjustable strap and the molding feature I mentioned. I was also worried about the mask making me sweat and that hasn't been an issue either. The material its made of stays very cool from the time you put it on until the time you take it off.

One thing I think I should mention is that the ear plugs that come with this mask are the type you see in stores for $1 for a pack of 20 or so. They are just the cheap disposable foam type. I use this same type of ear plug at work and we toss them after a day of use. I haven't used the ones included with this mask but I'd expect them to last a week at best. I don't feel its worth docking a star for that since the main reason I bought this was for the sleep mask, which is excellent.

column6: Remington Silk Ceramic Professional Hair Dryer
column13: A very powerful dryer which gives you a lot of control and has a cool air setting which dries without causing damage.
column14:
The Remington Studio Silk dryer is very large and powerful. It comes with 2 attachments, one to focus the air and the other to diffuse it. What I like best about it is the amount of control it gives you, from the choice of heads to the variable heat. It is a good choice for people who use a blow dryer for styling.

I have tried a number of ceramic appliances and this one makes less sense than most. It seems to me that the ceramic coating matters most when it contacts your hair directly. I have never experienced any benefit from any appliance which claimed that it generated ions, and did not notice much of a difference in that regard here either.

It is large, but designed well so that it is comfortable to hold. It has a very solid build and looks like it will hold up well over time. That has always been my experience with Remington products. It's a brand I look to first in a number of areas because I have has consistently good experience with their products.

I had a little folding conair dryer which I liked quite a lot for its' portability. I live in Hawaii and rarely blow dry, using them more when I travel. My daughter went to college in Cleveland and needed it more than I did, so it left with her the last time she visited. This one is more powerful with more features, but considerably less portable. Maybe I can swap with her the next time she visits ;)

It is a very competent dryer with good safety features.

On the pro side:
It is powerful and dries fast.
Has 2 attachments to focus to diffuse the air.
Has 3 heat and 2 speed settings, giving you a lot of control.
Cool air setting allows you to dry without damage
Nice safety features

The biggest down side for me is the size. It is not something I would ever pack with the current charges and limitation on luggage. That makes it a good deal less useful to me since I seldom use a blow dryer at home but do when I travel.

In sum it is a nice blow dryer, very powerful with a good deal of control over heat and speed settings, and attachments which allow you to focus or diffuse the air.

My favorite feature I the cool air setting which dries without causing damage (the main reason I have avoided using blow dryers much in the past). I came back and revised my rating becase this feature makes it more useful than any blow drier I have used, and more likely that I will use it more. I would rather not go to sleep with wet hair and if I can dry without causing damage, this becomes verry much more useful.at and speed settings, and attachments which allow you to focus or diffuse the air. I have raved before about Kanechecom & Silicon Mix, but this is even better than that! as it adds loads of moisture and Kanechcom can make the hair feel like paper (but that makes for super fast flat ironing). Many people with Thyroid issues often have dry brittle hair, please try this before trying those expensive prescription shampoos. I also had a dry brittle crown as I age, and this seemed to take care of it.
Thumbs up if you like my review. I really enjoy giving my honest opinion about things. Add this product line to your hair regime, you won't need anything else!

This body wash has a very subtle smell to it, and it makes your skin feel refreshed after use. The big surprise was that it was better than any shampoo for my hair as well. i have a very sensitive scalp (commonly flares up, lots of dandruff, very scratchy) while most shampoos work to clear dandruff they leave my scalp very red and scratchy this was very soothing, left me dandruff free, and left just enough oils in my hair so that it was easy to style afterwards. This is now the only thing i need to shower with, i use it as my body wash, conditioner and shampoo, and i couldn't be happier!
If i had to find a con it would be that it doesn't bubble as much as artificial body washes

The only reason I purchased it was because I had a growing number of home remedies, lotions, and soaps that were calling for it and I finally gave in. The reason I don't like shea butter is because of the commercial smell that you get from over the counter lotions and scents containing the stuff. column6: Noxzema Ultimate Clear Pads Anti Blemish, 90 ct
column13: Powerful cleanser and exfoliator with a powerful scent. Clear skin is worth holding your breath.
column14:
These textured salicylic acid facial pads work better on my skin than all the others I've tried (Clean n Clear, Biore, etc.) so I'm giving them a 5-star rating. They actually have a rough feel to them, which seems to be more effective on my skin for removing dirt and oil. I tend to have very oily skin, so the gentler alcohol-free cleansing pads I have tried don't work as well for me.

As other reviewers have noted, these pads have an EXTREMELY strong chemical odor. I hold my breath when I use them, wiping over my nose and chin area first, so it dries before I have to breath again haha. I usually fan my face when I inhale again so as not to breathe in the smell. Don't let it scare you, though, if you have very oily skin and don't always have the energy to wash and rinse your face with soap/liquid cleanser and water at the end of the day or first thing in the morning. I suppose it's probably better to actually wash your face at night before bed if you have makeup on, or if you sweat a lot at the gym or work in landscaping or whatever, but when I don't have the energy to do the full routine, I use these pads to remove residue and exfoliate before bed.

Sometimes I use before a shower, as I rinse off the harsher chemicals immediately and follow with a gentle non-soap facial cleanser, to get the exfoliating pore-penetrating effects of the pads without the drying effects.

I am very curious about the ratings of this shaver system. I'm guessing that most of the reviews are done shortly after the shaver was received and put in service. I really wonder what people's response are to this shaver after a period of time. I've used my shaver for approximately 5 months now. I was quite impressed at how close a shave I received when I first got it. However, after a few months, it was taking longer and longer to shave and and the shave was getting less and less close. I clean my unit daily, so I know it doesn't have to do with lack of care. After 5 months, it's taking twice as long to shave as it did at the start--I go over my face again and again in differing directions, and the area on the left and right under my chin will only become close after a lot of abrasive shaving.

On top of that, the differing directions required to get a close shave makes for an arduous task. I have finally concluded after spending a lot of money on this expensive unit that I am going to return to a Philips Norelco shaver. Even if it doesn't shave quite as close over the long haul, the more natural circular shaving motion is much more effective in clearing my face in a reasonable time and without as much abrasion. Also, I don't have to be staring in the mirror all the time to accomplish my morning ritual. In the end, given the reduced efficiency of the Braun over time, the Norelco and Braun shavers end up shaving about at the same level, and perhaps the Norelco even has the nod over the long haul.

I think this type of product, like all, work differently for everyone (thus the mixed reviews) but I can tell you I am not paid but have use this for 2 weeks and can say that as someone with sensitive skin, this product not only smells amazing, CURED my underarm irritation and really works as a deodorant. column6: Merkur Heavy Duty Double Edge Razor (Blade Included)
column13: Great razor for beginners and beyond! Excellent value!
column14:
I'm getting back to DE shaving after many years away. For anyone, like me, with less than fond memories of the old gillettes, this razor is a remarkable improvement. Also much much cheaper to use over time that the current better quality cartridge razors. This thing will last more than my life time.
Very simple to use. The top unscrews and comes off. You plop the blade on and screw the top back on. The short handle on this bad boy basically prevents you from leveraging the handle and pushing down to hard. No adjustments to the razor are necessary (or possible.)

There are cheaper "starter" razors available. Don't fall for those. Spend a little more and get a very high quality product that you won't get tired of. You'll save money in the not very long run. A lot of reviewers and you tubers love this razor, even when compared to much more expensive options. I wish more stuff was made like this.

One blade comes with. Order more with the razor. I recommend the Feather brand. I have reviewed those separately.

Highly recommended.

column6: Silk'n Blue Acne Solution Device
column14:
The Silk'n Blue Acne Solution Device is advertised as a way to rid your skin of pimples, acne, and even prevent further breakouts. Using this product steadily for five days, I noticed a few things.

First of all, it is inconvenient. You aren't supposed to use it in the bathroom and there is no way that this product can be used quickly Because of the natural blue light and dermal heating, you are supposed to steadily hold the device on the infected area for more than three minutes. Of course, there isn't a time, switch, or morse code to tell the user when time is up.

Secondly, the product is expensive. For the price of this product, I can have three facials which in turn do as much good as this product did in a week of use every single day. Plus, facials are way more relaxing.

If you don't mind sitting on your couch with this device pressed to your face then this product is for you. It is definitely not for someone who only has a few minutes here and there.

Natalie S. for Amazon Vine
The dual power of natural blue light and dermal heating offers a safe, drug-free, and effective way to combat the root causes of present and future acne: the blue light destroys existing acne-causing bacteria residing beneath the skinâ€™s surface, and the dermal heating dehydrates the overproducing oil-glands

column6: Azure Pure Spa Detox Mud Mask with Antioxidant Vitamin C, No Preservatives, Kaolin and Bentonite Clay Ethically Mined in the USA,
column13: Bentonite clay, not just for beauty. Great for a variety of skin ailments and insect stings
column14:
I've used high quality Bentonite clay for years for a variety of skin ailments so I was curious how this product would measure up. Most of my experience is with calcium bentonite clay rather than sodium bentonite which is used in this product. One difference is that calcium bentonite can be consumed internally where sodium bentonite is for external use only. Which is fine because this is a face mask. But don't let that limit your use to your beauty routine only. Applying a nice thick paste of bentonite clay on wasp stings, tick bites, and other insect bites draws out the toxins and clears up the bite in just a few hours, not days. It's also fantastic on any sort of fungal rash.

I didn't read the description well enough, so I assumed this product was prehydrated based on the word "mask". That was my fault for not reading better and doesn't reflect on this product at all. I still wish it was hydrated, but it's rather difficult to hydrate clay to mask consistency (I've tried) and then store it without it drying and I assume would require additives. When mixing it is important to not use metal utensils or bowls as bentonite clay absorbs the toxins found in metals and you don't want to be putting that on your skin to be absorbed. For that reason I highly suggest using filtered or distilled water to mix it.

Upon mixing, it looked a bit lumpy, but when applying it went on nice and smooth. It had a nice smell to it, better than just plain clay does. I assume this was from the added Vitamin C. It was nice and comfortable. As it dried, I could feel some tightness as with any mask. When I washed it off, my skin felt cleaner than before even though I had just washed my face an hour before applying. It came off much easier than other masks I've used. Overall this is a great product and I will be using it often.

I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest, unbiased review. All opinions are my own.eartedly believe that all reviews should be open and honest, regardless of how the product was obtained: be it bought at a store, bought at Amazon, gotten for free or at a discount. I am fair complected with rosacea so finding a blush that suits my coloring is difficult. I also need one that isn't going to irritate my skin and cause a break out. I use Neutrogena soaps and foundation so it made sense to try this blush. In the package I received the blush Rosy plus the bronzer and the luminous powder. All can be used as a blusher but I used Rosy for blush, the bronzer to highlight areas to get a sunkist look and the luminous powder all over. You need your own brushes to apply this product. It goes on nicely and blends very well. On my pale skin with red blotches, it smooths out the colors and looks natural. If you are looking for something bold, keep looking. This is a blush that is very subtle.

At the end of the day, when I remove my makeup with a facial cleansing wipe, there is plenty of color so it stays on very well. It's just very subtle.

column6: Piona Strong Brightening Cream 3.38 Ounce 100 Gram
column13: ... hair that became infected and turned into what looked like a cystic acne spot
column14: Last year I had an ingrown hair that became infected and turned into what looked like a cystic acne spot. It stayed infected for about six months and after was left with an ugly scar.  I had the scar for about three months before trying piona. I've been using it twice a day almost three weeks without much luck but then yesterday I go to apply it and can hardly find the scar at all!! I'm so happy. I never thought the scar would fade!  It's a big jar and a little goes a long way. I'm sure, like most bleaching creams, the results probably aren't permanent, and you will probably have to maintain the results by applying cream periodically even after the scar has faded. Anyway, I am really happy with my results and would definitely recommend!

column6: Striafade Advanced Stretch Mark Cream for Removal and Prevention
column13: My stretch marks from having a baby have lightened up over a few weeks. Rather than bright red they are a pale pink.  A+
column14:
I have some crazy stretch marks from delivering my over 8lb daughter. They are all over my stomach and red, they look terrible. I know that stretch marks are permanent and no matter how much cream you use they are going to still be there but i REALLY would like them to fade from red to a skin-ish color so they aren't so obvious.
I noticed this particular stretch mark cream online and wanted to give it a try to see if i can make them less red. I've been using this for a few weeks now and I've been pretty pleased. The bottle arrived quickly by mail and was well packed to prevent leakage. The bottle contains 100mL of cream and has a pump to make it easier to get from the bottle. I had never tried stretch mark cream so I was excited to see if it would indeed work. Per the instructions on the bottle I applied this 2 times a day and I chose morning and night. In the morning, I would take my shower and then apply a good amount and gently rub it in. The cream itself is yellow in color and has a nice, light consistency that absorbs quick and doesn't leave you all greasy or stain your clothes. The scent is very light and reminds me of some sort of soap (or at least that's what I think it smells like). I will say that the scent is VERY light and doesn't interfere with my perfume scent. I have sensitive skin and psoriasis on the areas being treated and I had no itching, burning, or irritation of my psoriasis. The ingredients weren't too alarming either as I didn't see any parabens. Below is a list of the ingredients in this cream:

Palmitoyl Tripeptide-5,
Pseudoalteromonas Ferment Extract,
Cholesterol,
Ceramide EOP,
Ceramide EOS,
Ceramide NP,
Ceramide NS,
Ceramide AP,
Caprooyl-Phytosphingosine,
Caprooyl-Sphingosine,
Shea Butter,
Onion Bulb Extract,
Safflower Oil,
Chamomile Extract,
Allantoin,
Marine Collagen Hydrolysate (1%),
Glycerin,
Sodium PCA,
Retinol Molecular Film,
Idebenone,
Alpha Tocopherol,
Tea Tree Oil,
Deionised Water,
Stearic Acid,
Butylene Glycol,
Phenoxyethanol
Caprylyl Glycol,
Sorbic Acid,
Dmdmhydantoin

After a few weeks of using this Striafade, my skin is softer and looks a bit better. Usually, my stretch marks are bright red because they are fairly new and I gained 80lbs with my daughter but they have been fading into a pale shade rather than bright red. I don't expect the stretch marks to go away completely but the fact that they have faded a bit has really made me feel a bit better about how my stomach looks post-childbirth. I purchased this at the promotional price or for free to try it out and give my honest, unbiased opinion. Overall, I'm pleased that my stretch marks have lightened up and I will continue using this cream to see how light I can get them over a longer period of time.> Retinol Molecular Film,

I don't expect the stretch marks to go away completely but the fact that they have faded a bit has really made me feel a bit better about how my stomach looks post-childbirth. I purchased this at the promotional price or for free to try it out and give my honest, unbiased opinion. Overall, I'm pleased that my stretch marks have lightened up and I will continue using this cream to see how light I can get them over a longer period of time.

column6: Gillette Fusion5 ProGlide Men's Razor Blades Refills Mens Fusion Razors / Blades
column13: Best of the Best!  The blades really last long!
column14:
Before I start reviewing here I want to bust a myth: Yes, these cartridges are interchangeable with regular Fusion Proglide or Fusion Proglide Flexiball razors or the Fusion Proglide Slider 3-1. You do not need to have different versions of cartridges.

I have used safety razors for most of my shaving ages till I came across these 5 blade system. I shouldn't say I am never going back to the safety razor but it does not look like I am switching back in the near future. My initial purchase was Fusion Proglide Power with 4+1 blades as I couldn't find replacement blades at a convenient store while travelling. The next move has to be the next gen shaving kit if and when it comes out.

These are the best and the top of the line cartridges available for \\\nearly\\\\\" top of the line razors. The machining and technology is the best. It should work smoothly on most types of beards, if you have issues with these I would try different shaving creams as sometimes you just need a better moisturizer or need to let you beard soak for a while. The strips on top of the blades works for some (based on the other reviews) but I don't think they add a lot of value to me.

My experience with the blades and this purchase:
1. How long do these replacement blades last?
I shave every day on weekdays and occasionally on weekends and have to replace the blade once every ~8 weeks. I know most people recommend changing this sooner, but I learnt that if you clean your razor more often while shaving and no hair gets clogged between the blades these last a bit longer. Considering the price I think it is better to spend that extra time in rinsing more to get those additional weeks.

2. Where is cheapest price to buy these replacement pack?
As of 1st Aug 2015 - the standard internet search engines, local department stores, local membership stores I found Amazon to be the cheapest. This does not include any coupons that one can find occasionally. Do your research before you buy some. I personally do not prefer random internet sites so these were excluded from the research. Also, Amazon does get an extra star for convenience and delivery. Also, my purchase from Amazon included a $3 coupon which made it slightly more cheaper.

3. Why the 8 pack?
I did the math and figured that 8-pack should last me roughly another 60-70 weeks. Think about it, either the new technology is going to force the price lower or one will upgrade to the new better model if available.

4. Why only 4 stars?
Price. Yes, it is pennies per shave but I think there is a small room for price improvements.

I trust the company and have been using their products for a long time so I strongly recommend this product.

column6: Razorock Mudder Focker Shave Soap
column13: Now this is some great Mudder Focking soap!
column14:
I have to admit this is my first time trying a RazoRock soap and what a great surprise. I've used a lot of other artisan soaps and this is the cream of the crop. The scent is very pleasing, I would describe it as a... warm vanilla. Even my wife really enjoyed the scent, she said it reminds her of the "Vanilla Fields" cologne. It's a soft Italian style soap made in Italy, which makes it really easy to load a brush with.

A great thing about this soap is how easy it churns up into a thick silky slick lather. It really makes the razor glide across my face with the feeling of no resistance. But the best thing about this soap is how it makes my face feel after the shave. Not only is my face baby-butt smooth, but it is sooo soft. It was quite shocking how soft this soap made my skin.

This leads me to the ingredients of this soap. The one that I assume gives it it's name is the Fuller's Earth. Fuller's Earth is a type of clay and one of those miracle products made by mother nature. The benefits of Fuller's Earth are many and it is used for absorbing excess oil from skin, removes scars, improves skin complexion, treats acne, increases skin elasticity... You really begin to see the benefits of this ingredient after using the Mudder Focker soap. I can't recommend it enough, buy it now!

I LOVE this stuff. This oil is my new go-to for moisturizing my skin and hair. I purchased it after reading about the great benefits of almond oil. I was previously part of the coconut oil bandwagon, but found it too greasy, sometimes too smelly, and in a few instances, it actually caused my skin to break out (I have pretty good skin that isn't sensitive--coconut oil was the first thing in a LONG time that consistently caused me to break out). From what I could find, sweet almond oil provides many of the same benefits as coconut oil minus the greasiness and smell (I have tried organic coconut oil that is scentless, but it's still too greasy and the consistency in one jar can vary a lot between smooth and grainy).

I decided to buy this brand because from reading the label, it was the most transparent---that is, it seemed to be the "cleanest" sweet almond oil and the label didn't contain a lot of puffery. So far, I've been using it as an after-shower moisturizer and moisturizer for my hair. The oil doesn't feel greasy on my skin, and a little goes a long way, so I find that I have to be conservative in how much I use or I'll be waiting all day for it to absorb fully into my skin. The same was true when I applied it to my hair. I noticed after blow-drying my hair that it had a beautiful sheen to it and didn't feel the slightest bit greasy, clammy, or heavy. I attributed this to the sweet almond oil, as it was the only product change in my regimen. I'll continue using this product and update my review if necessary, but so far, it's a winner!

column13: I have all the scents above
column14: I have all the scents above.  They are all wonderful in a different way.  The lemongrass lift is perfect for summer.  it makes me think sunshine the moment I smooth it into my skin. Just a note that you do not need much. A little goes a long way with shea butter and you don't want to feel greasy by using too much. It does absorb into the skin nicely. I esp like it for elbows, knees and heels but then I smooth the rest into my whole body.  Lavender Bliss is heaven on earth. Ylang ylang has a sweet erotic smell and lavender is relaxing. I love this one at night.  Tea Tree Surprise is unique. It is not medicinal as some people associate with pure tea tree oil. The clove gives it a little spice and the lime gives it a hint of sweetness.  Frankincense Delight is meditative because of the combination of clary sage added to it. Clary sage is calming and frankincense is grounding. This is great for anxiety because both scents work together for mental clarity.  Eucalyptus Spring helps you to breathe. It is great for sinus and allergy sufferers. The cedarwood and peppermint are picked up in the background more then the pink grapefruit.  I also ordered the patchouli sunrise which is NOT part of the gift pack. The orange bursts through the patchouli scent to make it less earthy and more citrusy. I prefer that to straight patchouli myself because I love citrus scents personally.  Whatever your mood or what your own preference, you will find it here.

Looks less gaudy and I love it now. 2015-08-05 US 33471257 RJJYJNY3WG22M B00IK8VBWU 275619274 King Will TYRE 8mm Black Brushed Matte Finish Tungsten Carbide Ring Domed Engagement Wedding Band Comfort Fit Jewelry 5 0 0 N N Exceptional ring: handsome, durable, perfectly sized -- great for yourself or as a gift I love silver, I love decorative detail, but I also love the clean minimalist lines of bands, so it's absolutely no wonder why I've had my eye on this ring for a very long time. I wear my rings everyday. They take a beating and because of this, I've gone through so many in the past that didn't hold up. However, the one other I have that's also tungsten carbide is nearly indestructible, so when I saw this band I knew I wanted it.

I have to say that I LOVE it. This is a SOLID ring -- there's no mistake that this is well-made and seriously sturdy. The sizing is perfect -- it fits like a dream (it's sizing is perfection which isn't the case with MANY rings, especially ones ordered online). The ring is also really handsome, suitable for any gender (but I think more than sufficiently masculine for other guys who like to wear rings), and the shine that you see in the picture is precisely the same shine in person. I've worn it every day and it hasn't tarnished (and if it's like my other tungsten carbide ring that I've been wearing for years, it won't).

It also comes in really attractive packaging. The ring came in a velvet-lined faux-leather ring box with the King Will branding and insignia. This box came inside a box sleeve, and this came inside a sturdy cardboard box so that nothing was damaged in transit. I got this ring for myself (because I've wanted it for a very long time), but I imagine this would make an incredible gift to a very special friend. Overall, exceptional packaging, fabulous item, really helpful and responsive customer service too.

I ended up receiving this ring at a discount in exchange for a genuine critique. 2015-08-05 US 20018527 R30YQAQLUHH4MD B00OJFUJHQ 781252293 14k Solid Yellow Gold 4.5\" Italian Figaro Chain Baby ID Bracelet Spring Ring Clasp"

column14: This necklace is beyond cool. It's a nice weight... heavy enough that you don't feel like it's going to break or bend if you move the wrong way, but light enough that you're not constantly aware of it throughout the day. It's got joints where the different pieces connect so you can actually change the look of the dinosaur by pulling the necklace one way or the other. The chain is actually longer than I expected from the default pictures (which is a good thing) but it's also adjustable so you can really pick any length. It lays pretty flat and didn't buckle or anything when moving, showing the quality of the construction. Basically, it was so much better than I expected, especially considering it's less than $20! I'm definitely adding the black and silver versions to my wishlist. Disclaimer: I received this item at a discount in exchange for my honest review.

The abalone inlay is a beautiful blue green color that really shines and has a lot of depth. It's constructed very well. It's strong and durable. This would make a great fun gift for any girl, especially one who loves animals or sea life.This necklace could easy go from casual to more dressed up just by swapping it out with your favorite silver chain. This is a really pretty piece.

I received this product for free for my honest review.
