column13: Strangely Pretty But WATCH Out For Pricing!
column14:
Well I noticed that the price was raised form around fifty bucks to over seventy bucks the day BEFORE the "deal of the day" SPECIAL price of $41.03 with tax here in California....NICE Trick. I also was not at all amused this morning to wake up to an email from my Camelizer alert that these had NOW gone on sale direct from Amazon for only $26.24! It just keeps getting better. I honestly am beginning to understand peoples growing frustration with Amazons pricing fluctuations and yes, I AM aware of daily & sometime hourly price changes. Being aware and understanding that doesn't offer much consolation when I cash my Social Security check to buy "sale" items that a week later sell for half of THAT price however.

To these earrings. I ordered these for my wife for one simple reason and one reason alone. I had never seen this color and style anywhere before. Being completely different, I had to try them. When they arrived they didn't look good to either of us at ALL. Reason being is the gold coloring around the FAKE stones, whatever they may be. It just looked somehow cheap or gaudy or....not sure how to accurately describe it. But in our hands up close, the gold just throws ALL the coloring off to us both. But then the oddest thing happened. We also both noticed that if you hold them about 4 feet away, about the distance someone would be viewing these at, they were BEAUTIFUL! To us both and the transformation by moving them a couple feet away, is honestly pretty amazing.

Now beauty is very subjective, so who knows how you will find these? The above was the observation of both my wife and myself. Luckily I could return the ones bought on "sale" and repurchase these today at the new Amazon direct price. I give these 5 stars if observed at arms length at 2 or 3 stars if right up close. So I will average these to a 4 star item given the strange way their look changes with distance and the pricing fiasco.

column6: Unisex Multi-strand Black Leather Wrap Bracelet for Men for Women Genuine Leather Wristband with Buckle
column14: I'm a female with smallish wrists (5.5 inches) and have a very hard time finding wraps or bracelets that fit me well. This one, by the nature of its design, is fully adjustable. I've been looking for a nice leather wrap and purchased this despite the bad review. Very glad I did!  I can wrap it around my wrist 6 times. The slide clasp is more secure than I expected - I pull it the leather about a half inch through and it doesn't budge at all. The leather itself looks and smells good quality to me. The band is substantial in depth, the leather does not look thin, but the width of leather strand is not overly wide, about 5 millimeters, definitely thin like the other poster said - which I like since I think it looks more feminine.  I think the description is saying on average it is 21mm wide (under an inch), but that of course depends on how many times you can wrap it around your wrist.  For me, it's over an inch wide.  Unlike the other poster, mine came damage-free.

column13: Beautiful, comfortable ring and great service from Metal Masters!
column14:
I purchased this ring as an engagement band because I wanted something durable and hypoallergenic. I'm allergic to even surgical stainless steel, so all my jewelry is titanium. I'm also hard on my hands and very active, so even if I could wear gold or silver, I would annihilate it in short order.

I also wanted something non-traditional, pretty and elegant, without being overly feminine. This fits the bill and suits me right down to the ground. I wear a size 7 ring, and since this is a comfort fit band, I ordered a half size smaller and the fit is perfect.

I'm not a jeweler, but to my eye, the CZ's in this ring are perfectly cut and set absolutely flush and even. They catch the light wonderfully with a smoky, gunmetal fire. The way the princess cut stones sparkle around the circumference of the band reminds me of a chasing LED light. Very nice sparkle, and since it's an eternity band, it glitters from the palm side too, which is really nice.

The titanium band means that it's very lightweight and easy to wear. The color of the titanium is a dark, true black. I don't know if it's plated, painted or anodized, but I'm hoping the color will last for the life of the ring. I haven't worn it much yet, and I've taken it off before washing, sleeping, and doing anything hard on my hands. I'll update this review after more wear time.

The band does have some thickness to it's profile - maybe 2 mms thick or so. There is also a lip where the CZ's meet the metal. I wouldn't call it sharp, but definitely edged. I don't think you could manage to scratch skin with this, but I'd probably take it off if I were bathing a baby or something. I can feel the edge if I press my fingers firmly together, but with normal wear and activity, I don't feel it at all. It's due to this design that some reviewers say it gets dirty easily. I did get a tiny bit of cruft showing up in mine, so I simply used a clean, dry, soft bristled toothbrush to clear any debris from the channel setting and it was back to looking like new. Easy care if you ask me.

This is a great ring, but the best part has been dealing with Metal Masters. I ordered two other rings from them in two different styles for my partner. We had to return one because she didn't like the style, one for a loose stone (the only thing that was an error on Metal Masters part), and finally, one because she changed her mind on the size. I also emailed them to ask a question about the ring's finish. In every instance, Metal Masters was speedy, professional, polite and very helpful. They responded to my messages the same day, they shipped the same day they approved the return, and they were generally efficient and made my buying experience as low friction as possible. In the case of the loose stone they even provided a pre-paid return envelope when they sent the replacement. All around good service. I would happily buy jewelry from them again!.ris from the channel setting and it was back to looking like new. Easy care if you ask me.

column6: Aiyaya 1carat Cut Cz Solitaire Bridal Ring
column13: This ring is beautiful, one of the most beautiful CZ stones I have seen. You will be happily surprised.
column14:
I am always skeptical of Cubic zirconia. Cubic zirconia (CZ) is the cubic crystalline form of zirconium dioxide (ZrO2). The synthesized material is hard, optically flawless and usually colorless, but may be made in a variety of different colors. It should not be confused with zircon, which is a zirconium silicate (ZrSiO4). It is sometimes erroneously called "cubic zirconium".

Because of its low cost, durability, and close visual likeness to diamond, synthetic cubic zirconia has remained the most gemologically and economically important competitor for diamonds since commercial production began in 1976. Its main competitor as a synthetic gemstone is a more recently cultivated material, synthetic moissanite.

I have seen some stones that are far from what they are advertised as being "like the real thing" - very apparent they are not. I was pretty sure I could write quite the review if this ring didn't meet my expectations --- I am more than impressed!

What You Get: (1) 1 carat Princess (square) Cut Cz Solitaire, set in a 4 prong, 18K white gold plated, with textured tone, bridal ring. (1) Red, drawstring felt ring bag.

PROs:

âž”Cubic zirconia vs diamond.There are a few key features of cubic zirconia which distinguish it from diamond:

âž”âž” Hardness: cubic zirconia has a rating of approximately 8 on Mohs hardness scale vs. a rating of 10 for diamond.

âž”âž” Specific gravity: the density of cubic zirconia is about 1.7 times that of diamond.

âž”âž” Refractive index: cubic zirconia has a refractive index of 2.15â€“2.18, compared to a diamond's 2.42.

âž”âž” Dispersion is very high at 0.058â€“0.066, exceeding a diamond's 0.044.

âž”âž” Cut: cubic zirconia gemstones may be cut differently from diamonds. The facet edges can be rounded or "smooth".

âž”âž”Color: only the rarest of diamonds are truly colorless, most having a tinge of yellow or brown to some extent. By comparison, a cubic zirconia is often entirely colorless: equivalent to a perfect "D" on diamond's color grading scale. Other desirable colors of cubic zirconia can be produced including near colorless, yellow, pink, purple, green, and even multicolored.

Thoughts: The princess cut of this stone is flawless, very clear in an X pattern, it has fire - I mean, it really sparkles and the array of colors that play off the light looks very convincing, very close to the real thing. There is a play of color in any angle the ring is displayed.

âž” Size. This princess cut stone is very realistic. Very believable. It is 1/4" inch x 1/4" inch with a depth of 1/8" inches.

âž” Setting. The stone is set in (4) classic triangular prongs, which hold the stone at each of it's corners - in each prong there is a small cutout to allow light to filter into the stone. There is a 1.59mm open hole in ring, directly under the pronged setting, to allow light in as well. It is only 1/4" inches high, which is nice because it won't get caught on clothing etc.

âž” The white gold plated ring features a beveled band - the inside is flat, but the outside does not dome, like most rings, it's sides meet to form a tapered peak, starting at 1.25mm which gets taller / thicker in proximity to the stone and meets the prongs, half way, at the highest points (1.56mm) on either side. This band is very comfortable on the finger.

CONs:

âž” I honestly had no qualms about this ring. I wished it would have come in a ring box, and not a ring bag, for gifting.

CONCLUSION:

This ring is beautiful, one of the most beautiful CZ stones I have seen. You will be happily surprised. Would make a perfect substitute while you're saving up to buy the 3x monthly salary ring.

column14:
We needed crystal stud earrings for a dance performance and running out for a quick piercing wasn't an option. I'm so glad I found these magnetic earrings on Amazon.

We wore them for an hour when they first arrived and they were a little bothersome. But the next day we were able to wear them longer and longer... This was fine as we only really needed them for about an hour. As we got used to them, they didn't hurt our ears as much. But they did leave a serious impression on our earlobes if we wore them for too long.

The magnets are incredibly strong and held on through some pretty enthusiastic dancing.

Overall I was pleased with these earrings. And the pain factor associated with the magnets is less that what you'd get with most piercings.

This is my second pair of earrings from the Sitara Collection and there will be more in the future. The earrings are crafted by women in India and definitely show master craftsmanship. Part of the proceeds also go to support a school in India which is wonderful!
The size is perfect, the stones are faceted beautifully, they sparkle in the dimmest room. The ear wires are not the flimsy feel like you sometimes get with silver dangle earrings. I was lucky enough to receive a discount in exchange for an honest review of these and I honestly love love love them! These were going to be a gift for my mother but I'm keeping them, hope she doesn't read my review!

column14: This is a lovely ring, but it's not the sapphire blue as shown in the picture. It's a much lighter blue, and in certain lights has a purpley-blue tinge to it. There are certain angles of light that sparkle pink in one of the facets, but that happens very rarely, and you really have to look for it. I was pleasantly surprise to find there are very small stones along the sides adjacent to the center stone. I'm sure the description mentions them, but for some reason I had it in my head that was just a part of the design of the setting. I think it looks very nice on the finger. I considered returning it because of the difference in color, but decided it looks quite nice, even if lighter, and I do like the setting. After all, if I wanted a sapphire colored stone, I probably should have bought a sapphire. I was going to take off one star due to the color difference between the photo and the ring, but I tried to take a photo of it myself to upload, and all of the photos I took it came out looking as dark as the photo on the product page.

column13: Great masculine cross to wear or gift
column14:
I don't wear jewelry. I know guys do, but I just don't. I also personally didn't think it was appropriate to wear dog tags as jewelry. When I saw this, though, I made the exception.

Believers wage spiritual warfare every day, so I'm okay with wearing this. It's also quite understated, and can be worn with just about anything. What wasn't clear in the product photo is that the loop for the chain moves freely on a pin. The photo led me to believe the loop was fixed, but either way is fine.

The back is flat, and on the front, the cross is flat, but the bezel is polished. Very nice combination. I included photos to show the thickness of the tag, which is a little more than two U.S. quarters high. The back looks like it's ready to engrave. I can't wait to add my favorite verse.

Highly recommended, especially since its price here on Amazon is a fraction of its selling price elsewhere!

column6: Pack of 12 Pairs 12 Color 10mm Bead Faux Pearl Stud Earrings
column14: I'm one of those people that is constantly losing just one earring. It drives me nuts, so I decided to try buying 4 packs of these (for back ups).  I was concerned that given the price they would look cheap, but they do not at all.  As other reviewers have commented, the backs are cheap clear plastic, so if you wear your hair up it is a dead giveaway that they are cheap. I went ahead and bought a set of silver earring backs (http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00BBAXQP4?redirect=true&ref_=cm_cr_ryp_prd_ttl_sol_2) to relieve this problem, and now you seriously can't tell they are fake (the white, gold and grey, that is... the other colors are obviously fake, but fun and vibrant, and don't appear to to be cheap).  I'd also note, that the size is perfect - larger studs tend to droop in a sloppy manner, but these stay perky.  Once I run through my backup earrings (inevitably) I will certainly refill.

One year update: the piece is just as nice, shiny and no pieces missing as the first day!! 100% worth $5 atleast.!

I originally had a beautiful Claddagh ring that I lost after 10 years of having it and I want to find a nice replacement as the original one I had doubled in price. I looked for days and still haven't found the one I want, so I decided to look for a cheap temp one. It had to be silver or white gold because fake things instantly turn green on me. I bought this after reading some reviews, and decided if anything I'm out $5.

I'm amazed this goes for $5! It looks amazing! I'm not sure how long it will hold up, or when the CZ will fall out, but for now it helps keep that spot until I buy my new one. Its bright and lovely and shiny. The pictures don't do it justice. But you can tell how nice it looks compared to my engagement ring which is 2carats and white good.

column6: Jstyle Mens Vintage Leather Wrist Band Brown Rope Bracelet Bangle
column14:
I'm giving this product a 5-star rating because there is no reason to detract any points. It fits exactly as expected and is exactly as advertised. This is a pretty simple thing: a leather men's bracelet with some metal pieces on it. This would be a pretty difficult thing to "screw up," but it does happen occasionally. With respect to this piece, there are no screw-ups.

A note on its visual appearance: When i told my wife I had ordered a bracelet on Amazon, she rolled her eyes and expressed extreme skepticism, because she is not "into guys who wear bracelets." The item arrived, I put it on, and the next day she noticed it and said, "Hey, that looks good!" So there you go - anecdotal evidence that this bracelet is attractive enough to even win over women who don't like men's bracelets. Also: my baby daughter loves playing with it, but I guess that's beside the point...

Sterling Silver, Freshwater Cultured Pearl, and Swarovski Zirconia Pendant Necklace, 18\"	Jewelry	4	0	0	Y	N	Great for day-to-night transitions	This is a beautiful necklace that is perfect for a dressy occasion as well as a business setting.  The single teardrop pearl combined with the large cubic zirconia (CZ) gives this piece a look of simple elegance.  When worn with the CZ facing outwards, the necklace is very sparkly and appropriate for a dressy evening event.  The CZ is surrounded by smaller stones, and the effect is too glitzy for office wear, in my opinion.  However, if worn backwards, the CZ is not visible.  Instead, there is the simple pearl that appears to be in a plain silver setting.  This way is best for a business setting.  This would be the perfect necklace to wear to work backwards and then to switch it forwards for an evening event that same day.  The quality of the workmanship is good, and the pearl is a nice size, uniformity, and color.  My only (small) complaint is that the sterling silver chain is a bit chunky and not as finely crafted as the rest of the piece.  I think this pendant would look better on a chain of higher quality.	2015-08-05

column6: King Will Unisex 8mm Wooden Inlay Cubic Zirconi Polished Tungsten Ring Wedding Band Comfort Fit
column14:
First things first, I received this ring free for the purpose of review. Hopefully, my observations and impressions will prove helpful to you in your decision making. If you have questions, feel free to post them in the comments section, and I'll do my best to answer based on my own experience with the product.

What you're getting with this order:

(1) "King Will" Unisex 8mm Wooden Inlay, Cubic Zirc. Tungsten Carbide ring.

What is Tungsten Carbide, and how does it compare to Tungsten?: Tungsten is an element and Tungsten Carbide an alloy. You will find differing opinions, but many feel that Tungsten Carbide is the better material for a ring because it is essentially scratch resistant to anything but diamond. Both have very similar characteristics when it comes to looks, and the two terms are frequently used interchangeably.

The "King Will" 8mm wooden inlay Tungsten Carbide ring: This ring features the polished silver look of tungsten carbide on the outside with beveled edges while a dark wooden inlay dominates the center of the ring. A single cubic zirconia stands alone in the middle of the ring, not too large or showy, but enough to reflect the light and make its presence known. The dark hue of the wooden inlay contrasts nicely with the tungsten making for a unique and attractive band. The inner ring is comfort fit, meaning that it is contoured and is easier to slide on/off your finger compared to flat bands.

Bottom line: This is a unique Tungsten Carbide ring that by nature of its construction is very durable and highly scratch resistant. It is well represented in the product description photos, but with the actual product, the wooden inlay is actually more visible. The craftsmanship is excellent. I don't hesitate to recommend it to anyone looking for a durable and stylish band, and at its current price point one has very little to lose. Enjoy!

Rhodium plating means the bright, white metal won't tarnish. To many women that's a plus. A lot of gals also like lever back earrings, because you're not going to loose the backings as with studs or post styles. That said, I shop year round for holiday and birthday gifts in order to get the best prices. When I saw these at a very low price, I first ordered the blue topaz for myself, and then placed an order for each of the other colors to use as gifts. Here's a breakdown color by color:

Blue topaz - the topaz stones are a very light, ice blue and are clear with no visible inclusions

Amethyst - the pair I received are clear, clean, and a much darker purple than pictured on Amazon's product page, more like the product page picture of the matching necklace

Garnet - a deep, rich, clear, almost Zinfandel red, these are probably the most impressive of all the gemstone options and will be perfect for holiday outfits

Peridot - these stones were a little disappointing in that they were pale and cloudy

Citrine - although so pale they're almost clear, there are no inclusions in the earrings I received

The created white sapphire stones are bright and clear; they're small enough to give a diamond look without the diamond price. Each pair of earrings appears to be well made. Durable. Amazon's packaging makes them ideal for gift giving, whether as stocking stuffers or a small gift with a lot of bang for the buck. I'd recommend the blue topaz, amethyst and garnet versions. You might receive a better peridot pair than I did, and your citrine pair might have more depth of color without losing any clarity, but I can't personally recommend those. It's a matter of taste. The earrings aren't large, but they *are* noticeable. They measure just over 1/2 inch in length (not including wires) by just under 1/2 inch in width. She could wear these to work. column6: King Will 8mm Tungsten Carbide High Polish Pipe Cut and Cubic Zirconia Inlay Wedding Band Ring
column14:
First things first, I received this ring free for the purpose of review. Hopefully, my observations and impressions will prove helpful to you in your decision making. If you have questions, feel free to post them in the comments section, and I'll do my best to answer based on my own experience with the product.

What you're getting with this order:

(1) "King Will" 8mm Cubic zirconia inlay Tungsten Carbide ring.

What is Tungsten Carbide, and how does it compare to Tungsten?: Tungsten is an element and Tungsten Carbide an alloy. You will find differing opinions, but many feel that Tungsten Carbide is the better material for a ring because it is essentially scratch resistant to anything but diamond. Both have very similar characteristics when it comes to looks, and the two terms are frequently used interchangeably.

The "King Will" 8mm cubic zirconia inlay Tungsten Carbide ring: This ring features the polished dark silver of tungsten carbide on the outside with beveled edges while an inlay half black and half cubic zirconia band dominates the center of the ring. The black of the inlay and the shimmer of the cubic zirconias contrasts beautifully with the tungsten making for a unique and attractive band. The inner ring is comfort fit, meaning that it is contoured and is easier to slide on/off your finger compared to flat bands.

Bottom line: This is a unique Tungsten Carbide ring that by nature of its construction is very durable and highly scratch resistant. It is well represented in the product description photos, but with the actual product, the cubic zirconias are actually more visible with the light playing off of their repeating pattern. The craftsmanship is excellent. I don't hesitate to recommend it to anyone looking for a durable and stylish band, and at its current price point one has very little to lose. Enjoy!

column13: I love the 'secret' message, a great inexpensive everyday ring or promise ring...
column14:
I received this ring in a women's size 7 and it seems to fit very well, true to size. When it first arrived I was surprised at how lightweight it is, it almost feels like it is made of plastic at first. But it is very comfortable to wear for a long time and slides on and off my finger very easily.
The inscription "you are my only love" is VERY tiny. It is almost impossible for me to find it at first. But I kind of like it that way, it's like the ring has a secret message on it.
I also appreciate that it does not tarnish and is very non-allergenic.
The inside has engraving too, but it's not a secret message, it is simply stating that the ring is stainless steel.
The ring seems very unisex, would look fine on a man or woman. I think this ring is perfect for a promise ring when money is tight, or if you are in a situation where you can't wear expensive jewelry. This ring would be the perfect every day ring to wear. I received a sample of this ring for review purposes and I'm pleased with it.

column6: Sterling Silver Oxidized Celtic Knot Drop Earrings
column14:
Numerous reviews state that the picture of the earrings is on the deceptive side, since it makes them appear larger than they are. The reviews are right. These are not, by any means, statement earrings. What they are is relatively small, delicate earrings whose silver catches the light beautifully. The knot design is really well done and the openness of the loops is lovely and delicate-looking. The actual part of the earring that dangles is probably just over an inch long. They sit comfortably in the ear and aren't at all heavy, but they have just enough weight to them that you can feel them swing when you move your head.

Given the small-ish size and delicate design, these earrings really can - and do - work for everything from everyday wear to special occasions; they look just as appropriate with a casual outfit of a shirt and shorts or jeans, as they do with a dress, so they really are very versatile and one can get a lot of use/wear out of them.

I've mentioned that they look delicate and aren't heavy, but that doesn't mean that they're easily breakable. They don't feel flimsy at all, so bends, breaks or the earrings coming apart don't seem to be things to worry about.

I think the only other thing to note is that they come in a simple, yet sturdy black box that one can easily use to store these earrings or anything else one so chooses.

The bottom line is that these are small, lovely, and exceedingly versatile earrings, and I'd definitely recommend them to anyone looking for some earrings out of which they can get a lot of use.

First things first, I received this ring free for the purpose of review. Hopefully, my observations and impressions will prove helpful to you in your decision making. If you have questions, feel free to post them in the comments section, and I'll do my best to answer based on my own experience with the product.

What you're getting with this order:

(1) "King Will" 8mm Black and gold carbon fiber inlay Tungsten Carbide ring.

What is Tungsten Carbide, and how does it compare to Tungsten?: Tungsten is an element and Tungsten Carbide an alloy. You will find differing opinions, but many feel that Tungsten Carbide is the better material for a ring because it is essentially scratch resistant to anything but diamond. Both have very similar characteristics when it comes to looks, and the two terms are frequently used interchangeably.

The "King Will" Black and Gold 8mm carbon fiber inlay Tungsten Carbide ring: This ring features a dark tungsten carbide on the outside with beveled edges while a carbon fiber inlay dominates the center of the ring. The black of the carbon fiber is ensconced in the darkness of the tungsten, making itself known when it reflects light. Gold flecks in the carbon fiber contrast with the blacks of the tungsten and carbon to form a unique and attractive band. The inner ring is comfort fit, meaning that it is contoured and is easier to slide on/off your finger compared to flat bands.

Bottom line: This is a unique Tungsten Carbide ring that by nature of its construction is very durable and highly scratch resistant. It is well represented in the product description photos, but with the actual product, the carbon fiber is actually more visible with the light playing off its modern pattern. The craftsmanship is excellent. I don't hesitate to recommend it to anyone looking for a durable and stylish band, and at its current price point one has very little to lose. column6: I Love You to the Moon and Back Bracelet Fashion Jewelry Bracelets From Minals! A Bangle Bracelets with Charms, Sentimental Jewelry for Best Friend or Couples Gifts
column14: This bracelet is gorgeous! It has the saying " I love you to the moon and back" on it which I've said to my daughter ever since she was little. Her 19th Birthday is coming up so I bought this bracelet thinking it would make a very heartfelt gift from me to her. It's silver, which is my daughter's favorite and she's going to love the saying on it!  I also like that it is silver, and it's very comparable to Alex and Ani bracelets, which have been very trendy for a while now. It has the most gorgeous pearl charm on it that I love. Along with a diamond like crystal charm, a key to my heart charm and a round crystal studded charm. And of course the I Love You and to the moon and back charms as well. So that's six charms total! Alex and Ani only come with one charm per bracelet, so right there you have a considerable savings!  Plus this bangle bracelet is adjustable so one size fits all, very convenient! I especially love the care they took in presenting this lovely bracelet in a silk lined box. Plus it was shipped fast and packaged appropriately. I did receive a slight discount on this bracelet in exchange I would give my honest opinion. Honestly, it looks just like an Alex and Ani bracelet except it has more charms and the price is reasonable. I love this bracelet so much and can't wait to give it to my daughter on her birthday, she's going to love it!

column14: Sad, sad, sad! This necklace is so cool looking in person. I bought it especially for a wedding I was attending, and it looked fantastic. I even bought a new clutch to match it. Unfortunately, the necklace broke in two places before the end of the night! That was the first time I'd ever worn it. I contacted Amazon for a replacement. As usual, their customer service was fantastic--I printed out a return label, packed up my necklace, and someone came by to pick it up the next day. The day after that (two days after I requested it), my replacement necklace arrived, and this time, it ARRIVED already broken. I can't believe this piece originally retailed for more than a hundred bucks--there must be some very disappointed consumers out there! I purchased it on sale and am reasonably crafty so I'm considering keeping the replacement necklace and trying to fix it myself. It is THAT beautiful. But I paid for a finished necklace and I would rather not have to carry pliers in my purse every time I wear it in case it breaks mid-outing.

Hopefully, my observations and impressions will prove helpful to you in your decision making. If you have questions, feel free to post them in the comments section, and I'll do my best to answer based on my own experience with the product.

What you're getting with this order:

(1) "King Will" 8mm Blue and Black carbon fiber inlay Tungsten Carbide ring.

What is Tungsten Carbide, and how does it compare to Tungsten?: Tungsten is an element and Tungsten Carbide an alloy. You will find differing opinions, but many feel that Tungsten Carbide is the better material for a ring because it is essentially scratch resistant to anything but diamond. Both have very similar characteristics when it comes to looks, and the two terms are frequently used interchangeably.

The "King Will" Blue and Black 8mm carbon fiber inlay Tungsten Carbide ring: This ring features the polished dark silver of tungsten carbide on the outside with beveled edges while a carbon fiber inlay dominates the center of the ring with flecks of blue noticeable. The black of the carbon fiber contrasts beautifully with the tungsten making for a unique and attractive band, and the blue adds a third color that makes this particular ring unique. The inner ring is comfort fit, meaning that it is contoured and is easier to slide on/off your finger compared to flat bands.

Bottom line: This is a unique Tungsten Carbide ring that by nature of its construction is very durable and highly scratch resistant. It is well represented in the product description photos, but with the actual product, the carbon fiber is actually more visible with the light playing off its modern pattern. The craftsmanship is excellent. I don't hesitate to recommend it to anyone looking for a durable and stylish band, and at its current price point one has very little to lose. I got the rings pretty quick. 2015-08-05 US 30016700 R29A3QFC1VHC4S B00QRJ0R10 722865784 Casoty Jewelry Star Trek Cufflinks Starfleet Command Cufflinks in Gift Box Jewelry 5 0 0 N N Cuff Links That Should be Taken Seriously **I was sent this product in exchange for my opinion of it**

Cufflinks, at least as early as I could remember, have always been over the edge of men's luxury items. Meaning, they are small, not easily found and a little pricey. Usually cuff links are 35$+ and can go much higher depending on the place you buy them at. Not speaking of the links that are made of precious metal, in general, they are made the same--metal. Therefore most will have a very high mark up versus what it cost to make them.

Take the Casoty Star Trek links. Comparing these to cuff links that I paid over 60$ for at a very common men's suit shop, these are the exact same quality. The metal is shiny (not worn or tarnished), the paint isn't chipping, and the paint (plaque) is glossed over with clearcoat--just like my others.

Meaning, if you happen to like the Star Trek symbolization, there is no reason to go for another maker that is higher priced, nor worry about whether these are simply going to be costume jewelry, not to be taken seriously. Rather, you could put a 75$ price tag on it, make it limited edition inside a popular men's shop and it would sell. No one would give it anymore thought.

The pros of this ring:

1) It fit like we expected it to which was a huge plus considering some companies sizing charts are a bit off from what you would find in stores.
2) The camo on the ring is really nice. It isn't cheap or cheesy looking at all.
3) The ring is amazingly lightweight which is a huge plus.

The cons of the ring:

The only con we found was that it may feel a bit too lightweight and almost cheap to people who have never worn titanium.

Overall, we are very happy with the purchase. The only reason we are giving a 4 instead of 5 star is because the coating on the ring doesn't seem to be that durable. If it holds up over the next week of his work, yard work, and putting it through its paces then I'll come back and update.
